208 
209 void map::generate( const tripoint_abs_omt &p, const time_point &when )
210 {
211  dbg( D_INFO ) << "map::generate( g[" << g.get() << "], p[" << p << "], "
212  "when[" << to_string( when ) << "] )";
213 
214  const tripoint_abs_sm p_sm = project_to<coords::sm>( p );
215  set_abs_sub( p_sm );
216 
217  // First we have to create new submaps and initialize them to 0 all over
218  // We create all the submaps, even if we're not a tinymap, so that map
219  // generation which overflows won't cause a crash. At the bottom of this
220  // function, we save the upper-left 4 submaps, and delete the rest.
221  // Mapgen is not z-level aware yet. Only actually initialize current z-level
222  // because other submaps won't be touched.
223  for( int gridx = 0; gridx < my_MAPSIZE; gridx++ ) {
224  for( int gridy = 0; gridy < my_MAPSIZE; gridy++ ) {
225  const size_t grid_pos = get_nonant( { gridx, gridy, p_sm.z()} );
226  if( getsubmap( grid_pos ) ) {
227  debugmsg( "Submap already exists at (%d, %d, %d)", gridx, gridy, p_sm.z() );
228  continue;
229  }
230  setsubmap( grid_pos, new submap() );
231  // TODO: memory leak if the code below throws before the submaps get stored/deleted!
232  }
233  }
234  oter_id terrain_type = overmap_buffer.ter( p );
235 
236  // This attempts to scale density of zombies inversely with distance from the nearest city.
237  // In other words, make city centers dense and perimeters sparse.
238  float density = 0.0f;
239  for( int i = -MON_RADIUS; i <= MON_RADIUS; i++ ) {
240  for( int j = -MON_RADIUS; j <= MON_RADIUS; j++ ) {
241  density += overmap_buffer.ter( p + point( i, j ) )->get_mondensity();
242  }
243  }
244  density = density / 100;
245 
246  mapgendata dat( p, *this, density, when, nullptr );
247  draw_map( dat );
248 
249  // At some point, we should add region information so we can grab the appropriate extras
250  map_extras &this_ex = region_settings_map["default"].region_extras[terrain_type->get_extras()];
251  map_extras ex = this_ex.filtered_by( dat );
252  if( this_ex.chance > 0 && ex.values.empty() && !this_ex.values.empty() ) {
253  DebugLog( D_WARNING, D_MAP_GEN ) << "Overmap terrain " << terrain_type->get_type_id().str() <<
254  " (extra type \"" << terrain_type->get_extras() <<
255  "\") zlevel = " << p.z() <<
256  " is out of range of all assigned map extras. Skipping map extra generation.";
257  } else if( ex.chance > 0 && one_in( ex.chance ) ) {
258  map_extra_id *extra = ex.values.pick();
259  if( extra == nullptr ) {
260  debugmsg( "failed to pick extra for type %s (ter = %s)", terrain_type->get_extras(),
261  terrain_type->get_type_id().str() );
262  } else {
263  MapExtras::apply_function( *ex.values.pick(), *this, tripoint_abs_sm( abs_sub ) );
264  }
265  }
266 
267  const overmap_static_spawns &spawns = terrain_type->get_static_spawns();
268 
269  float spawn_density = 1.0f;
270  if( MonsterGroupManager::is_animal( spawns.group ) ) {
271  spawn_density = get_option< float >( "SPAWN_ANIMAL_DENSITY" );
272  } else {
273  spawn_density = get_option< float >( "SPAWN_DENSITY" );
274  }
275 
276  // Apply a multiplier to the number of monsters for really high densities.
277  float odds_after_density = spawns.chance * spawn_density;
278  const float max_odds = 100 - ( 100 - spawns.chance ) / 2.0f;
279  float density_multiplier = 1.0f;
280  if( odds_after_density > max_odds ) {
281  density_multiplier = 1.0f * odds_after_density / max_odds;
282  odds_after_density = max_odds;
283  }
284  const int spawn_count = roll_remainder( density_multiplier );
285 
286  if( spawns.group && x_in_y( odds_after_density, 100 ) ) {
287  int pop = spawn_count * rng( spawns.population.min, spawns.population.max );
288  for( ; pop > 0; pop-- ) {
289  std::vector<MonsterGroupResult> spawn_details =
290  MonsterGroupManager::GetResultFromGroup( spawns.group, &pop );
291  for( const MonsterGroupResult &mgr : spawn_details ) {
292  if( !mgr.name ) {
293  continue;
294  }
295  if( const std::optional<tripoint> pt =
296  random_point( *this, [this]( const tripoint & n ) {
297  return passable( n );
298  } ) ) {
299  const tripoint_bub_ms pnt = tripoint_bub_ms( pt.value() );
300  add_spawn( mgr, pnt );
301  }
302  }
303  }
304  }
305 
306  // Okay, we know who our neighbors are. Let's draw!
307  // And finally save used submaps and delete the rest.
308  for( int i = 0; i < my_MAPSIZE; i++ ) {
309  for( int j = 0; j < my_MAPSIZE; j++ ) {
310  dbg( D_INFO ) << "map::generate: submap (" << i << "," << j << ")";
311 
312  const tripoint pos( i, j, p_sm.z() );
313  if( i <= 1 && j <= 1 ) {
314  saven( pos );
315  } else {
316  const size_t grid_pos = get_nonant( pos );
317  delete getsubmap( grid_pos );
318  setsubmap( grid_pos, nullptr );
319  }
320  }
321  }
322 }

329 /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
330 /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
331 ///// mapgen_function class.
332 ///// all sorts of ways to apply our hellish reality to a grid-o-squares
333 
334 class mapgen_basic_container
335 {
336  private:
337  std::vector<std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function>> mapgens_;
338  //mapgens that need to be recalculated with a function when spawned
339  std::vector<std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function>> mapgens_to_recalc_;
340  weighted_int_list<std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function>> weights_;
341 
342  public:
343  int add( const std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function> &ptr ) {
344  cata_assert( ptr );
345  if( std::find( mapgens_.begin(), mapgens_.end(), ptr ) != mapgens_.end() ) {
346  debugmsg( "Adding duplicate mapgen to container!" );
347  }
348  mapgens_.push_back( ptr );
349  return mapgens_.size() - 1;
350  }
351  /**
352  * Pick a mapgen function randomly and call its generate function.
353  * This basically runs the mapgen functions with the given @ref mapgendata
354  * as argument.
355  * @return Whether the mapgen function has been run. It may not get run if
356  * the list of mapgen functions is effectively empty.
357  * @p hardcoded_weight Weight for an additional entry. If that entry is chosen,
358  * false is returned. If unsure, just use 0 for it.
359  */
360  bool generate( mapgendata &dat, const int hardcoded_weight ) {
361  for( const std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function> &ptr : mapgens_to_recalc_ ) {
362  dialogue d( get_talker_for( get_avatar() ), std::make_unique<talker>() );
363  int const weight = ptr->weight.evaluate( d );
364  if( weight >= 1 ) {
365  weights_.add_or_replace( ptr, weight );
366  } else {
367  weights_.remove( ptr );
368  }
369  }
370 
371  if( hardcoded_weight > 0 &&
372  rng( 1, weights_.get_weight() + hardcoded_weight ) > weights_.get_weight() ) {
373  return false;
374  }
375  const std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function> *const ptr = weights_.pick();
376  if( !ptr ) {
377  return false;
378  }
379  cata_assert( *ptr );
380  ( *ptr )->generate( dat );
381  return true;
382  }
383  /**
384  * Calls @ref mapgen_function::setup and sets up the internal weighted list using
385  * the **current** value of @ref mapgen_function::weight. This value may have
386  * changed since it was first added, so this is needed to recalculate the weighted list.
387  */
388  void setup() {
389  for( const std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function> &ptr : mapgens_ ) {
390  cata_assert( ptr->weight );
391  if( ptr->weight.is_constant() ) {
392  int const weight = ptr->weight.constant();
393  if( weight < 1 ) {
394  continue; // rejected!
395  }
396  weights_.add( ptr, weight );
397  } else {
398  mapgens_to_recalc_.push_back( ptr );
399  }
400 
401  ptr->setup();
402  }
403  // Not needed anymore, pointers are now stored in weights_ (or not used at all)
404  mapgens_.clear();
405  }
406  void finalize_parameters() {
407  for( auto &mapgen_function_ptr : weights_ ) {
408  mapgen_function_ptr.obj->finalize_parameters();
409  }
410  }
411  void check_consistency() const {
412  for( const auto &mapgen_function_ptr : weights_ ) {
413  mapgen_function_ptr.obj->check();
414  }
415  }
416  void check_consistency_with( const oter_t &ter ) const {
417  for( const auto &mapgen_function_ptr : weights_ ) {
418  mapgen_function_ptr.obj->check_consistent_with( ter );
419  }
420  }
421 
422  mapgen_parameters get_mapgen_params( mapgen_parameter_scope scope,
423  const std::string &context ) const {
424  mapgen_parameters result;
425  for( const weighted_object<int, std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function>> &p : weights_ ) {
426  result.check_and_merge( p.obj->get_mapgen_params( scope ), context );
427  }
428  return result;
429  }
430 };
431 
432 class mapgen_factory
433 {
434  private:
435  std::map<std::string, mapgen_basic_container> mapgens_;
436 
437  /// Collect all the possible and expected keys that may get used with @ref pick.
438  static std::set<std::string> get_usages() {
439  std::set<std::string> result;
440  for( const oter_t &elem : overmap_terrains::get_all() ) {
441  result.insert( elem.get_mapgen_id() );
442  result.insert( elem.id.str() );
443  }
444  // Why do I have to repeat the MapExtras here? Wouldn't "MapExtras::factory" be enough?
445  for( const map_extra &elem : MapExtras::mapExtraFactory().get_all() ) {
446  if( elem.generator_method == map_extra_method::mapgen ) {
447  result.insert( elem.generator_id );
448  }
449  }
450  // Used in C++ code only, see calls to `oter_mapgen.generate()` below
451  result.insert( "lab_1side" );
452  result.insert( "lab_4side" );
453  result.insert( "lab_finale_1level" );
454  return result;
455  }
456 
457  public:
458  void reset() {
459  mapgens_.clear();
460  }
461  /// @see mapgen_basic_container::setup
462  void setup() {
463  for( std::pair<const std::string, mapgen_basic_container> &omw : mapgens_ ) {
464  omw.second.setup();
465  inp_mngr.pump_events();
466  }
467  // Dummy entry, overmap terrain null should never appear and is
468  // therefore never generated.
469  mapgens_.erase( "null" );
470  }
471  void finalize_parameters() {
472  for( std::pair<const std::string, mapgen_basic_container> &omw : mapgens_ ) {
473  omw.second.finalize_parameters();
474  }
475  }
476  void check_consistency() const {
477  // Cache all strings that may get looked up here so we don't have to go through
478  // all the sources for them upon each loop.
479  const std::set<std::string> usages = get_usages();
480  for( const std::pair<const std::string, mapgen_basic_container> &omw : mapgens_ ) {
481  omw.second.check_consistency();
482  if( usages.count( omw.first ) == 0 ) {
483  debugmsg( "Mapgen %s is not used by anything!", omw.first );
484  }
485  }
486  }
487  /**
488  * Checks whether we have an entry for the given key.
489  * Note that the entry itself may not contain any valid mapgen instance
490  * (could all have been removed via @ref erase).
491  */
492  bool has( const std::string &key ) const {
493  return mapgens_.count( key ) != 0;
494  }
495  const mapgen_basic_container *find( const std::string &key ) const {
496  auto it = mapgens_.find( key );
497  if( it == mapgens_.end() ) {
498  return nullptr;
499  } else {
500  return &it->second;
501  }
502  }
503  /// @see mapgen_basic_container::add
504  int add( const std::string &key, const std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function> &ptr ) {
505  return mapgens_[key].add( ptr );
506  }
507  /// @see mapgen_basic_container::generate
508  bool generate( mapgendata &dat, const std::string &key, const int hardcoded_weight = 0 ) {
509  const auto iter = mapgens_.find( key );
510  if( iter == mapgens_.end() ) {
511  return false;
512  }
513  return iter->second.generate( dat, hardcoded_weight );
514  }
515 
516  mapgen_parameters get_map_special_params( const std::string &key ) const {
517  const auto iter = mapgens_.find( key );
518  if( iter == mapgens_.end() ) {
519  return mapgen_parameters();
520  }
521  return iter->second.get_mapgen_params( mapgen_parameter_scope::overmap_special,
522  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(cata-translate-string-literal)
523  string_format( "map special %s", key ) );
524  }
525 };
526 
527 static mapgen_factory oter_mapgen;

530 std::map<update_mapgen_id, update_mapgen> update_mapgens;
531 static std::unordered_map<std::string, tripoint_abs_ms> queued_points;

533 template<>
534 bool string_id<nested_mapgen>::is_valid() const
535 {
536  return str() == "null" || nested_mapgens.find( *this ) != nested_mapgens.end();
537 }
538 
539 template<>
540 const nested_mapgen &string_id<nested_mapgen>::obj() const
541 {
542  auto it = nested_mapgens.find( *this );
543  if( it == nested_mapgens.end() ) {
544  debugmsg( "Using invalid nested_mapgen_id %s", str() );
545  static const nested_mapgen null_mapgen;
546  return null_mapgen;
547  }
548  return it->second;
549 }

551 template<>

553 {

555 }

557 template<>
558 const update_mapgen &string_id<update_mapgen>::obj() const
559 {
560  auto it = update_mapgens.find( *this );
561  if( it == update_mapgens.end() ) {
562  debugmsg( "Using invalid nested_mapgen_id %s", str() );
563  static const update_mapgen null_mapgen;
564  return null_mapgen;
565  }
566  return it->second;
567 }

569 /*
570  * setup mapgen_basic_container::weights_ which mapgen uses to diceroll. Also setup mapgen_function_json
571  */
572 void calculate_mapgen_weights() // TODO: rename as it runs jsonfunction setup too
573 {
574  oter_mapgen.setup();
575  // Not really calculate weights, but let's keep it here for now
576  for( auto &pr : nested_mapgens ) {
577  for( const weighted_object<int, std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function_json_nested>> &ptr :
578  pr.second.funcs() ) {
579  ptr.obj->setup();
580  inp_mngr.pump_events();
581  }
582  }
583  for( auto &pr : update_mapgens ) {
584  for( const auto &ptr : pr.second.funcs() ) {
585  ptr->setup();
586  inp_mngr.pump_events();
587  }
588  }
589  // Having set up all the mapgens we can now perform a second
590  // pass of finalizing their parameters
591  oter_mapgen.finalize_parameters();
592  for( auto &pr : nested_mapgens ) {
593  for( const weighted_object<int, std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function_json_nested>> &ptr :
594  pr.second.funcs() ) {
595  ptr.obj->finalize_parameters();
596  inp_mngr.pump_events();
597  }
598  }
599  for( auto &pr : update_mapgens ) {
600  for( const auto &ptr : pr.second.funcs() ) {
601  ptr->finalize_parameters();
602  inp_mngr.pump_events();
603  }
604  }
605 }
606 
607 void check_mapgen_definitions()
608 {
609  oter_mapgen.check_consistency();
610  for( const auto &oter_definition : nested_mapgens ) {
611  for( const auto &mapgen_function_ptr : oter_definition.second.funcs() ) {
612  mapgen_function_ptr.obj->check();
613  }
614  }
615  for( const auto &oter_definition : update_mapgens ) {
616  for( const auto &mapgen_function_ptr : oter_definition.second.funcs() ) {
617  mapgen_function_ptr->check();
618  }
619  }
620 }

626 /**
627  * Tiny little namespace to hold error messages
628  */
629 namespace mapgen_defer
630 {
631 static std::string member;
632 static std::string message;
633 static bool defer;
634 static JsonObject jsi;
635 } // namespace mapgen_defer

637 static void set_mapgen_defer( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string &member,
638  const std::string &message )
639 {
640  mapgen_defer::defer = true;
641  mapgen_defer::jsi = jsi;
642  mapgen_defer::member = member;
643  mapgen_defer::message = message;

645 
646 /*
647  * load a single mapgen json structure; this can be inside an overmap_terrain, or on it's own.
648  */
649 std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function>
650 load_mapgen_function( const JsonObject &jio, const std::string &id_base, const point &offset,
651  const point &total )
652 {
653  dbl_or_var weight = get_dbl_or_var( jio, "weight", false, 1000 );
654 
655  if( jio.get_bool( "disabled", false ) ) {
656  jio.allow_omitted_members();
657  return nullptr; // nothing
658  }
659  const std::string mgtype = jio.get_string( "method" );
660  if( mgtype == "builtin" ) {
661  if( const building_gen_pointer ptr = get_mapgen_cfunction( jio.get_string( "name" ) ) ) {
662  return std::make_shared<mapgen_function_builtin>( ptr, std::move( weight ) );
663  } else {
664  jio.throw_error_at( "name", "function does not exist" );
665  }
666  } else if( mgtype == "json" ) {
667  if( !jio.has_object( "object" ) ) {
668  jio.throw_error( R"(mapgen with method "json" must define key "object")" );
669  }
670  JsonObject jo = jio.get_object( "object" );
671  jo.allow_omitted_members();
672  return std::make_shared<mapgen_function_json>(
673  jo, std::move( weight ), "mapgen " + id_base, offset, total );
674  } else {
675  jio.throw_error_at( "method", R"(invalid value: must be "builtin" or "json")" );
676  }
677 }
678 
679 void load_and_add_mapgen_function( const JsonObject &jio, const std::string &id_base,
680  const point &offset, const point &total )
681 {
682  std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function> f = load_mapgen_function( jio, id_base, offset, total );
683  if( f ) {
684  oter_mapgen.add( id_base, f );
685  }
686 }
687 
688 static void load_nested_mapgen( const JsonObject &jio, const nested_mapgen_id &id_base )
689 {
690  const std::string mgtype = jio.get_string( "method" );
691  if( mgtype == "json" ) {
692  if( jio.has_object( "object" ) ) {
693  int weight = jio.get_int( "weight", 1000 );
694  JsonObject jo = jio.get_object( "object" );
695  jo.allow_omitted_members();
696  nested_mapgens[id_base].add(
697  std::make_shared<mapgen_function_json_nested>(
698  jo, "nested mapgen " + id_base.str() ),
699  weight );
700  } else {
701  debugmsg( "Nested mapgen: Invalid mapgen function (missing \"object\" object)", id_base.c_str() );
702  }
703  } else {
704  debugmsg( "Nested mapgen: type for id %s was %s, but nested mapgen only supports \"json\"",
705  id_base.c_str(), mgtype.c_str() );
706  }
707 }
708 
709 static void load_update_mapgen( const JsonObject &jio, const update_mapgen_id &id_base )
710 {
711  const std::string mgtype = jio.get_string( "method" );
712  if( mgtype == "json" ) {
713  if( jio.has_object( "object" ) ) {
714  JsonObject jo = jio.get_object( "object" );
715  jo.allow_omitted_members();
716  update_mapgens[id_base].add(
717  std::make_unique<update_mapgen_function_json>(
718  jo, "update mapgen " + id_base.str() ) );
719  } else {
720  debugmsg( "Update mapgen: Invalid mapgen function (missing \"object\" object)",
721  id_base.c_str() );
722  }
723  } else {
724  debugmsg( "Update mapgen: type for id %s was %s, but update mapgen only supports \"json\"",
725  id_base.c_str(), mgtype.c_str() );
726  }
727 }
728 
729 /*
730  * feed bits `o json from standalone file to load_mapgen_function. (standalone json "type": "mapgen")
731  */
732 void load_mapgen( const JsonObject &jo )
733 {
734  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(cata-use-named-point-constants)
735  static constexpr point point_one( 1, 1 );
736 
737  if( jo.has_array( "om_terrain" ) ) {
738  JsonArray ja = jo.get_array( "om_terrain" );
739  if( ja.test_array() ) {
740  point offset;
741  point total( ja.get_array( 0 ).size(), ja.size() );
742  for( JsonArray row_items : ja ) {
743  for( const std::string mapgenid : row_items ) {
744  load_and_add_mapgen_function( jo, mapgenid, offset, total );
745  offset.x++;
746  }
747  offset.y++;
748  offset.x = 0;
749  }
750  } else {
751  std::vector<std::string> mapgenid_list;
752  for( const std::string line : ja ) {
753  mapgenid_list.push_back( line );
754  }
755  if( !mapgenid_list.empty() ) {
756  const std::string mapgenid = mapgenid_list[0];
757  const auto mgfunc = load_mapgen_function( jo, mapgenid, point_zero, point_one );
758  if( mgfunc ) {
759  for( auto &i : mapgenid_list ) {
760  oter_mapgen.add( i, mgfunc );
761  }
762  }
763  }
764  }
765  } else if( jo.has_string( "om_terrain" ) ) {
766  load_and_add_mapgen_function( jo, jo.get_string( "om_terrain" ), point_zero, point_one );
767  } else if( jo.has_string( "nested_mapgen_id" ) ) {
768  load_nested_mapgen( jo, nested_mapgen_id( jo.get_string( "nested_mapgen_id" ) ) );
769  } else if( jo.has_string( "update_mapgen_id" ) ) {
770  load_update_mapgen( jo, update_mapgen_id( jo.get_string( "update_mapgen_id" ) ) );
771  } else {
772  debugmsg( "mapgen entry requires \"om_terrain\" or \"nested_mapgen_id\"(string, array of strings, or array of array of strings)\n%s\n",
773  jo.str() );
774  }
775 }
776 
777 void reset_mapgens()
778 {
779  oter_mapgen.reset();
780  nested_mapgens.clear();
781  update_mapgens.clear();
782 }

784 /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
785 ///// 2 - right after init() finishes parsing all game json and terrain info/etc is set..
786 ///// ...parse more json! (mapgen_function_json)
787 
788 size_t mapgen_function_json_base::calc_index( const point &p ) const
789 {
790  if( p.x >= mapgensize.x ) {
791  debugmsg( "invalid value %zu for x in calc_index", p.x );
792  }
793  if( p.y >= mapgensize.y ) {
794  debugmsg( "invalid value %zu for y in calc_index", p.y );
795  }
796  return p.y * mapgensize.y + p.x;
797 }
798 
799 static bool common_check_bounds( const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
800  const point &mapgensize, const JsonObject &jso )
801 {
802  half_open_rectangle<point> bounds( point_zero, mapgensize );
803  if( !bounds.contains( point( x.val, y.val ) ) ) {
804  return false;
805  }
806 
807  if( x.valmax < x.val ) {
808  jso.throw_error( "x maximum is less than x minimum" );
809  }
810 
811  if( y.valmax < y.val ) {
812  jso.throw_error( "y maximum is less than y minimum" );
813  }
814 
815  if( z.valmax != z.val ) {
816  jso.throw_error( "z maximum has to be identical to z minimum" );
817  }
818 
819  if( x.valmax > mapgensize.x - 1 ) {
820  jso.throw_error_at( "x", "coordinate range cannot cross grid boundaries" );
821  }
822 
823  if( y.valmax > mapgensize.y - 1 ) {
824  jso.throw_error_at( "y", "coordinate range cannot cross grid boundaries" );
825  }
826 
827  return true;
828 }
829 
830 void mapgen_function_json_base::merge_non_nest_parameters_into(
831  mapgen_parameters &params, const std::string &outer_context ) const
832 {
833  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(cata-translate-string-literal)
834  const std::string context = string_format( "%s within %s", context_, outer_context );
835  params.check_and_merge( parameters, context, mapgen_parameter_scope::nest );
836 }
837 
838 bool mapgen_function_json_base::check_inbounds( const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y,
839  const jmapgen_int &z,
840  const JsonObject &jso ) const
841 {
842  return common_check_bounds( x, y, z, mapgensize, jso );
843 }

882 jmapgen_int::jmapgen_int( point p ) : val( p.x ), valmax( p.y )
883 {
884  cata_assert( p.x <= std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max() );
885  cata_assert( p.y <= std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max() );
886 }
887 
888 jmapgen_int::jmapgen_int( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string_view tag )
889 {
890  if( jo.has_array( tag ) ) {
891  JsonArray sparray = jo.get_array( tag );
892  if( sparray.empty() || sparray.size() > 2 ) {
893  jo.throw_error_at( tag, "invalid data: must be an array of 1 or 2 values" );
894  }
895  int tmpval = sparray.get_int( 0 );
896  if( tmpval >= std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max() ) {
897  jo.throw_error_at( tag, string_format( "Value %d too large", tmpval ) );
898  }
899  val = tmpval;
900  if( sparray.size() == 2 ) {
901  int tmpvalmax = sparray.get_int( 1 );
902  if( tmpvalmax >= std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max() ) {
903  jo.throw_error_at( tag, string_format( "Value %d too large", tmpvalmax ) );
904  }
905  valmax = tmpvalmax;
906  } else {
907  valmax = val;
908  }
909  } else {
910  val = valmax = jo.get_int( tag );
911  }
912 }
913 
914 jmapgen_int::jmapgen_int( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string_view tag, const int &def_val,
915  const int &def_valmax )
916  : val( def_val )
917  , valmax( def_valmax )
918 {
919  if( jo.has_array( tag ) ) {
920  JsonArray sparray = jo.get_array( tag );
921  if( sparray.size() > 2 ) {
922  jo.throw_error_at( tag, "invalid data: must be an array of 1 or 2 values" );
923  }
924  if( !sparray.empty() ) {
925  int tmpval = sparray.get_int( 0 );
926  if( tmpval >= std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max() ) {
927  jo.throw_error_at( tag, string_format( "Value %d too large", tmpval ) );
928  }
929  val = tmpval;
930  }
931  if( sparray.size() >= 2 ) {
932  int tmpvalmax = sparray.get_int( 1 );
933  if( tmpvalmax >= std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max() ) {
934  jo.throw_error_at( tag, string_format( "Value %d too large", tmpvalmax ) );
935  }
936  valmax = tmpvalmax;
937  }
938  } else if( jo.has_member( tag ) ) {
939  int tmpval = jo.get_int( tag );
940  if( tmpval >= std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max() ) {
941  jo.throw_error_at( tag, string_format( "Value %d too large", tmpval ) );
942  }
943  val = valmax = tmpval;
944  }
945 }
946 
947 int jmapgen_int::get() const
948 {
949  return val == valmax ? val : rng( val, valmax );
950 }
951 
952 /*
953  * Turn json gobbldigook into machine friendly gobbldigook, for applying
954  * basic map 'set' functions, optionally based on one_in(chance) or repeat value
955  */
956 void mapgen_function_json_base::setup_setmap( const JsonArray &parray )
957 {
958  std::string tmpval;
959  std::map<std::string, jmapgen_setmap_op> setmap_opmap;
960  setmap_opmap[ "terrain" ] = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TER;
961  setmap_opmap[ "furniture" ] = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_FURN;
962  setmap_opmap[ "trap" ] = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TRAP;
963  setmap_opmap[ "trap_remove" ] = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TRAP_REMOVE;
964  setmap_opmap[ "creature_remove" ] = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_CREATURE_REMOVE;
965  setmap_opmap[ "item_remove" ] = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_ITEM_REMOVE;
966  setmap_opmap[ "field_remove" ] = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_FIELD_REMOVE;
967  setmap_opmap[ "radiation" ] = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_RADIATION;
968  setmap_opmap[ "bash" ] = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_BASH;
969  setmap_opmap[ "variable" ] = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_VARIABLE;
970  std::map<std::string, jmapgen_setmap_op>::iterator sm_it;
971  jmapgen_setmap_op tmpop;
972  int setmap_optype = 0;
973 
974  for( const JsonObject pjo : parray ) {
975  if( pjo.read( "point", tmpval ) ) {
976  setmap_optype = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_OPTYPE_POINT;
977  } else if( pjo.read( "set", tmpval ) ) {
978  setmap_optype = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_OPTYPE_POINT;
979  debugmsg( "Warning, set: [ { \"set\": } is deprecated, use set: [ { \"point\": " );
980  } else if( pjo.read( "line", tmpval ) ) {
981  setmap_optype = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_OPTYPE_LINE;
982  } else if( pjo.read( "square", tmpval ) ) {
983  setmap_optype = JMAPGEN_SETMAP_OPTYPE_SQUARE;
984  } else {
985  pjo.throw_error( R"(invalid data: must contain "point", "set", "line" or "square" member)" );
986  }
987 
988  sm_it = setmap_opmap.find( tmpval );
989  if( sm_it == setmap_opmap.end() ) {
990  pjo.throw_error( string_format( "invalid subfunction %s", tmpval.c_str() ) );
991  }
992 
993  tmpop = sm_it->second;
994  jmapgen_int tmp_x2( 0, 0 );
995  jmapgen_int tmp_y2( 0, 0 );
996  jmapgen_int tmp_i( 0, 0 );
997  std::string string_val;
998  int tmp_chance = 1;
999  int tmp_rotation = 0;
1000  int tmp_fuel = -1;
1001  int tmp_status = -1;
1002 
1003  const jmapgen_int tmp_x( pjo, "x" );
1004  const jmapgen_int tmp_y( pjo, "y" );
1005  const jmapgen_int tmp_z( pjo, "z", 0, 0 );
1006  if( !check_inbounds( tmp_x, tmp_y, tmp_z, pjo ) ) {
1007  pjo.allow_omitted_members();
1008  continue;
1009  }
1010  if( setmap_optype != JMAPGEN_SETMAP_OPTYPE_POINT ) {
1011  tmp_x2 = jmapgen_int( pjo, "x2" );
1012  tmp_y2 = jmapgen_int( pjo, "y2" );
1013  if( !check_inbounds( tmp_x2, tmp_y2, tmp_z, pjo ) ) {
1014  pjo.allow_omitted_members();
1015  continue;
1016  }
1017  }
1018  if( tmpop == JMAPGEN_SETMAP_RADIATION ) {
1019  tmp_i = jmapgen_int( pjo, "amount" );
1020  } else if( tmpop == JMAPGEN_SETMAP_BASH || tmpop == JMAPGEN_SETMAP_ITEM_REMOVE ||
1021  tmpop == JMAPGEN_SETMAP_FIELD_REMOVE || tmpop == JMAPGEN_SETMAP_CREATURE_REMOVE ) {
1022  //suppress warning
1023  } else if( tmpop == JMAPGEN_SETMAP_VARIABLE ) {
1024  string_val = pjo.get_string( "id" );
1025  } else {
1026  std::string tmpid = pjo.get_string( "id" );
1027  switch( tmpop ) {
1028  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TER: {
1029  const ter_str_id tid( tmpid );
1030 
1031  if( !tid.is_valid() ) {
1032  set_mapgen_defer( pjo, "id", "no such terrain" );
1033  return;
1034  }
1035  tmp_i.val = tid.id().to_i();
1036  }
1037  break;
1038  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_FURN: {
1039  const furn_str_id fid( tmpid );
1040 
1041  if( !fid.is_valid() ) {
1042  set_mapgen_defer( pjo, "id", "no such furniture" );
1043  return;
1044  }
1045  tmp_i.val = fid.id().to_i();
1046  }
1047  break;
1048  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TRAP_REMOVE:
1049  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TRAP: {
1050  const trap_str_id sid( tmpid );
1051  if( !sid.is_valid() ) {
1052  set_mapgen_defer( pjo, "id", "no such trap" );
1053  return;
1054  }
1055  tmp_i.val = sid.id().to_i();
1056  }
1057  break;
1058 
1059  default:
1060  //Suppress warnings
1061  break;
1062  }
1063  // TODO: ... support for random furniture? or not.
1064  tmp_i.valmax = tmp_i.val;
1065  }
1066  // TODO: sanity check?
1067  const jmapgen_int tmp_repeat = jmapgen_int( pjo, "repeat", 1, 1 );
1068  pjo.read( "chance", tmp_chance );
1069  pjo.read( "rotation", tmp_rotation );
1070  pjo.read( "fuel", tmp_fuel );
1071  pjo.read( "status", tmp_status );
1072  jmapgen_setmap tmp( tmp_x, tmp_y, tmp_z, tmp_x2, tmp_y2,
1073  static_cast<jmapgen_setmap_op>( tmpop + setmap_optype ), tmp_i,
1074  tmp_chance, tmp_repeat, tmp_rotation, tmp_fuel, tmp_status, string_val );
1075 
1076  setmap_points.push_back( tmp );
1077  tmpval.clear();
1078  }
1079 
1080 }
1081 
1082 void mapgen_function_json_base::finalize_parameters_common()
1083 {
1084  objects.merge_parameters_into( parameters, context_ );
1085 }

1091 }

1200 // Mapgen often uses various id values. Usually these are specified verbatim
1201 // as strings, but they can also be parameterized. This class encapsulates
1202 // such a value. It records how the value was specified so that it can be
1203 // calculated later based on the parameters chosen for a particular instance of
1204 // the mapgen.
1205 template<typename Id>
1206 class mapgen_value
1207 {
1208  public:
1209  using StringId = to_string_id_t<Id>;
1210  struct void_;
1211  using Id_unless_string =
1212  std::conditional_t<std::is_same_v<Id, std::string>, void_, Id>;
1213 
1214  struct value_source {
1215  virtual ~value_source() = default;
1216  virtual Id get( const mapgendata & ) const = 0;
1217  virtual void check( const std::string &/*oter_name*/, const mapgen_parameters &
1218  ) const {};
1219  virtual void check_consistent_with(
1220  const value_source &, const std::string &context ) const = 0;
1221  virtual std::vector<StringId> all_possible_results(
1222  const mapgen_parameters & ) const = 0;
1223  virtual const std::string *get_name_if_parameter() const {
1224  return nullptr;
1225  }
1226  };
1227 
1228  struct null_source : value_source {
1229  Id get( const mapgendata & ) const override {
1230  return make_null_helper<Id> {}();
1231  }
1232 
1233  void check_consistent_with(
1234  const value_source &o, const std::string &context ) const override {
1235  if( const null_source *other = dynamic_cast<const null_source *>( &o ) ) {
1236  // OK
1237  } else {
1238  debugmsg( "inconsistent default types for %s", context );
1239  }
1240  }
1241 
1242  std::vector<StringId> all_possible_results( const mapgen_parameters & ) const override {
1243  return { make_null_helper<StringId>{}() };
1244  }
1245  };
1246 
1247  struct id_source : value_source {
1248  Id id;
1249 
1250  explicit id_source( const std::string &s ) :
1251  id( s ) {
1252  }
1253 
1254  explicit id_source( const Id_unless_string &s ) :
1255  id( s ) {
1256  }
1257 
1258  Id get( const mapgendata & ) const override {
1259  return id;
1260  }
1261 
1262  void check( const std::string &context, const mapgen_parameters & ) const override {
1263  if( !is_valid_helper( id ) ) {
1264  debugmsg( "mapgen '%s' uses invalid entry '%s'",
1265  context, cata_variant( id ).get_string() );
1266  }
1267  }
1268 
1269  void check_consistent_with(
1270  const value_source &o, const std::string &context ) const override {
1271  if( const id_source *other = dynamic_cast<const id_source *>( &o ) ) {
1272  if( id != other->id ) {
1273  debugmsg( "inconsistent default values for %s (%s vs %s)",
1274  context, cata_variant( id ).get_string(),
1275  cata_variant( other->id ).get_string() );
1276  }
1277  } else {
1278  debugmsg( "inconsistent default types for %s", context );
1279  }
1280  }
1281 
1282  std::vector<StringId> all_possible_results( const mapgen_parameters & ) const override {
1283  return { to_string_id_helper( id ) };
1284  }
1285  };
1286 
1287  struct param_source : value_source {
1288  std::string param_name;
1289  std::optional<StringId> fallback;
1290 
1291  explicit param_source( const JsonObject &jo )
1292  : param_name( jo.get_string( "param" ) ) {
1293  jo.read( "fallback", fallback, false );
1294  }
1295 
1296  Id get( const mapgendata &dat ) const override {
1297  if( fallback ) {
1298  return Id( dat.get_arg_or<StringId>( param_name, *fallback ) );
1299  } else {
1300  return Id( dat.get_arg<StringId>( param_name ) );
1301  }
1302  }
1303 
1304  void check( const std::string &context, const mapgen_parameters &parameters
1305  ) const override {
1306  auto param_it = parameters.map.find( param_name );
1307  if( param_it == parameters.map.end() ) {
1308  debugmsg( "mapgen '%s' uses undefined parameter '%s'", context, param_name );
1309  } else {
1310  const mapgen_parameter &param = param_it->second;
1311  constexpr cata_variant_type req_type = cata_variant_type_for<StringId>();
1312  cata_variant_type param_type = param.type();
1313  if( param_type != req_type && req_type != cata_variant_type::string ) {
1314  debugmsg( "mapgen '%s' uses parameter '%s' of type '%s' in a context "
1315  "expecting type '%s'", context, param_name,
1316  io::enum_to_string( param_type ),
1317  io::enum_to_string( req_type ) );
1318  }
1319  if( param.scope() == mapgen_parameter_scope::overmap_special && !fallback ) {
1320  debugmsg( "mapgen '%s' uses parameter '%s' of map_special scope without a "
1321  "fallback. Such parameters must provide a fallback to allow "
1322  "for changes to overmap_special definitions", context,
1323  param_name );
1324  }
1325  }
1326  }
1327 
1328  void check_consistent_with(
1329  const value_source &o, const std::string &context ) const override {
1330  if( const param_source *other = dynamic_cast<const param_source *>( &o ) ) {
1331  if( param_name != other->param_name ) {
1332  debugmsg( "inconsistent default values for %s (%s vs %s)",
1333  context, param_name, other->param_name );
1334  }
1335  } else {
1336  debugmsg( "inconsistent default types for %s", context );
1337  }
1338  }
1339 
1340  std::vector<StringId> all_possible_results(
1341  const mapgen_parameters &params ) const override {
1342  auto param_it = params.map.find( param_name );
1343  if( param_it == params.map.end() ) {
1344  return {};
1345  } else {
1346  const mapgen_parameter &param = param_it->second;
1347  std::vector<StringId> result;
1348  for( const std::string &s : param.all_possible_values( params ) ) {
1349  result.emplace_back( s );
1350  }
1351  return result;
1352  }
1353  }
1354 
1355  const std::string *get_name_if_parameter() const override {
1356  return &param_name;
1357  }
1358  };
1359 
1360  struct distribution_source : value_source {
1361  weighted_int_list<StringId> list;
1362 
1363  explicit distribution_source( const JsonObject &jo ) {
1364  load_weighted_list( jo.get_member( "distribution" ), list, 1 );
1365  }
1366 
1367  Id get( const mapgendata & ) const override {
1368  return *list.pick();
1369  }
1370 
1371  void check( const std::string &context, const mapgen_parameters & ) const override {
1372  for( const weighted_object<int, StringId> &wo : list ) {
1373  if( !is_valid_helper( wo.obj ) ) {
1374  debugmsg( "mapgen '%s' uses invalid entry '%s' in weighted list",
1375  context, cata_variant( wo.obj ).get_string() );
1376  }
1377  }
1378  }
1379 
1380  void check_consistent_with(
1381  const value_source &o, const std::string &context ) const override {
1382  if( const distribution_source *other =
1383  dynamic_cast<const distribution_source *>( &o ) ) {
1384  if( list != other->list ) {
1385  const std::string my_list = list.to_debug_string();
1386  const std::string other_list = other->list.to_debug_string();
1387  debugmsg( "inconsistent default value distributions for %s (%s vs %s)",
1388  context, my_list, other_list );
1389  }
1390  } else {
1391  debugmsg( "inconsistent default types for %s", context );
1392  }
1393  }
1394 
1395  std::vector<StringId> all_possible_results( const mapgen_parameters & ) const override {
1396  std::vector<StringId> result;
1397  for( const weighted_object<int, StringId> &wo : list ) {
1398  result.push_back( wo.obj );
1399  }
1400  return result;
1401  }
1402  };
1403 
1404  struct switch_source : value_source {
1405  // This has to be a pointer because mapgen_value is an incomplete
1406  // type. We could resolve this by pulling out all these
1407  // value_source classes and defining them at namespace scope after
1408  // mapgen_value, but that would make the code much more verbose.
1409  std::unique_ptr<mapgen_value<std::string>> on;
1410  std::unordered_map<std::string, StringId> cases;
1411 
1412  explicit switch_source( const JsonObject &jo )
1413  : on( std::make_unique<mapgen_value<std::string>>( jo.get_object( "switch" ) ) ) {
1414  jo.read( "cases", cases, true );
1415  }
1416 
1417  Id get( const mapgendata &dat ) const override {
1418  std::string based_on = on->get( dat );
1419  auto it = cases.find( based_on );
1420  if( it == cases.end() ) {
1421  debugmsg( "switch does not handle case %s", based_on );
1422  return make_null_helper<Id> {}();
1423  }
1424  return Id( it->second );
1425  }
1426 
1427  void check( const std::string &context, const mapgen_parameters &params
1428  ) const override {
1429  on->check( context, params );
1430  for( const std::pair<const std::string, StringId> &p : cases ) {
1431  if( !is_valid_helper( p.second ) ) {
1432  debugmsg( "mapgen '%s' uses invalid entry '%s' in switch",
1433  context, cata_variant( p.second ).get_string() );
1434  }
1435  }
1436  std::vector<std::string> possible_values = on->all_possible_results( params );
1437  for( const std::string &value : possible_values ) {
1438  if( !cases.count( value ) ) {
1439  debugmsg( "mapgen '%s' has switch which does not account for potential "
1440  "case '%s' of the switched-on value", context, value );
1441  }
1442  }
1443  }
1444 
1445  void check_consistent_with(
1446  const value_source &o, const std::string &context ) const override {
1447  if( const switch_source *other = dynamic_cast<const switch_source *>( &o ) ) {
1448  on->check_consistent_with( *other->on, context );
1449  if( cases != other->cases ) {
1450  auto dump_set = []( const std::unordered_map<std::string, StringId> &s ) {
1451  bool first = true;
1452  std::string result = "{ ";
1453  for( const std::pair<const std::string, StringId> &p : s ) {
1454  if( first ) {
1455  first = false;
1456  } else {
1457  result += ", ";
1458  }
1459  result += p.first;
1460  result += ": ";
1461  result += cata_variant( p.second ).get_string();
1462  }
1463  return result;
1464  };
1465 
1466  const std::string my_list = dump_set( cases );
1467  const std::string other_list = dump_set( other->cases );
1468  debugmsg( "inconsistent switch cases for %s (%s vs %s)",
1469  context, my_list, other_list );
1470  }
1471  } else {
1472  debugmsg( "inconsistent default types for %s", context );
1473  }
1474  }
1475 
1476  std::vector<StringId> all_possible_results( const mapgen_parameters & ) const override {
1477  std::vector<StringId> result;
1478  result.reserve( cases.size() );
1479  for( const std::pair<const std::string, StringId> &p : cases ) {
1480  result.push_back( p.second );
1481  }
1482  return result;
1483  }
1484  };
1485 
1486  mapgen_value()
1487  : is_null_( true )
1488  , source_( make_shared_fast<null_source>() )
1489  {}
1490 
1491  explicit mapgen_value( const std::string &s ) {
1492  init_string( s );
1493  }
1494 
1495  explicit mapgen_value( const Id_unless_string &id ) {
1496  init_string( id );
1497  }
1498 
1499  explicit mapgen_value( const JsonValue &jv ) {
1500  if( jv.test_string() ) {
1501  init_string( jv.get_string() );
1502  } else {
1503  init_object( jv.get_object() );
1504  }
1505  }
1506 
1507  explicit mapgen_value( const JsonObject &jo ) {
1508  init_object( jo );
1509  }
1510 
1511  template<typename S>
1512  void init_string( const S &s ) {
1513  source_ = make_shared_fast<id_source>( s );
1514  is_null_ = is_null_helper( s );
1515  }
1516 
1517  void init_object( const JsonObject &jo ) {
1518  if( jo.has_member( "param" ) ) {
1519  source_ = make_shared_fast<param_source>( jo );
1520  } else if( jo.has_member( "distribution" ) ) {
1521  source_ = make_shared_fast<distribution_source>( jo );
1522  } else if( jo.has_member( "switch" ) ) {
1523  source_ = make_shared_fast<switch_source>( jo );
1524  } else {
1525  jo.throw_error(
1526  R"(Expected member "param", "distribution", or "switch" in mapgen object)" );
1527  }
1528  }
1529 
1530  bool is_null() const {
1531  return is_null_;
1532  }
1533 
1534  void check( const std::string &context, const mapgen_parameters &params ) const {
1535  source_->check( context, params );
1536  }
1537  void check_consistent_with( const mapgen_value &other, const std::string &context ) const {
1538  source_->check_consistent_with( *other.source_, context );
1539  }
1540 
1541  Id get( const mapgendata &dat ) const {
1542  return source_->get( dat );
1543  }
1544  std::vector<StringId> all_possible_results( const mapgen_parameters &params ) const {
1545  return source_->all_possible_results( params );
1546  }
1547 
1548  const std::string *get_name_if_parameter() const {
1549  return source_->get_name_if_parameter();
1550  }
1551 
1552  void deserialize( const JsonValue &jsin ) {
1553  if( jsin.test_object() ) {
1554  *this = mapgen_value( jsin.get_object() );
1555  } else {
1556  *this = mapgen_value( jsin.get_string() );
1557  }
1558  }
1559  private:
1560  bool is_null_ = false;
1561  shared_ptr_fast<const value_source> source_;
1562 };

1567 template<>
1568 std::string enum_to_string<jmapgen_flags>( jmapgen_flags v )
1569 {
1570  switch( v ) {
1571  // *INDENT-OFF*
1572  case jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_other_data: return "ALLOW_TERRAIN_UNDER_OTHER_DATA";
1573  case jmapgen_flags::dismantle_all_before_placing_terrain:
1574  return "DISMANTLE_ALL_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN";
1575  case jmapgen_flags::erase_all_before_placing_terrain:
1576  return "ERASE_ALL_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN";
1577  case jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_furniture: return "ALLOW_TERRAIN_UNDER_FURNITURE";
1578  case jmapgen_flags::dismantle_furniture_before_placing_terrain:
1579  return "DISMANTLE_FURNITURE_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN";
1580  case jmapgen_flags::erase_furniture_before_placing_terrain:
1581  return "ERASE_FURNITURE_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN";
1582  case jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_trap: return "ALLOW_TERRAIN_UNDER_TRAP";
1583  case jmapgen_flags::dismantle_trap_before_placing_terrain:
1584  return "DISMANTLE_TRAP_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN";
1585  case jmapgen_flags::erase_trap_before_placing_terrain:
1586  return "ERASE_TRAP_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN";
1587  case jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_items: return "ALLOW_TERRAIN_UNDER_ITEMS";
1588  case jmapgen_flags::erase_items_before_placing_terrain:
1589  return "ERASE_ITEMS_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN";
1590  case jmapgen_flags::no_underlying_rotate: return "NO_UNDERLYING_ROTATE";
1591  case jmapgen_flags::avoid_creatures: return "AVOID_CREATURES";
1592  // *INDENT-ON*
1593  case jmapgen_flags::last:
1594  break;
1595  }
1596  debugmsg( "unknown jmapgen_flags %d", static_cast<int>( v ) );
1597  return "";
1598 }
1599 
1600 template<>
1601 std::string enum_to_string<mapgen_parameter_scope>( mapgen_parameter_scope v )
1602 {
1603  switch( v ) {
1604  // *INDENT-OFF*
1605  case mapgen_parameter_scope::overmap_special: return "overmap_special";
1606  case mapgen_parameter_scope::omt: return "omt";
1607  case mapgen_parameter_scope::nest: return "nest";
1608  // *INDENT-ON*
1609  case mapgen_parameter_scope::last:
1610  break;
1611  }
1612  debugmsg( "unknown mapgen_parameter_scope %d", static_cast<int>( v ) );
1613  return "";
1614 }

1618 mapgen_parameter::mapgen_parameter() = default;
1619 
1620 mapgen_parameter::mapgen_parameter( const mapgen_value<std::string> &def, cata_variant_type type,
1621  mapgen_parameter_scope scope )
1622  : scope_( scope )
1623  , type_( type )
1624  , default_( make_shared_fast<mapgen_value<std::string>>( def ) )
1625 {}
1626 
1627 void mapgen_parameter::deserialize( const JsonObject &jo )
1628 {
1629  optional( jo, false, "scope", scope_, mapgen_parameter_scope::overmap_special );
1630  jo.read( "type", type_, true );
1631  default_ = make_shared_fast<mapgen_value<std::string>>( jo.get_member( "default" ) );
1632 }
1633 
1634 cata_variant_type mapgen_parameter::type() const
1635 {
1636  return type_;
1637 }
1638 
1639 cata_variant mapgen_parameter::get( const mapgendata &md ) const
1640 {
1641  return cata_variant::from_string( type_, default_->get( md ) );
1642 }
1643 
1644 std::vector<std::string> mapgen_parameter::all_possible_values(
1645  const mapgen_parameters &params ) const
1646 {
1647  return default_->all_possible_results( params );
1648 }
1649 
1650 void mapgen_parameter::check( const mapgen_parameters &params, const std::string &context ) const
1651 {
1652  default_->check( context, params );
1653  for( const std::string &value : all_possible_values( params ) ) {
1654  if( !cata_variant::from_string( type_, std::string( value ) ).is_valid() ) {
1655  debugmsg( "%s can take value %s which is not a valid value of type %s",
1656  context, value, io::enum_to_string( type_ ) );
1657  }
1658  }
1659 }
1660 
1661 void mapgen_parameter::check_consistent_with(
1662  const mapgen_parameter &other, const std::string &context ) const
1663 {
1664  if( scope_ != other.scope_ ) {
1665  debugmsg( "mismatched scope for mapgen parameters %s (%s vs %s)",
1666  context, io::enum_to_string( scope_ ), io::enum_to_string( other.scope_ ) );
1667  }
1668  if( type_ != other.type_ ) {
1669  debugmsg( "mismatched type for mapgen parameters %s (%s vs %s)",
1670  context, io::enum_to_string( type_ ), io::enum_to_string( other.type_ ) );
1671  }
1672  default_->check_consistent_with( *other.default_, context );
1673 }
1674 
1675 auto mapgen_parameters::add_unique_parameter(
1676  const std::string &prefix, const mapgen_value<std::string> &def, cata_variant_type type,
1677  mapgen_parameter_scope scope ) -> iterator
1678 {
1679  uint64_t i = 0;
1680  std::string candidate_name;
1681  while( true ) {
1682  candidate_name = string_format( "%s%d", prefix, i );
1683  if( map.find( candidate_name ) == map.end() ) {
1684  break;
1685  }
1686  ++i;
1687  }
1688 
1689  return map.emplace( candidate_name, mapgen_parameter( def, type, scope ) ).first;
1690 }
1691 
1692 mapgen_parameters mapgen_parameters::params_for_scope( mapgen_parameter_scope scope ) const
1693 {
1694  mapgen_parameters result;
1695  for( const std::pair<const std::string, mapgen_parameter> &p : map ) {
1696  const mapgen_parameter &param = p.second;
1697  if( param.scope() == scope ) {
1698  result.map.insert( p );
1699  }
1700  }
1701  return result;
1702 }
1703 
1704 mapgen_arguments mapgen_parameters::get_args(
1705  const mapgendata &md, mapgen_parameter_scope scope ) const
1706 {
1707  std::unordered_map<std::string, cata_variant> result;
1708  for( const std::pair<const std::string, mapgen_parameter> &p : map ) {
1709  const std::string &param_name = p.first;
1710  const mapgen_parameter &param = p.second;
1711  if( param.scope() == scope ) {
1712  cata_variant value = md.get_arg_or( param_name, param.get( md ) );
1713  result.emplace( param_name, value );
1714  }
1715  }
1716  return mapgen_arguments{ result };
1717 }
1718 
1719 void mapgen_parameters::check_and_merge( const mapgen_parameters &other,
1720  const std::string &context, mapgen_parameter_scope up_to_scope )
1721 {
1722  for( const std::pair<const std::string, mapgen_parameter> &p : other.map ) {
1723  const mapgen_parameter &other_param = p.second;
1724  if( other_param.scope() >= up_to_scope ) {
1725  continue;
1726  }
1727  auto insert_result = map.insert( p );
1728  if( !insert_result.second ) {
1729  const std::string &name = p.first;
1730  const mapgen_parameter &this_param = insert_result.first->second;
1731  this_param.check_consistent_with(
1732  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(cata-translate-string-literal)
1733  other_param, string_format( "parameter %s in %s", name, context ) );
1734  }
1735  }
1736 }
1737 
1738 /**
1739  * This is a generic mapgen piece, the template parameter PieceType should be another specific
1740  * type of jmapgen_piece. This class contains a vector of those objects and will chose one of
1741  * it at random.
1742  */
1743 template<typename PieceType>
1744 class jmapgen_alternatively : public jmapgen_piece
1745 {
1746  public:
1747  // Note: this bypasses virtual function system, all items in this vector are of type
1748  // PieceType, they *can not* be of any other type.
1749  std::vector<PieceType> alternatives;
1750  jmapgen_alternatively() = default;
1751  mapgen_phase phase() const override {
1752  if( alternatives.empty() ) {
1753  return mapgen_phase::default_;
1754  }
1755  return alternatives[0].phase();
1756  }
1757  void check( const std::string &context, const mapgen_parameters &params,
1758  const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z ) const override {
1759  if( alternatives.empty() ) {
1760  debugmsg( "zero alternatives in jmapgen_alternatively in %s", context );
1761  }
1762  for( const PieceType &piece : alternatives ) {
1763  piece.check( context, params, x, y, z );
1764  }
1765  }
1766  void merge_parameters_into( mapgen_parameters &params,
1767  const std::string &outer_context ) const override {
1768  for( const PieceType &piece : alternatives ) {
1769  piece.merge_parameters_into( params, outer_context );
1770  }
1771  }
1772  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
1773  const std::string &context ) const override {
1774  if( const auto chosen = random_entry_opt( alternatives ) ) {
1775  chosen->get().apply( dat, x, y, z, context );
1776  }
1777  }
1778  bool has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &p ) const override {
1779  return dat.m.veh_at( tripoint( p.x(), p.y(), dat.zlevel() + p.z() ) ).has_value();
1780  }
1781 };
1782 
1783 template<typename Value>
1784 class jmapgen_constrained : public jmapgen_piece
1785 {
1786  public:
1787  jmapgen_constrained( shared_ptr_fast<const jmapgen_piece> und,
1788  const std::vector<mapgen_constraint<Value>> &cons )
1789  : underlying_piece( std::move( und ) )
1790  , constraints( cons )
1791  {}
1792 
1793  shared_ptr_fast<const jmapgen_piece> underlying_piece;
1794  std::vector<mapgen_constraint<Value>> constraints;
1795 
1796  mapgen_phase phase() const override {
1797  return underlying_piece->phase();
1798  }
1799  void check( const std::string &context, const mapgen_parameters &params,
1800  const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z ) const override {
1801  underlying_piece->check( context, params, x, y, z );
1802  }
1803 
1804  void merge_parameters_into( mapgen_parameters &params, const std::string &outer_context
1805  ) const override {
1806  underlying_piece->merge_parameters_into( params, outer_context );
1807  }
1808  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
1809  const std::string &context ) const override {
1810  for( const mapgen_constraint<Value> &constraint : constraints ) {
1811  Value param_value = dat.get_arg<Value>( constraint.parameter_name );
1812  if( param_value != constraint.value ) {
1813  return;
1814  }
1815  }
1816  underlying_piece->apply( dat, x, y, z, context );
1817  }
1818 };

1820 /**
1821  * Places fields on the map.
1822  * "field": field type ident.
1823  * "intensity": initial field intensity.
1824  * "age": initial field age.
1825  */
1826 class jmapgen_field : public jmapgen_piece
1827 {
1828  public:
1829  mapgen_value<field_type_id> ftype;
1830  std::vector<int> intensities;
1831  time_duration age;
1832  bool remove;
1833  jmapgen_field( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ ) :
1834  ftype( jsi.get_member( "field" ) )
1835  , age( time_duration::from_turns( jsi.get_int( "age", 0 ) ) )
1836  , remove( jsi.get_bool( "remove", false ) ) {
1837  if( jsi.has_array( "intensity" ) ) {
1838  for( JsonValue jv : jsi.get_array( "intensity" ) ) {
1839  intensities.push_back( jv.get_int() );
1840  }
1841  }
1842  if( intensities.empty() ) {
1843  intensities.push_back( jsi.get_int( "intensity", 1 ) );
1844  }
1845  }
1846  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
1847  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {
1848  field_type_id chosen_id = ftype.get( dat );
1849  if( chosen_id.id().is_null() ) {
1850  return;
1851  }
1852  if( remove ) {
1853  dat.m.remove_field( tripoint( x.get(), y.get(), z.get() ), chosen_id );
1854  } else {
1855  dat.m.add_field( tripoint( x.get(), y.get(), z.get() ), chosen_id,
1856  random_entry( intensities ), age );
1857  }
1858  }
1859 
1860  void check( const std::string &oter_name, const mapgen_parameters &parameters,
1861  const jmapgen_int &/*x*/, const jmapgen_int &/*y*/, const jmapgen_int &/*z*/
1862  ) const override {
1863  ftype.check( oter_name, parameters );
1864  }
1865 };
1866 /**
1867  * Place an NPC.
1868  * "class": the npc class, see @ref map::place_npc
1869  */
1870 class jmapgen_npc : public jmapgen_piece
1871 {
1872  public:
1873  mapgen_value<string_id<npc_template>> npc_class;
1874  bool target;
1875  std::vector<trait_id> traits;
1876  std::string unique_id;
1877  jmapgen_npc( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ ) :
1878  npc_class( jsi.get_member( "class" ) )
1879  , target( jsi.get_bool( "target", false ) ) {
1880  if( jsi.has_string( "add_trait" ) ) {
1881  traits.emplace_back();
1882  jsi.read( "add_trait", traits.back() );
1883  } else if( jsi.has_array( "add_trait" ) ) {
1884  jsi.read( "add_trait", traits );
1885  }
1886  if( jsi.has_string( "unique_id" ) ) {
1887  jsi.read( "unique_id", unique_id );
1888  }
1889  }
1890  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
1891  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {
1892  string_id<npc_template> chosen_id = npc_class.get( dat );
1893  if( chosen_id.is_null() ) {
1894  return;
1895  }
1896  if( !unique_id.empty() && g->unique_npc_exists( unique_id ) ) {
1897  add_msg_debug( debugmode::DF_NPC, "NPC with unique id %s already exists.", unique_id );
1898  return;
1899  }
1900  tripoint const dst( x.get(), y.get(), z.get() );
1901  // TODO: Make place_npc 3D aware.
1902  character_id npc_id = dat.m.place_npc( dst.xy(), chosen_id );
1903  if( get_map().inbounds( dat.m.getglobal( dst ) ) ) {
1904  dat.m.queue_main_cleanup();
1905  }
1906  if( dat.mission() && target ) {
1907  dat.mission()->set_target_npc_id( npc_id );
1908  }
1909  npc *p = g->find_npc( npc_id );
1910  if( p != nullptr ) {
1911  for( const trait_id &new_trait : traits ) {
1912  p->set_mutation( new_trait );
1913  }
1914  if( !unique_id.empty() ) {
1915  p->set_unique_id( unique_id );
1916  }
1917  }
1918  }
1919 
1920  void check( const std::string &oter_name, const mapgen_parameters &parameters,
1921  const jmapgen_int &/*x*/, const jmapgen_int &/*y*/, const jmapgen_int &/*z*/
1922  ) const override {
1923  npc_class.check( oter_name, parameters );
1924  }
1925 };

1957 /**
1958  * Place a sign with some text.
1959  * "signage": the text on the sign.
1960  */
1961 class jmapgen_sign : public jmapgen_piece
1962 {
1963  private:
1964  furn_id sign_furniture;
1965  public:
1966  translation signage;
1967  std::string snippet;
1968  jmapgen_sign( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ ) :
1969  snippet( jsi.get_string( "snippet", "" ) ) {
1970  jsi.read( "signage", signage );
1971  optional( jsi, false, "furniture", sign_furniture, furn_f_sign );
1972  if( signage.empty() && snippet.empty() ) {
1973  jsi.throw_error( "jmapgen_sign: needs either signage or snippet" );
1974  }
1975  if( !sign_furniture->has_flag( ter_furn_flag::TFLAG_SIGN ) ) {
1976  jsi.throw_error( "jmapgen_sign: specified furniture needs SIGN flag" );
1977  }
1978  }
1979  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
1980  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {
1981  const tripoint_bub_ms r( x.get(), y.get(), z.get() );
1982  dat.m.furn_set( r, furn_str_id::NULL_ID() );
1983  dat.m.furn_set( r, sign_furniture );
1984 
1985  std::string signtext;
1986 
1987  if( !snippet.empty() ) {
1988  // select a snippet from the category
1989  signtext = SNIPPET.random_from_category( snippet ).value_or( translation() ).translated();
1990  } else if( !signage.empty() ) {
1991  signtext = signage.translated();
1992  }
1993  if( !signtext.empty() ) {
1994  // replace tags
1995  std::string cityname = "illegible city name";
1996  tripoint_abs_sm abs_sub = dat.m.get_abs_sub();
1997  const city *c = overmap_buffer.closest_city( abs_sub ).city;
1998  if( c != nullptr ) {
1999  cityname = c->name;
2000  }
2001  signtext = apply_all_tags( signtext, cityname );
2002  }
2003  dat.m.set_signage( r.raw(), signtext );
2004  }
2005  std::string apply_all_tags( std::string signtext, const std::string &cityname ) const {
2006  signtext = SNIPPET.expand( signtext );
2007  replace_city_tag( signtext, cityname );
2008  return signtext;
2009  }
2010  bool has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &p ) const override {
2011  return dat.m.veh_at( tripoint_bub_ms( p.x(), p.y(), dat.zlevel() + p.z() ) ).has_value();
2012  }
2013 };

2129 /**
2130  * Place a gas pump with fuel in it.
2131  * "amount": number of fuel charges to place.
2132  */
2133 class jmapgen_gaspump : public jmapgen_piece
2134 {
2135  public:
2136  jmapgen_int amount;
2137  mapgen_value<itype_id> fuel;
2138  jmapgen_gaspump( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ ) :
2139  amount( jsi, "amount", 0, 0 ) {
2140  if( jsi.has_member( "fuel" ) ) {
2141  jsi.read( "fuel", fuel );
2142  }
2143  }
2144 
2145  void check( const std::string &oter_name, const mapgen_parameters &parameters,
2146  const jmapgen_int &/*x*/, const jmapgen_int &/*y*/, const jmapgen_int &/*z*/
2147  ) const override {
2148  fuel.check( oter_name, parameters );
2149  static const std::unordered_set<itype_id> valid_fuels = {
2150  itype_id::NULL_ID(), itype_gasoline, itype_diesel, itype_jp8, itype_avgas
2151  };
2152  for( const itype_id &possible_fuel : fuel.all_possible_results( parameters ) ) {
2153  // may want to not force this, if we want to support other fuels for some reason
2154  if( !valid_fuels.count( possible_fuel ) ) {
2155  debugmsg( "invalid fuel %s in %s", possible_fuel.str(), oter_name );
2156  }
2157  }
2158  }
2159 
2160  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
2161  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {
2162  const tripoint_bub_ms r( x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get() );
2163  int charges = amount.get() * 100;
2164  dat.m.furn_set( r, furn_str_id::NULL_ID() );
2165  if( charges == 0 ) {
2166  charges = rng( 10000, 50000 );
2167  }
2168  itype_id chosen_fuel = fuel.get( dat );
2169  if( chosen_fuel.is_null() ) {
2170  dat.m.place_gas_pump( r, charges );
2171  } else {
2172  dat.m.place_gas_pump( r, charges, chosen_fuel );
2173  }
2174  }
2175  bool has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &p ) const override {
2176  return dat.m.veh_at( tripoint_bub_ms( p.x(), p.y(), dat.zlevel() + p.z() ) ).has_value();
2177  }
2178 };

2180 /**
2181  * Place a specific liquid into the map.
2182  * "liquid": id of the liquid item (item should use charges)
2183  * "amount": quantity of liquid placed (a value of -1 uses the default amount)
2184  * "chance": chance of liquid being placed, see @ref map::place_items
2185  */
2186 class jmapgen_liquid_item : public jmapgen_piece
2187 {
2188  public:
2189  jmapgen_int amount;
2190  mapgen_value<itype_id> liquid;
2191  jmapgen_int chance;
2192  jmapgen_liquid_item( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ ) :
2193  amount( jsi, "amount", -1, -1 )
2194  , liquid( jsi.get_member( "liquid" ) )
2195  , chance( jsi, "chance", 1, 1 ) {
2196  }
2197  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
2198  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {
2199  if( one_in( chance.get() ) ) {
2200  itype_id chosen_id = liquid.get( dat );
2201  if( chosen_id.is_null() ) {
2202  return;
2203  }
2204  // Itemgroups apply migrations when being loaded, but we need to migrate
2205  // individual items here.
2206  itype_id migrated = item_controller->migrate_id( chosen_id );
2207  item newliquid( migrated, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
2208 
2209  if( amount.val > -1 ) {
2210  if( amount.valmax > -1 ) {
2211  newliquid.charges = amount.get();
2212  } else {
2213  newliquid.charges = amount.val;
2214  }
2215  if( migrated == itype_gasoline ||
2216  migrated == itype_avgas ||
2217  migrated == itype_diesel ||
2218  migrated == itype_jp8 ) {
2219  newliquid.charges *= 100;
2220  }
2221  }
2222  if( newliquid.charges > 0 ) {
2223  dat.m.add_item_or_charges(
2224  tripoint( x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get() ), newliquid );
2225  }
2226  }
2227  }
2228 
2229  void check( const std::string &oter_name, const mapgen_parameters &parameters,
2230  const jmapgen_int &/*x*/, const jmapgen_int &/*y*/, const jmapgen_int & /*z*/
2231  ) const override {
2232  liquid.check( oter_name, parameters );
2233  }
2234 };

2304 class jmapgen_loot : public jmapgen_piece
2305 {

2307 
2308  public:
2309  explicit jmapgen_loot( const JsonObject &jsi ) :
2310  result_group( Item_group::Type::G_COLLECTION, 100, jsi.get_int( "ammo", 0 ),
2311  jsi.get_int( "magazine", 0 ), "mapgen loot entry" )
2312  , chance( jsi.get_int( "chance", 100 ) ) {
2313  const item_group_id group( jsi.get_string( "group", std::string() ) );
2314  itype_id ity;
2315  jsi.read( "item", ity );
2316

2318  jsi.throw_error( "must provide either item or group" );
2319  }
2320  if( !group.is_empty() && !item_group::group_is_defined( group ) ) {
2321  set_mapgen_defer( jsi, "group", "no such item group" );
2322  }
2323  if( !ity.is_empty() && !item::type_is_defined( ity ) ) {
2324  set_mapgen_defer( jsi, "item", "no such item type '" + ity.str() + "'" );
2325  }
2326

2330  // migrated individually

2333  variant = jsi.get_string( "variant" );
2334  }

2336  } else {
2337  result_group.add_group_entry( group, 100 );
2338  }
2339  result_group.finalize( itype_id::NULL_ID() );
2340  }

2343  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {

2346  std::vector<item> spawn;
2347  spawn.reserve( 20 );
2348  isd->create( spawn, calendar::start_of_cataclysm,
2349  spawn_flags::use_spawn_rate );
2350  dat.m.spawn_items( tripoint( rng( x.val, x.valmax ), rng( y.val, y.valmax ),
2351  dat.zlevel() + z.get() ), spawn );
2352  }

2394 /**
2395  * Place spawn points for a specific monster.
2396  * "monster": id of the monster. or "group": id of the monster group.
2397  * "friendly": whether the new monster is friendly to the player character.
2398  * "name": the name of the monster (if it has one).
2399  * "chance": the percentage chance of a monster, affected by spawn density
2400  * If high density means greater than one hundred percent, can place multiples.
2401  * "repeat": roll this many times for creatures, potentially spawning multiples.
2402  * "pack_size": place this many creatures each time a roll is successful.
2403  * "one_or_none": place max of 1 (or pack_size) monsters, even if spawn density > 1.
2404  * Defaults to true if repeat and pack_size are unset, false if one is set.
2405  */
2406 class jmapgen_monster : public jmapgen_piece
2407 {
2408  public:
2409  weighted_int_list<mapgen_value<mtype_id>> ids;
2410  mapgen_value<mongroup_id> m_id;
2411  jmapgen_int chance;
2412  jmapgen_int pack_size;
2413  bool one_or_none;
2414  bool friendly;
2415  std::optional<translation> name = std::nullopt;
2416  std::string random_name_str;
2417  bool target;
2418  bool use_pack_size;
2419  struct spawn_data data;
2420  jmapgen_monster( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ ) :
2421  chance( jsi, "chance", 100, 100 )
2422  , pack_size( jsi, "pack_size", 1, 1 )
2423  , one_or_none( jsi.get_bool( "one_or_none",
2424  !( jsi.has_member( "repeat" ) ||
2425  jsi.has_member( "pack_size" ) ) ) )
2426  , friendly( jsi.get_bool( "friendly", false ) )
2427  , random_name_str( jsi.get_string( "random_name", "" ) )
2428  , target( jsi.get_bool( "target", false ) )
2429  , use_pack_size( jsi.get_bool( "use_pack_size", false ) ) {
2430 
2431  {
2432  translation translated_name;
2433  if( jsi.read( "name", translated_name ) ) {
2434  name.emplace( std::move( translated_name ) );
2435  } else if( random_name_str == "snippet" ) {
2436  debugmsg( "Field \"name\" is missing for random name 'snippet'" );
2437  }
2438  }
2439 
2440  if( jsi.has_member( "group" ) ) {
2441  jsi.read( "group", m_id );
2442  } else if( jsi.has_array( "monster" ) ) {
2443  load_weighted_list( jsi.get_member( "monster" ), ids, 100 );
2444  } else {
2445  mapgen_value<mtype_id> id( jsi.get_member( "monster" ) );
2446  ids.add( id, 100 );
2447  }
2448 
2449  std::set<std::string> valid_random_name_strs = { "random", "female", "male", "snippet", "" };
2450  if( valid_random_name_strs.count( random_name_str ) == 0 ) {
2451  debugmsg( "Invalid random name '%s'", random_name_str );
2452  }
2453 
2454  if( jsi.has_object( "spawn_data" ) ) {
2455  const JsonObject &sd = jsi.get_object( "spawn_data" );
2456  if( sd.has_array( "ammo" ) ) {
2457  const JsonArray &ammos = sd.get_array( "ammo" );
2458  for( const JsonObject adata : ammos ) {
2459  data.ammo.emplace( itype_id( adata.get_string( "ammo_id" ) ),
2460  jmapgen_int( adata, "qty" ) );
2461  }
2462  }
2463  if( sd.has_array( "patrol" ) ) {
2464  const JsonArray &patrol_pts = sd.get_array( "patrol" );
2465  for( const JsonObject p_pt : patrol_pts ) {
2466  jmapgen_int ptx = jmapgen_int( p_pt, "x" );
2467  jmapgen_int pty = jmapgen_int( p_pt, "y" );
2468  data.patrol_points_rel_ms.emplace_back( ptx.get(), pty.get() );
2469  }
2470  }
2471  }
2472  }
2473 
2474  void check( const std::string &oter_name, const mapgen_parameters &parameters,
2475  const jmapgen_int &/*x*/, const jmapgen_int &/*y*/, const jmapgen_int &/*z*/
2476  ) const override {
2477  for( const weighted_object<int, mapgen_value<mtype_id>> &id : ids ) {
2478  id.obj.check( oter_name, parameters );
2479  }
2480  m_id.check( oter_name, parameters );
2481  }
2482 
2483  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
2484  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {
2485 
2486  int raw_odds = chance.get();
2487 
2488  // Handle spawn density: Increase odds, but don't let the odds of absence go below
2489  // half the odds at density 1.
2490  // Instead, apply a multiplier to the number of monsters for really high densities.
2491  // For example, a 50% chance at spawn density 4 becomes a 75% chance of ~2.7 monsters.
2492  int odds_after_density = raw_odds * get_option<float>( "SPAWN_DENSITY" );
2493  int max_odds = ( 100 + raw_odds ) / 2;
2494  float density_multiplier = 1.0f;
2495  if( odds_after_density > max_odds ) {
2496  density_multiplier = 1.0f * odds_after_density / max_odds;
2497  odds_after_density = max_odds;
2498  }
2499 
2500  int mission_id = -1;
2501  if( dat.mission() && target ) {
2502  mission_id = dat.mission()->get_id();
2503  }
2504 
2505  int spawn_count = roll_remainder( density_multiplier );
2506 
2507  // don't let high spawn density alone cause more than 1 to spawn.
2508  if( one_or_none ) {
2509  spawn_count = std::min( spawn_count, 1 );
2510  }
2511  // don't spawn less than 1 if odds were 100%, even with low spawn density.
2512  if( raw_odds == 100 ) {
2513  spawn_count = std::max( spawn_count, 1 );
2514  } else {
2515  if( !x_in_y( odds_after_density, 100 ) ) {
2516  return;
2517  }
2518  }
2519 
2520  mongroup_id chosen_group = m_id.get( dat );
2521  std::optional<std::string> chosen_name = std::nullopt;
2522  if( !random_name_str.empty() ) {
2523  if( random_name_str == "female" ) {
2524  chosen_name.emplace( SNIPPET.expand( "<female_given_name>" ) );
2525  } else if( random_name_str == "male" ) {
2526  chosen_name.emplace( SNIPPET.expand( "<male_given_name>" ) );
2527  } else if( random_name_str == "random" ) {
2528  chosen_name.emplace( SNIPPET.expand( "<given_name>" ) );
2529  } else if( random_name_str == "snippet" && name.has_value() ) {
2530  chosen_name.emplace( SNIPPET.expand( name.value().translated() ) );
2531  }
2532  }
2533  if( !chosen_name.has_value() && name.has_value() ) {
2534  chosen_name.emplace( name.value().translated() );
2535  }
2536  if( !chosen_group.is_null() ) {
2537  std::vector<MonsterGroupResult> spawn_details =
2538  MonsterGroupManager::GetResultFromGroup( chosen_group, nullptr, nullptr, false, nullptr,
2539  use_pack_size );
2540  for( const MonsterGroupResult &mgr : spawn_details ) {
2541  dat.m.add_spawn( mgr.name, spawn_count * pack_size.get(),
2542  { x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get()},
2543  friendly, -1, mission_id, chosen_name, data );
2544  }
2545  } else if( ids.is_valid() ) {
2546  mtype_id chosen_type = ids.pick()->get( dat );
2547  if( !chosen_type.is_null() ) {
2548  dat.m.add_spawn( chosen_type, spawn_count * pack_size.get(),
2549  { x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get()},
2550  friendly, -1, mission_id, chosen_name, data );
2551  }
2552  }
2553  }
2554 };
2555 
2556 static inclusive_rectangle<point> vehicle_bounds( const vehicle_prototype &vp )
2557 {
2558  point min( INT_MAX, INT_MAX );
2559  point max( INT_MIN, INT_MIN );
2560 
2561  cata_assert( !vp.parts.empty() );
2562 
2563  for( const vehicle_prototype::part_def &part : vp.parts ) {
2564  min.x = std::min( min.x, part.pos.x );
2565  max.x = std::max( max.x, part.pos.x );
2566  min.y = std::min( min.y, part.pos.y );
2567  max.y = std::max( max.y, part.pos.y );
2568  }
2569 
2570  return { min, max };
2571 }
2572 
2573 /**
2574  * Place a vehicle.
2575  * "vehicle": id of the vehicle.
2576  * "chance": chance of spawning the vehicle: 0...100
2577  * "rotation": rotation of the vehicle, see @ref vehicle::vehicle
2578  * "fuel": fuel status of the vehicle, see @ref vehicle::vehicle
2579  * "status": overall (damage) status of the vehicle, see @ref vehicle::vehicle
2580  */
2581 class jmapgen_vehicle : public jmapgen_piece
2582 {
2583  public:
2584  mapgen_value<vgroup_id> type;
2585  jmapgen_int chance;
2586  std::vector<units::angle> rotation;
2587  int fuel;
2588  int status;
2589  std::string faction;
2590  jmapgen_vehicle( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ ) :
2591  type( jsi.get_member( "vehicle" ) )
2592  , chance( jsi, "chance", 1, 1 )
2593  //, rotation( jsi.get_int( "rotation", 0 ) ) // unless there is a way for the json parser to
2594  // return a single int as a list, we have to manually check this in the constructor below
2595  , fuel( jsi.get_int( "fuel", -1 ) )
2596  , status( jsi.get_int( "status", -1 ) ) {
2597  if( jsi.has_array( "rotation" ) ) {
2598  for( const JsonValue elt : jsi.get_array( "rotation" ) ) {
2599  rotation.push_back( units::from_degrees( elt.get_int() ) );
2600  }
2601  } else {
2602  rotation.push_back( units::from_degrees( jsi.get_int( "rotation", 0 ) ) );
2603  }
2604 
2605  if( jsi.has_string( "faction" ) ) {
2606  faction = jsi.get_string( "faction" );
2607  }
2608  }
2609  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
2610  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {
2611  if( !x_in_y( chance.get(), 100 ) ) {
2612  return;
2613  }
2614  vgroup_id chosen_id = type.get( dat );
2615  if( chosen_id.is_null() ) {
2616  return;
2617  }
2618  tripoint const dst( x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get() );
2619  vehicle *veh = dat.m.add_vehicle( chosen_id->pick(), dst, random_entry( rotation ),
2620  fuel, status );
2621  if( veh && !faction.empty() ) {
2622  veh->set_owner( faction_id( faction ) );
2623  }
2624  if( get_map().inbounds( dat.m.getglobal( dst ) ) ) {
2625  dat.m.queue_main_cleanup();
2626  }
2627  }
2628  bool has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &p ) const override {
2629  return dat.m.veh_at( tripoint_bub_ms( p.x(), p.y(), dat.zlevel() + p.z() ) ).has_value();
2630  }
2631 
2632  void check( const std::string &context, const mapgen_parameters &parameters,
2633  const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &/*z*/
2634  ) const override {
2635  type.check( context, parameters );
2636 
2637  if( x.val == -1 ) {
2638  // We are in a palette, so no need to verify that the positions
2639  // are valid
2640  return;
2641  }
2642 
2643  // The rest of this function is devoted to ensuring that this
2644  // vehicle placement does not lead to a vehicle overlapping an OMT
2645  // boundary, because that causes issues (e.g. if the vehicle is
2646  // damaged and tries to drop items during mapgen, they may drop on
2647  // points outside the map).
2648 
2649  point min( INT_MAX, INT_MAX );
2650  point max( INT_MIN, INT_MIN );
2651  vgroup_id min_x_vg;
2652  vproto_id min_x_vp;
2653  vgroup_id max_x_vg;
2654  vproto_id max_x_vp;
2655  vgroup_id min_y_vg;
2656  vproto_id min_y_vp;
2657  vgroup_id max_y_vg;
2658  vproto_id max_y_vp;
2659  for( const vgroup_id &vg_id : type.all_possible_results( parameters ) ) {
2660  for( const vproto_id &vp_id : vg_id->all_possible_results() ) {
2661  inclusive_rectangle<point> bounds = vehicle_bounds( *vp_id );
2662  if( bounds.p_min.x < min.x ) {
2663  min_x_vg = vg_id;
2664  min_x_vp = vp_id;
2665  min.x = bounds.p_min.x;
2666  }
2667  if( bounds.p_max.x > max.x ) {
2668  max_x_vg = vg_id;
2669  max_x_vp = vp_id;
2670  max.x = bounds.p_max.x;
2671  }
2672  if( bounds.p_min.y < min.y ) {
2673  min_y_vg = vg_id;
2674  min_y_vp = vp_id;
2675  min.y = bounds.p_min.y;
2676  }
2677  if( bounds.p_max.y > max.y ) {
2678  max_y_vg = vg_id;
2679  max_y_vp = vp_id;
2680  max.y = bounds.p_max.y;
2681  }
2682  }
2683  }
2684 
2685  for( units::angle rot : rotation ) {
2686  int degrees = to_degrees( rot );
2687  while( degrees < 0 ) {
2688  degrees += 360;
2689  }
2690  if( degrees % 90 != 0 ) {
2691  // TODO: support non-rectilinear vehicle placement
2692  continue;
2693  }
2694  int turns = degrees / 90;
2695  point rotated_min = min.rotate( turns );
2696  point rotated_max = max.rotate( turns );
2697  point new_min( std::min( rotated_min.x, rotated_max.x ),
2698  std::min( rotated_min.y, rotated_max.y ) );
2699  point new_max( std::max( rotated_min.x, rotated_max.x ),
2700  std::max( rotated_min.y, rotated_max.y ) );
2701 
2702  new_min += point( x.val, y.val );
2703  new_max += point( x.valmax, y.valmax );
2704 
2705  cube_direction bad_rotated_direction = cube_direction::last;
2706  std::string extreme_coord;
2707 
2708  if( new_min.x < 0 ) {
2709  bad_rotated_direction = cube_direction::west;
2710  extreme_coord = string_format( "x = %d (should be at least 0)", new_min.x );
2711  } else if( new_max.x >= 24 ) {
2712  bad_rotated_direction = cube_direction::east;
2713  extreme_coord = string_format( "x = %d (should be at most 23)", new_max.x );
2714  } else if( new_min.y < 0 ) {
2715  extreme_coord = string_format( "y = %d (should be at least 0)", new_min.y );
2716  bad_rotated_direction = cube_direction::north;
2717  } else if( new_max.y >= 24 ) {
2718  bad_rotated_direction = cube_direction::south;
2719  extreme_coord = string_format( "y = %d (should be at most 23)", new_max.y );
2720  } else {
2721  continue;
2722  }
2723 
2724  cube_direction bad_direction = bad_rotated_direction - turns;
2725 
2726  std::string bad_vehicle;
2727  auto format_option = []( const vgroup_id & vg, const vproto_id & vp ) {
2728  return string_format(
2729  "[vgroup_id %s; vproto_id %s]", vg.str(), vp.str() );
2730  };
2731  switch( bad_direction ) {
2732  case cube_direction::north:
2733  bad_vehicle = format_option( min_y_vg, min_y_vp );
2734  break;
2735  case cube_direction::south:
2736  bad_vehicle = format_option( max_y_vg, max_y_vp );
2737  break;
2738  case cube_direction::east:
2739  bad_vehicle = format_option( max_x_vg, max_x_vp );
2740  break;
2741  case cube_direction::west:
2742  bad_vehicle = format_option( min_x_vg, min_x_vp );
2743  break;
2744  default:
2745  cata_fatal( "Invalid bad_direction %d", bad_direction );
2746  }
2747  debugmsg( "In %s, vehicle placement at x:[%d,%d], y:[%d,%d]: "
2748  "potential placement of vehicle out of bounds. "
2749  "At rotation %d the vehicle %s extends too far %s, "
2750  "reaching coordinate %s",
2751  context, x.val, x.valmax, y.val, y.valmax, degrees,
2752  bad_vehicle, io::enum_to_string( bad_rotated_direction ),
2753  extreme_coord );
2754  // Early exit because we don't want too much error spam
2755  // from the same mapgen piece
2756  return;
2757  }
2758  }
2759 };
2760 /**
2761  * Place a specific item.
2762  * "item": id of item type to spawn.
2763  * "chance": chance of spawning it (1 = always, otherwise one_in(chance)).
2764  * "amount": amount of items to spawn.
2765  * "repeat": number of times to apply this piece
2766  */
2767 class jmapgen_spawn_item : public jmapgen_piece
2768 {
2769  public:
2770  mapgen_value<itype_id> type;
2771  std::string variant;
2772  std::string faction;
2773  jmapgen_int amount;
2774  jmapgen_int chance;
2775  std::set<flag_id> flags;
2776  jmapgen_spawn_item( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ ) :
2777  type( jsi.get_member( "item" ) )
2778  , amount( jsi, "amount", 1, 1 )
2779  , chance( jsi, "chance", 100, 100 )
2780  , flags( jsi.get_tags<flag_id>( "custom-flags" ) ) {
2781  if( jsi.has_string( "variant" ) ) {
2782  variant = jsi.get_string( "variant" );
2783  }
2784  if( jsi.has_string( "faction" ) ) {
2785  faction = jsi.get_string( "faction" );
2786  }
2787  repeat = jmapgen_int( jsi, "repeat", 1, 1 );
2788  }
2789  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
2790  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {
2791  itype_id chosen_id = type.get( dat );
2792  if( chosen_id.is_null() ) {
2793  return;
2794  }
2795  // Itemgroups apply migrations when being loaded, but we need to migrate
2796  // individual items here.
2797  chosen_id = item_controller->migrate_id( chosen_id );
2798 
2799  const int c = chance.get();
2800 
2801  // 100% chance = exactly 1 item, otherwise scale by item spawn rate.
2802  const float spawn_rate = get_option<float>( "ITEM_SPAWNRATE" );
2803  int spawn_count = ( c == 100 ) ? 1 : roll_remainder( c * spawn_rate / 100.0f );
2804  for( int i = 0; i < spawn_count; i++ ) {
2805  dat.m.spawn_item( tripoint( x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get() ), chosen_id, amount.get(),
2806  0, calendar::start_of_cataclysm, 0, flags, variant, faction );
2807  }
2808  }
2809 
2810  void check( const std::string &oter_name, const mapgen_parameters &parameters,
2811  const jmapgen_int &/*x*/, const jmapgen_int &/*y*/, const jmapgen_int &/*z*/
2812  ) const override {
2813  type.check( oter_name, parameters );
2814  }
2815 };

2817  * Place a trap.
