2819  */
2820 class jmapgen_trap : public jmapgen_piece
2821 {
2822  public:

2825 
2826  jmapgen_trap( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ ) {
2827  init( jsi.get_member( "trap" ) );
2828  remove = jsi.get_bool( "remove", false );
2829  }
2830 
2831  explicit jmapgen_trap( const JsonValue &tid ) {
2832  if( tid.test_object() ) {
2833  JsonObject jo = tid.get_object();
2834  remove = jo.get_bool( "remove", false );
2835  if( jo.has_member( "trap" ) ) {
2836  init( jo.get_member( "trap" ) );
2837  return;
2838  }
2839  }
2840  init( tid );
2841  }
2842  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
2843  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {

2846  return;
2847  }
2848  const tripoint actual_loc = tripoint( x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get() );
2849  if( remove ) {
2850  dat.m.remove_trap( actual_loc );
2851  } else {
2852  dat.m.trap_set( actual_loc, chosen_id );
2853  }
2854  }
2855  bool has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &p ) const override {
2856  return dat.m.veh_at( tripoint_bub_ms( p.x(), p.y(), dat.zlevel() + p.z() ) ).has_value();
2857  }

2861  ) const override {
2862  id.check( oter_name, parameters );
2863  }
2864  private:
2865  void init( const JsonValue &jsi ) {
2866  id = mapgen_value<trap_id>( jsi );
2867  }

2903 /**
2904  * Place terrain.
2905  * "ter": id of the terrain.
2906  */
2907 class jmapgen_terrain : public jmapgen_piece
2908 {
2909  private:
2910  enum apply_action {
2911  act_unknown, act_ignore, act_dismantle, act_erase
2912  };
2913  public:
2914  mapgen_value<ter_id> id;
2915  jmapgen_terrain( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ ) :
2916  jmapgen_terrain( jsi.get_member( "ter" ) ) {}
2917  explicit jmapgen_terrain( const JsonValue &tid ) : id( mapgen_value<ter_id>( tid ) ) {}
2918 
2919  bool is_nop() const override {
2920  return id.is_null();
2921  }
2922  mapgen_phase phase() const override {
2923  return mapgen_phase::terrain;
2924  }
2925 
2926  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
2927  const std::string &context ) const override {
2928  ter_id chosen_id = id.get( dat );
2929  if( chosen_id.id().is_null() ) {
2930  return;
2931  }
2932  tripoint p( x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get() );
2933 
2934  ter_id terrain_here = dat.m.ter( p );
2935  const ter_t &chosen_ter = *chosen_id;
2936  const bool is_wall = chosen_ter.has_flag( ter_furn_flag::TFLAG_WALL );
2937  const bool place_item = chosen_ter.has_flag( ter_furn_flag::TFLAG_PLACE_ITEM );
2938  const bool is_boring_wall = is_wall && !place_item;
2939 
2940  apply_action act_furn = apply_action::act_unknown;
2941  apply_action act_trap = apply_action::act_unknown;
2942  apply_action act_item = apply_action::act_unknown;
2943 
2944  // shorthand flags
2945  if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_other_data ) ) {
2946  act_furn = apply_action::act_ignore;
2947  act_trap = apply_action::act_ignore;
2948  act_item = apply_action::act_ignore;
2949  } else if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::dismantle_all_before_placing_terrain ) ) {
2950  act_furn = apply_action::act_dismantle;
2951  act_trap = apply_action::act_dismantle;
2952  act_item = apply_action::act_ignore;
2953  } else if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::erase_all_before_placing_terrain ) ) {
2954  act_furn = apply_action::act_erase;
2955  act_trap = apply_action::act_erase;
2956  act_item = apply_action::act_erase;
2957  }
2958 
2959  // specific flags override shorthand flags
2960  if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_furniture ) ) {
2961  act_furn = apply_action::act_ignore;
2962  } else if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::dismantle_furniture_before_placing_terrain ) ) {
2963  act_furn = apply_action::act_dismantle;
2964  } else if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::erase_furniture_before_placing_terrain ) ) {
2965  act_furn = apply_action::act_erase;
2966  }
2967  if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_trap ) ) {
2968  act_trap = apply_action::act_ignore;
2969  } else if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::dismantle_trap_before_placing_terrain ) ) {
2970  act_trap = apply_action::act_dismantle;
2971  } else if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::erase_trap_before_placing_terrain ) ) {
2972  act_trap = apply_action::act_erase;
2973  }
2974  if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_items ) ) {
2975  act_item = apply_action::act_ignore;
2976  } else if( dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::erase_items_before_placing_terrain ) ) {
2977  act_item = apply_action::act_erase;
2978  }
2979 
2980  if( act_item == apply_action::act_erase &&
2981  ( act_furn == apply_action::act_dismantle || act_trap == apply_action::act_dismantle ) ) {
2982  debugmsg( "In %s on %s, the mapgen is configured to dismantle preexisting furniture "
2983  "and/or traps, but will also erase preexisting items. This is probably a "
2984  "mistake, as any dismantle outputs will not be preserved.",
2985  context, dat.terrain_type().id().str() );
2986  }
2987 
2988  if( is_boring_wall || act_furn == apply_action::act_erase ) {
2989  dat.m.furn_clear( p );
2990  // remove sign writing data from the submap
2991  dat.m.delete_signage( p );
2992  } else if( act_furn == apply_action::act_dismantle ) {
2993  int max_recurse = 10; // insurance against infinite looping
2994  std::string initial_furn = dat.m.furn( p ) != furn_str_id::NULL_ID() ? dat.m.furn(
2995  p ).id().str() : "";
2996  while( dat.m.has_furn( p ) && max_recurse-- > 0 ) {
2997  const furn_t &f = dat.m.furn( p ).obj();
2998  if( f.deconstruct.can_do ) {
2999  if( f.deconstruct.furn_set.str().empty() ) {
3000  dat.m.furn_clear( p );
3001  } else {
3002  dat.m.furn_set( p, f.deconstruct.furn_set );
3003  }
3004  dat.m.spawn_items( p, item_group::items_from( f.deconstruct.drop_group, calendar::turn ) );
3005  } else {
3006  if( f.bash.furn_set.str().empty() ) {
3007  dat.m.furn_clear( p );
3008  } else {
3009  dat.m.furn_set( p, f.bash.furn_set );
3010  }
3011  dat.m.spawn_items( p, item_group::items_from( f.bash.drop_group, calendar::turn ) );
3012  }
3013  }
3014  if( !max_recurse ) {
3015  dat.m.furn_clear( p );
3016  debugmsg( "In %s on %s, the mapgen failed to arrive at an empty tile after "
3017  "dismantling preexisting furniture %s at %s 10 times in succession.",
3018  context, dat.terrain_type().id().str(), initial_furn, p.to_string() );
3019  }
3020  // remove sign writing data from the submap
3021  dat.m.delete_signage( p );
3022  }
3023 
3024  if( is_boring_wall || act_trap == apply_action::act_erase ) {
3025  dat.m.remove_trap( p );
3026  } else if( act_trap == apply_action::act_dismantle ) {
3027  dat.m.tr_at( p ).on_disarmed( dat.m, p );
3028  }
3029 
3030  if( is_boring_wall || act_item == apply_action::act_erase ) {
3031  dat.m.i_clear( p );
3032  }
3033 
3034  if( chosen_id != terrain_here ) {
3035  std::string error;
3036  trap_str_id trap_here = dat.m.tr_at( p ).id;
3037  if( act_furn != apply_action::act_ignore && dat.m.furn( p ) != furn_str_id::NULL_ID() ) {
3038  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(cata-translate-string-literal)
3039  error = string_format( "furniture was %s", dat.m.furn( p ).id().str() );
3040  } else if( act_trap != apply_action::act_ignore && !trap_here.is_null() &&
3041  trap_here.id() != terrain_here->trap ) {
3042  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(cata-translate-string-literal)
3043  error = string_format( "trap %s existed", trap_here.str() );
3044  } else if( act_item != apply_action::act_ignore && !dat.m.i_at( p ).empty() ) {
3045  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(cata-translate-string-literal)
3046  error = string_format( "item %s existed",
3047  dat.m.i_at( p ).begin()->typeId().str() );
3048  }
3049  if( !error.empty() ) {
3050  debugmsg( "In %s on %s, setting terrain to %s (from %s) at %s when %s. "
3051  "Resolve this either by removing the terrain from this mapgen, "
3052  "adding suitable removal commands to the mapgen, or by adding an "
3053  "appropriate clearing flag to the innermost layered mapgen. "
3054  "Consult the \"mapgen flags\" section in MAPGEN.md for options.",
3055  context, dat.terrain_type().id().str(), chosen_id.id().str(),
3056  terrain_here.id().str(), p.to_string(), error );
3057  }
3058  }
3059  dat.m.ter_set( p, chosen_id );
3060  }
3061  bool has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &p ) const override {
3062  return dat.m.veh_at( tripoint_bub_ms( p.x(), p.y(), dat.zlevel() + p.z() ) ).has_value();
3063  }
3064 
3065  void check( const std::string &oter_name, const mapgen_parameters &parameters,
3066  const jmapgen_int &/*x*/, const jmapgen_int &/*y*/, const jmapgen_int &/*z*/
3067  ) const override {
3068  id.check( oter_name, parameters );
3069  }
3070 };

3150 class jmapgen_computer : public jmapgen_piece
3151 {

3153  translation name;
3154  translation access_denied;
3155  int security;
3156  std::vector<computer_option> options;
3157  std::vector<computer_failure> failures;
3158  std::vector<std::string> chat_topics;

3166  if( jsi.has_array( "options" ) ) {

3183  chat_topics.emplace_back( topic );

3186  }
3187  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
3188  const std::string &/*context*/ ) const override {
3189  const tripoint_bub_ms r( x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get() );
3190  dat.m.furn_set( r, furn_f_console );
3191  computer *cpu =
3192  dat.m.add_computer( r.raw(), name.translated(),
3193  security );
3194  for( const computer_option &opt : options ) {
3195  cpu->add_option( opt );
3196  }
3197  for( const computer_failure &opt : failures ) {
3198  cpu->add_failure( opt );
3199  }
3200  if( target && dat.mission() ) {
3201  cpu->set_mission( dat.mission()->get_id() );
3202  }
3203  for( const effect_on_condition_id &eoc : eocs ) {
3204  cpu->add_eoc( eoc );
3205  }
3206  for( const std::string &chat_topic : chat_topics ) {
3207  cpu->add_chat_topic( chat_topic );
3208  }
3209  // The default access denied message is defined in computer's constructor
3210  if( !access_denied.empty() ) {
3211  cpu->set_access_denied_msg( access_denied.translated() );
3212  }
3213  }
3214  bool has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &p ) const override {
3215  return dat.m.veh_at( tripoint_bub_ms( p.x(), p.y(), dat.zlevel() + p.z() ) ).has_value();
3216  }
3217 };

3219 /**
3220  * Place an item in furniture (expected to be used with NOITEM SEALED furniture like plants).
3221  * "item": item to spawn (object with usual parameters).
3222  * "items": item group to spawn (object with usual parameters).
3223  * "furniture": furniture to create around it.
3224  */
3225 class jmapgen_sealed_item : public jmapgen_piece
3226 {
3227  public:
3228  mapgen_value<furn_id> furniture;
3229  jmapgen_int chance;
3230  std::optional<jmapgen_spawn_item> item_spawner;
3231  std::optional<jmapgen_item_group> item_group_spawner;
3232  jmapgen_sealed_item( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string &context )
3233  : furniture( jsi.get_member( "furniture" ) )
3234  , chance( jsi, "chance", 100, 100 ) {
3235  if( jsi.has_object( "item" ) ) {
3236  JsonObject item_obj = jsi.get_object( "item" );
3237  item_spawner = jmapgen_spawn_item( item_obj, "item for " + context );
3238  }
3239  if( jsi.has_object( "items" ) ) {
3240  JsonObject items_obj = jsi.get_object( "items" );
3241  item_group_spawner = jmapgen_item_group( items_obj, "items for " + context );
3242  }
3243  }
3244 
3245  void check( const std::string &context, const mapgen_parameters &params,
3246  const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z ) const override {
3247  std::string short_summary =
3248  string_format( "sealed_item special in json mapgen for %s", context );
3249  if( !item_spawner && !item_group_spawner ) {
3250  debugmsg( "%s specifies neither an item nor an item group. "
3251  "It should specify at least one.",
3252  short_summary );
3253  return;
3254  }
3255 
3256  for( const furn_str_id &f : furniture.all_possible_results( params ) ) {
3257  std::string summary =
3258  string_format( "%s using furniture %s", short_summary, f.str() );
3259 
3260  if( !f.is_valid() ) {
3261  debugmsg( "%s which is not valid furniture", summary );
3262  return;
3263  }
3264 
3265  const furn_t &furn = *f;
3266 
3267  if( furn.has_flag( ter_furn_flag::TFLAG_PLANT ) ) {
3268  // plant furniture requires exactly one seed item within it
3269  if( item_spawner && item_group_spawner ) {
3270  debugmsg( "%s (with flag PLANT) specifies both an item and an item group. "
3271  "It should specify exactly one.",
3272  summary );
3273  return;
3274  }
3275 
3276  if( item_spawner ) {
3277  item_spawner->check( context, params, x, y, z );
3278  int count = item_spawner->amount.get();
3279  if( count != 1 ) {
3280  debugmsg( "%s (with flag PLANT) spawns %d items; it should spawn "
3281  "exactly one.", summary, count );
3282  return;
3283  }
3284  int item_chance = item_spawner->chance.get();
3285  if( item_chance != 100 ) {
3286  debugmsg( "%s (with flag PLANT) spawns an item with probability %d%%; "
3287  "it should always spawn. You can move the \"chance\" up to "
3288  "the sealed_item instead of the \"item\" within.",
3289  summary, item_chance );
3290  return;
3291  }
3292  for( const itype_id &t :
3293  item_spawner->type.all_possible_results( params ) ) {
3294  const itype *spawned_type = item::find_type( t );
3295  if( !spawned_type->seed ) {
3296  debugmsg( "%s (with flag PLANT) spawns item type %s which is not a "
3297  "seed.", summary, spawned_type->get_id().str() );
3298  return;
3299  }
3300  }
3301  }
3302 
3303  if( item_group_spawner ) {
3304  item_group_spawner->check( context, params, x, y, z );
3305  int ig_chance = item_group_spawner->chance.get();
3306  if( ig_chance != 100 ) {
3307  debugmsg( "%s (with flag PLANT) spawns item group %s with chance %d. "
3308  "It should have chance 100. You can move the \"chance\" up "
3309  "to the sealed_item instead of the \"items\" within.",
3310  summary, item_group_spawner->group_id.str(), ig_chance );
3311  return;
3312  }
3313  item_group_id group_id = item_group_spawner->group_id;
3314  for( const itype *type :
3315  item_group::every_possible_item_from( group_id ) ) {
3316  if( !type->seed ) {
3317  debugmsg( "%s (with flag PLANT) spawns item group %s which can "
3318  "spawn item %s which is not a seed.",
3319  summary, group_id.str(), type->get_id().str() );
3320  return;
3321  }
3322  }
3323 
3324  }
3325  }
3326  }
3327  }
3328 
3329  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
3330  const std::string &context ) const override {
3331  const int c = chance.get();
3332 
3333  // 100% chance = always generate, otherwise scale by item spawn rate.
3334  // (except is capped at 1)
3335  const float spawn_rate = get_option<float>( "ITEM_SPAWNRATE" );
3336  if( !x_in_y( ( c == 100 ) ? 1 : c * spawn_rate / 100.0f, 1 ) ) {
3337  return;
3338  }
3339 
3340  dat.m.furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get() ),
3341  furn_str_id::NULL_ID() );
3342  if( item_spawner ) {
3343  item_spawner->apply( dat, x, y, z, context );
3344  }
3345  if( item_group_spawner ) {
3346  item_group_spawner->apply( dat, x, y, z, context );
3347  }
3348  furn_id chosen_furn = furniture.get( dat );
3349  dat.m.furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( x.get(), y.get(), dat.zlevel() + z.get() ), chosen_furn );
3350  }
3351  bool has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &p ) const override {
3352  return dat.m.veh_at( tripoint_bub_ms( p.x(), p.y(), dat.zlevel() + p.z() ) ).has_value();
3353  }
3354 };

3429  return mapgen_phase::removal;
3430  }
3431  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,

3433 
3434  const tripoint start( x.val, y.val, dat.zlevel() + z.get() );
3435  const tripoint end( x.valmax, y.valmax, dat.zlevel() + z.get() );
3436  const tripoint_range<tripoint> range = tripoint_range<tripoint>( start, end );
3437  for( const tripoint &p : range ) {

3439  const auto rit = std::find( vehicles_to_remove.begin(), vehicles_to_remove.end(),
3440  vp->vehicle().type );
3441  if( rit != vehicles_to_remove.end() ) {
3442  get_map().remove_vehicle_from_cache( &vp->vehicle(), start.z, end.z );
3443  dat.m.destroy_vehicle( &vp->vehicle() );
3444  }
3445  }
3446  }

3512 /**
3513  * Calls another mapgen call inside the current one.
3514  * Note: can't use regular overmap ids.
3515  * @param entries list of pairs [nested mapgen id, weight].
3516  */
3517 class jmapgen_nested : public jmapgen_piece
3518 {
3519  private:
3520  class neighbor_oter_check
3521  {
3522  private:
3523  std::unordered_map<direction, cata::flat_set<std::pair<std::string, ot_match_type>>> neighbors;
3524  public:
3525  explicit neighbor_oter_check( const JsonObject &jsi ) {
3526  for( direction dir : all_enum_values<direction>() ) {
3527  std::string location = io::enum_to_string( dir );
3528  cata::flat_set<std::pair<std::string, ot_match_type>> dir_neighbors;
3529  if( !jsi.has_string( location ) ) {
3530  for( const JsonValue entry : jsi.get_array( location ) ) {
3531  std::pair<std::string, ot_match_type> dir_neighbor;
3532  if( entry.test_string() ) {
3533  dir_neighbor.first = entry.get_string();
3534  dir_neighbor.second = ot_match_type::contains;
3535  } else {
3536  JsonObject jo = entry.get_object();
3537  dir_neighbor.first = jo.get_string( "om_terrain" );
3538  dir_neighbor.second = jo.get_enum_value<ot_match_type>( "om_terrain_match_type",
3539  ot_match_type::contains );
3540  }
3541  dir_neighbors.insert( dir_neighbor );
3542  }
3543  } else {
3544  std::pair<std::string, ot_match_type> dir_neighbor;
3545  dir_neighbor.first = jsi.get_string( location );
3546  dir_neighbor.second = ot_match_type::contains;
3547  dir_neighbors.insert( dir_neighbor );
3548  }
3549  if( !dir_neighbors.empty() ) {
3550  neighbors[dir] = std::move( dir_neighbors );
3551  }
3552  }
3553  }
3554 
3555  bool test( const mapgendata &dat ) const {
3556  for( const std::pair<const direction, cata::flat_set<std::pair<std::string, ot_match_type>>> &p :
3557  neighbors ) {
3558  const direction dir = p.first;
3559  const cata::flat_set<std::pair<std::string, ot_match_type>> &allowed_neighbors = p.second;
3560 
3561  cata_assert( !allowed_neighbors.empty() );
3562 
3563  bool this_direction_matches = false;
3564  for( const std::pair<std::string, ot_match_type> &allowed_neighbor : allowed_neighbors ) {
3565  this_direction_matches |=
3566  is_ot_match( allowed_neighbor.first, dat.neighbor_at( dir ).id(),
3567  allowed_neighbor.second );
3568  }
3569  if( !this_direction_matches ) {
3570  return false;
3571  }
3572  }
3573  return true;
3574  }
3575  };

3719  class correct_z_level_check
3720  {
3721  private:
3722  std::unordered_set<int> required_z;
3723  public:
3724  explicit correct_z_level_check( const JsonArray &jarr ) {
3725  for( const JsonValue entry : jarr ) {
3726  required_z.emplace( entry.get_int() );
3727  }
3728  }
3729  bool test( const mapgendata &dat ) const {
3730  return required_z.empty() || required_z.count( dat.zlevel() ) == 1;
3731  }
3732  };
3733 
3734  public:
3735  weighted_int_list<mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id>> entries;
3736  weighted_int_list<mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id>> else_entries;
3737  neighbor_oter_check neighbor_oters;
3738  neighbor_join_check neighbor_joins;
3739  neighbor_flag_check neighbor_flags;
3740  neighbor_flag_any_check neighbor_flags_any;
3741  predecessor_oter_check predecessors;
3742  correct_z_level_check correct_z_level;
3743  jmapgen_nested( const JsonObject &jsi, const std::string_view/*context*/ )
3744  : neighbor_oters( jsi.get_object( "neighbors" ) )
3745  , neighbor_joins( jsi.get_object( "joins" ) )
3746  , neighbor_flags( jsi.get_object( "flags" ) )
3747  , neighbor_flags_any( jsi.get_object( "flags_any" ) )
3748  , predecessors( jsi.get_array( "predecessors" ) )
3749  , correct_z_level( jsi.get_array( "check_z" ) ) {
3750  if( jsi.has_member( "chunks" ) ) {
3751  load_weighted_list( jsi.get_member( "chunks" ), entries, 100 );
3752  }
3753  if( jsi.has_member( "else_chunks" ) ) {
3754  load_weighted_list( jsi.get_member( "else_chunks" ), else_entries, 100 );
3755  }
3756  }
3757  mapgen_phase phase() const override {
3758  return mapgen_phase::nested_mapgen;
3759  }
3760  void merge_parameters_into( mapgen_parameters &params,
3761  const std::string &outer_context ) const override {
3762  auto merge_from = [&]( const mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id> &val ) {
3763  for( const nested_mapgen_id &id : val.all_possible_results( params ) ) {
3764  if( id.is_null() ) {
3765  return;
3766  }
3767  const auto iter = nested_mapgens.find( id );
3768  if( iter == nested_mapgens.end() ) {
3769  debugmsg( "Unknown nested mapgen function id '%s'", id.str() );
3770  return;
3771  }
3772  using Obj = weighted_object<int, std::shared_ptr<mapgen_function_json_nested>>;
3773  for( const Obj &nested : iter->second.funcs() ) {
3774  nested.obj->merge_non_nest_parameters_into( params, outer_context );
3775  }
3776  }
3777  };
3778  for( const weighted_object<int, mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id>> &name : entries ) {
3779  merge_from( name.obj );
3780  }
3781  for( const weighted_object<int, mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id>> &name : else_entries ) {
3782  merge_from( name.obj );
3783  }
3784  }
3785  const weighted_int_list<mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id>> &get_entries(
3786  const mapgendata &dat ) const {
3787  if( neighbor_oters.test( dat ) && neighbor_joins.test( dat ) && neighbor_flags.test( dat ) &&
3788  neighbor_flags_any.test( dat ) && predecessors.test( dat ) && correct_z_level.test( dat ) ) {
3789  return entries;
3790  } else {
3791  return else_entries;
3792  }
3793  }
3794  void apply( const mapgendata &dat, const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z,
3795  const std::string &context ) const override {
3796  const mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id> *val = get_entries( dat ).pick();
3797  if( val == nullptr ) {
3798  return;
3799  }
3800 
3801  const nested_mapgen_id res = val->get( dat );
3802  if( res.is_empty() || res.is_null() ) {
3803  // This will be common when neighbors.test(...) is false, since else_entires is
3804  // often empty.
3805  return;
3806  }
3807  const auto iter = nested_mapgens.find( res );
3808  if( iter == nested_mapgens.end() ) {
3809  debugmsg( "Unknown nested mapgen function id %s", res.str() );
3810  return;
3811  }
3812 
3813  // A second roll? Let's allow it for now
3814  const auto &ptr = iter->second.funcs().pick();
3815  if( ptr == nullptr ) {
3816  return;
3817  }
3818 
3819  ( *ptr )->nest( dat, tripoint_rel_ms( x.get(), y.get(), z.get() ), context );
3820  }
3821  void check( const std::string &oter_name, const mapgen_parameters &parameters,
3822  const jmapgen_int &x, const jmapgen_int &y, const jmapgen_int &z
3823  ) const override {
3824  for( const weighted_object<int, mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id>> &p : entries ) {
3825  p.obj.check( oter_name, parameters );
3826  }
3827  for( const weighted_object<int, mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id>> &p : else_entries ) {
3828  p.obj.check( oter_name, parameters );
3829  }
3830  neighbor_joins.check( oter_name, parameters );
3831 
3832  // Check whether any of the nests can attempt to place stuff out of
3833  // bounds
3834  std::unordered_map<point, nested_mapgen_id> nest_placement_coords;
3835  auto add_coords_from = [&]( const mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id> &nest_id_val ) {
3836  for( const nested_mapgen_id &nest_id :
3837  nest_id_val.all_possible_results( parameters ) ) {
3838  if( nest_id.is_null() ) {
3839  continue;
3840  }
3841  for( const point &p : nest_id->all_placement_coords() ) {
3842  nest_placement_coords.emplace( p, nest_id );
3843  }
3844  }
3845  };
3846  for( const weighted_object<int, mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id>> &p : entries ) {
3847  add_coords_from( p.obj );
3848  }
3849  for( const weighted_object<int, mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id>> &p : else_entries ) {
3850  add_coords_from( p.obj );
3851  }
3852 
3853  point max_relative;
3854  nested_mapgen_id offending_nest_x;
3855  nested_mapgen_id offending_nest_y;
3856 
3857  for( const std::pair<const point, nested_mapgen_id> &p : nest_placement_coords ) {
3858  if( p.first.x > max_relative.x ) {
3859  max_relative.x = p.first.x;
3860  offending_nest_x = p.second;
3861  }
3862  if( p.first.y > max_relative.y ) {
3863  max_relative.y = p.first.y;
3864  offending_nest_y = p.second;
3865  }
3866  }
3867 
3868  static constexpr int omt_size = SEEX * 2;
3869  point max = point( x.valmax % omt_size, y.valmax % omt_size ) + max_relative;
3870 
3871  if( max.x >= omt_size ) {
3872  debugmsg( "nest %s within %s can place something at x = %d, which is in a "
3873  "different OMT from the smallest nest origin (%d, %d), and could lead to "
3874  "an out of bounds placement",
3875  offending_nest_x.str(), oter_name, x.valmax + max_relative.x, x.val,
3876  y.val );
3877  }
3878 
3879  if( max.y >= omt_size ) {
3880  debugmsg( "nest %s within %s can place something at y = %d, which is in a "
3881  "different OMT from the smallest nest origin (%d, %d), and could lead to "
3882  "an out of bounds placement",
3883  offending_nest_y.str(), oter_name, y.valmax + max_relative.y, x.val,
3884  y.val );
3885  }
3886  if( z.val != z.valmax ) {
3887  debugmsg( "nest %s within %s defines a range for Z level placement, which isn't"
3888  "permitted. Range: %d - %d.",
3889  offending_nest_x.str(), oter_name, z.val, z.valmax );
3890  }
3891  }
3892  bool has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &p ) const override {
3893  const weighted_int_list<mapgen_value<nested_mapgen_id>> &selected_entries =
3894  get_entries( dat );
3895  if( selected_entries.empty() ) {
3896  return false;
3897  }
3898 
3899  for( const auto &entry : selected_entries ) {
3900  nested_mapgen_id id = entry.obj.get( dat );
3901  if( id.is_null() ) {
3902  continue;
3903  }
3904  const auto iter = nested_mapgens.find( id );
3905  if( iter == nested_mapgens.end() ) {
3906  return false;
3907  }
3908  for( const auto &nest : iter->second.funcs() ) {
3909  if( nest.obj->has_vehicle_collision( dat, p ) ) {
3910  return true;
3911  }
3912  }
3913  }
3914 
3915  return false;
3916  }
3917 };

3937 template<typename PieceType>
3938 void jmapgen_objects::load_objects( const JsonArray &parray, const std::string_view context )
3939 {
3940  for( JsonObject jsi : parray ) {
3941  jmapgen_place where( jsi );
3942  where.offset( m_offset );
3943 
3944  if( check_bounds( where, jsi ) ) {
3945  add( where, make_shared_fast<PieceType>( jsi, context ) );
3946  } else {
3947  jsi.allow_omitted_members();
3948  }
3949  }
3950 }
3951 
3952 template<>
3953 void jmapgen_objects::load_objects<jmapgen_loot>(
3954  const JsonArray &parray, const std::string_view/*context*/ )
3955 {
3956  for( JsonObject jsi : parray ) {
3957  jmapgen_place where( jsi );
3958  where.offset( m_offset );
3959 
3960  if( !check_bounds( where, jsi ) ) {
3961  jsi.allow_omitted_members();
3962  continue;
3963  }
3964 
3965  auto loot = make_shared_fast<jmapgen_loot>( jsi );
3966  // spawn rates < 1 are handled in item_group
3967  const float rate = std::max( get_option<float>( "ITEM_SPAWNRATE" ), 1.0f );
3968 
3969  if( where.repeat.valmax != 1 ) {
3970  // if loot can repeat scale according to rate
3971  where.repeat.val = std::max( static_cast<int>( where.repeat.val * rate ), 1 );
3972  where.repeat.valmax = std::max( static_cast<int>( where.repeat.valmax * rate ), 1 );
3973 
3974  } else if( loot->chance != 100 ) {
3975  // otherwise except where chance is 100% scale probability
3976  loot->chance = std::max( std::min( static_cast<int>( loot->chance * rate ), 100 ), 1 );
3977  }
3978 
3979  add( where, loot );
3980  }
3981 }

3988  return;
3989  }
3990  load_objects<PieceType>( jsi.get_array( member_name ), member_name + " in " + context );
3991 }

3993 template<typename PieceType>
3994 void load_place_mapings( const JsonObject &jobj, mapgen_palette::placing_map::mapped_type &vect,
3995  const std::string &context )

3999 
4000 /*
4001 This is the default load function for mapgen pieces that only support loading from a json object,
4002 not from a simple string.
4003 Most non-trivial mapgen pieces (like item spawn which contains at least the item group and chance)
4004 are like this. Other pieces (trap, furniture ...) can be loaded from a single string and have
4005 an overload below.
4006 The mapgen piece is loaded from the member of the json object named key.
4007 */
4008 template<typename PieceType>
4009 void load_place_mapings( const JsonValue &value, mapgen_palette::placing_map::mapped_type &vect,
4010  const std::string &context )
4011 {
4012  if( value.test_object() ) {
4013  load_place_mapings<PieceType>( value.get_object(), vect, context );
4014  } else {
4015  for( JsonObject jo : value.get_array() ) {
4016  load_place_mapings<PieceType>( jo, vect, context );
4017  jo.allow_omitted_members();
4018  }
4019  }
4020 }
4021 
4022 /*
4023 This function allows loading the mapgen pieces from a single string, *or* a json object.
4024 */
4025 template<typename PieceType>
4026 void load_place_mapings_string(
4027  const JsonValue &value, mapgen_palette::placing_map::mapped_type &vect,
4028  const std::string &context )
4029 {
4030  if( value.test_string() || value.test_object() ) {
4031  try {
4032  vect.push_back( make_shared_fast<PieceType>( value ) );
4033  } catch( const std::runtime_error &err ) {
4034  // Using the json object here adds nice formatting and context information
4035  value.throw_error( err.what() );
4036  }
4037  } else {
4038  for( const JsonValue entry : value.get_array() ) {
4039  if( entry.test_string() ) {
4040  try {
4041  vect.push_back( make_shared_fast<PieceType>( entry ) );
4042  } catch( const std::runtime_error &err ) {
4043  // Using the json object here adds nice formatting and context information
4044  entry.throw_error( err.what() );
4045  }
4046  } else {
4047  load_place_mapings<PieceType>( entry.get_object(), vect, context );
4048  }
4049  }
4050  }
4051 }
4052 /*
4053 This function is like load_place_mapings_string, except if the input is an array it will create an
4054 instance of jmapgen_alternatively which will chose the mapgen piece to apply to the map randomly.
4055 Use this with terrain or traps or other things that can not be applied twice to the same place.
4056 */
4057 template<typename PieceType>
4058 void load_place_mapings_alternatively(
4059  const JsonValue &value, mapgen_palette::placing_map::mapped_type &vect,
4060  const std::string &context )
4061 {
4062  if( !value.test_array() ) {
4063  load_place_mapings_string<PieceType>( value, vect, context );
4064  } else {
4065  auto alter = make_shared_fast< jmapgen_alternatively<PieceType> >();
4066  for( const JsonValue entry : value.get_array() ) {
4067  if( entry.test_string() ) {
4068  try {
4069  alter->alternatives.emplace_back( entry );
4070  } catch( const std::runtime_error &err ) {
4071  // Using the json object here adds nice formatting and context information
4072  entry.throw_error( err.what() );
4073  }
4074  } else if( entry.test_object() ) {
4075  JsonObject jsi = entry.get_object();
4076  alter->alternatives.emplace_back( jsi, context );
4077  } else if( entry.test_array() ) {
4078  // If this is an array, it means it is an entry followed by a desired total count of instances.
4079  JsonArray piece_and_count_jarr = entry.get_array();
4080  if( piece_and_count_jarr.size() != 2 ) {
4081  piece_and_count_jarr.throw_error( "Array must have exactly two entries: the object, then the count." );
4082  }
4083 
4084  // Test if this is a string or object, and then just emplace it.
4085  if( piece_and_count_jarr.test_string() || piece_and_count_jarr.test_object() ) {
4086  try {
4087  alter->alternatives.emplace_back( piece_and_count_jarr.next_value() );
4088  } catch( const std::runtime_error &err ) {
4089  piece_and_count_jarr.throw_error( err.what() );
4090  }
4091  } else {
4092  piece_and_count_jarr.throw_error( "First entry must be a string or object." );
4093  }
4094 
4095  if( piece_and_count_jarr.test_int() ) {
4096  // We already emplaced the first instance, so do one less.
4097  int repeat = std::max( 0, piece_and_count_jarr.next_int() - 1 );
4098  PieceType piece_to_repeat = alter->alternatives.back();
4099  for( int i = 0; i < repeat; i++ ) {
4100  alter->alternatives.emplace_back( piece_to_repeat );
4101  }
4102  } else {
4103  piece_and_count_jarr.throw_error( "Second entry must be an integer." );
4104  }
4105  }
4106  }
4107  vect.push_back( alter );
4108  }
4109 }
4110 
4111 template<>
4112 void load_place_mapings<jmapgen_trap>(
4113  const JsonValue &value, mapgen_palette::placing_map::mapped_type &vect,
4114  const std::string &context )
4115 {
4116  load_place_mapings_alternatively<jmapgen_trap>( value, vect, context );
4117 }

4119 template<>
4120 void load_place_mapings<jmapgen_furniture>( const JsonValue &value,
4121  mapgen_palette::placing_map::mapped_type &vect, const std::string &context )
4122 {
4123  load_place_mapings_alternatively<jmapgen_furniture>( value, vect, context );
4124 }

4126 template<>

4133 template<typename PieceType>
4134 void mapgen_palette::load_place_mapings( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &member_name,
4135  placing_map &format_placings, const std::string &context )
4136 {
4137  if( jo.has_object( "mapping" ) ) {
4138  for( const JsonMember member : jo.get_object( "mapping" ) ) {
4139  const map_key key( member );
4140  JsonObject sub = member.get_object();
4141  sub.allow_omitted_members();
4142  if( !sub.has_member( member_name ) ) {
4143  continue;
4144  }
4145  auto &vect = format_placings[ key ];
4146  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(cata-translate-string-literal)
4147  std::string this_context = string_format( "%s in mapping in %s", member_name, context );
4148  ::load_place_mapings<PieceType>( sub.get_member( member_name ), vect, this_context );
4149  }
4150  }
4151  if( !jo.has_object( member_name ) ) {
4152  return;
4153  }
4154  for( const JsonMember member : jo.get_object( member_name ) ) {
4155  const map_key key( member );
4156  auto &vect = format_placings[ key ];
4157  std::string this_context =
4158  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(cata-translate-string-literal)
4159  string_format( "%s %s in %s", member_name, member.name(), context );
4160  ::load_place_mapings<PieceType>( member, vect, this_context );
4161  }
4162 }

4183 void mapgen_palette::check() const
4184 {
4185  std::string context = "palette " + id.str();
4186  jmapgen_int fake_coord( -1 );
4187  mapgen_parameters no_parameters;
4188  for( const std::pair<const std::string, mapgen_parameter> &param : parameters.map ) {
4189  std::string this_context = string_format( "parameter %s in %s", param.first, context );
4190  param.second.check( no_parameters, this_context );
4191  }
4192  for( const std::pair<const map_key, std::vector<shared_ptr_fast<const jmapgen_piece>>> &p :
4193  format_placings ) {
4194  for( const shared_ptr_fast<const jmapgen_piece> &j : p.second ) {
4195  j->check( context, parameters, fake_coord, fake_coord, fake_coord );
4196  }
4197  }
4198 }

4239 
4240 void mapgen_palette::add( const mapgen_value<std::string> &rh, const add_palette_context &context )
4241 {
4242  std::vector<std::string> possible_values =
4243  rh.all_possible_results( *context.current_parameters );
4244  if( possible_values.empty() ) {
4245  if( const std::string *param_name = rh.get_name_if_parameter() ) {
4246  debugmsg( "Parameter %s used for palette id in %s but has no possible values",
4247  *param_name, context.context );
4248  } else {
4249  debugmsg( "Mapgen value for used for palette id in %s has no possible values",
4250  context.context );
4251  }
4252  } else if( possible_values.size() == 1 ) {
4253  add( palette_id( possible_values.front() ), context );
4254  } else {
4255  std::string param_name;
4256  if( const std::string *name = rh.get_name_if_parameter() ) {
4257  param_name = *name;
4258  } else {
4259  const auto param_it =
4260  context.top_level_parameters->add_unique_parameter(
4261  "palette_choice_", rh, cata_variant_type::palette_id,
4262  mapgen_parameter_scope::overmap_special );
4263  param_name = param_it->first;
4264  }
4265  add_palette_context context_with_extra_constraint( context );
4266  for( const std::string &value : possible_values ) {
4267  palette_id val_id( value );
4268  context_with_extra_constraint.constraints.emplace_back( param_name, val_id );
4269  add( val_id, context_with_extra_constraint );
4270  context_with_extra_constraint.constraints.pop_back();
4271  }
4272  }
4273 }
4274 
4275 void mapgen_palette::add( const palette_id &rh, const add_palette_context &context )
4276 {
4277  add( get( rh ), context );
4278 }
4279 
4280 void mapgen_palette::add( const mapgen_palette &rh, const add_palette_context &context )
4281 {
4282  std::string actual_context = id.is_empty() ? context.context : "palette " + id.str();
4283 
4284  if( !rh.id.is_empty() ) {
4285  const std::vector<palette_id> &ancestors = context.ancestors;
4286  auto loop_start = std::find( ancestors.begin(), ancestors.end(), rh.id );
4287  if( loop_start != ancestors.end() ) {
4288  std::string loop_ids = enumerate_as_string( loop_start, ancestors.end(),
4289  []( const palette_id & i ) {
4290  return i.str();
4291  }, enumeration_conjunction::arrow );
4292  debugmsg( "loop in palette references: %s", loop_ids );
4293  return;
4294  }
4295  }
4296  add_palette_context new_context = context;
4297  new_context.ancestors.push_back( rh.id );
4298  new_context.current_parameters = &rh.parameters;
4299 
4300  for( const mapgen_value<std::string> &recursive_palette : rh.palettes_used ) {
4301  add( recursive_palette, new_context );
4302  }
4303  for( const auto &placing : rh.format_placings ) {
4304  const std::vector<mapgen_constraint<palette_id>> &constraints = context.constraints;
4305  std::vector<shared_ptr_fast<const jmapgen_piece>> constrained_placings = placing.second;
4306  if( !constraints.empty() ) {
4307  for( shared_ptr_fast<const jmapgen_piece> &piece : constrained_placings ) {
4308  piece = make_shared_fast<jmapgen_constrained<palette_id>>(
4309  std::move( piece ), constraints );
4310  }
4311  }
4312  std::vector<shared_ptr_fast<const jmapgen_piece>> &these_placings =
4313  format_placings[placing.first];
4314  these_placings.insert( these_placings.end(),
4315  constrained_placings.begin(), constrained_placings.end() );
4316  }
4317  for( const map_key &placing : rh.keys_with_terrain ) {
4318  keys_with_terrain.insert( placing );
4319  }
4320  parameters.check_and_merge( rh.parameters, actual_context );
4321 }
4322 
4323 mapgen_palette mapgen_palette::load_internal( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string_view,
4324  const std::string &context, bool require_id, bool allow_recur )
4325 {
4326  mapgen_palette new_pal;
4327  mapgen_palette::placing_map &format_placings = new_pal.format_placings;
4328  auto &keys_with_terrain = new_pal.keys_with_terrain;
4329  if( require_id ) {
4330  new_pal.id = palette_id( jo.get_string( "id" ) );
4331  }
4332 
4333  jo.read( "parameters", new_pal.parameters.map );
4334 
4335  if( jo.has_array( "palettes" ) ) {
4336  jo.read( "palettes", new_pal.palettes_used );
4337  if( allow_recur ) {
4338  // allow_recur means that it's safe to assume all the palettes have
4339  // been defined and we can inline now. Otherwise we just leave the
4340  // list in our palettes_used array and it will be consumed
4341  // recursively by calls to add which add this palette.
4342  add_palette_context add_context{ context, &new_pal.parameters };
4343  for( auto &p : new_pal.palettes_used ) {
4344  new_pal.add( p, add_context );
4345  }
4346  new_pal.palettes_used.clear();
4347  }
4348  }
4349 
4350  // mandatory: every character in rows must have matching entry, unless fill_ter is set
4351  // "terrain": { "a": "t_grass", "b": "t_lava" }. To help enforce this we
4352  // keep track of everything in the "terrain" object
4353  if( jo.has_member( "terrain" ) ) {
4354  for( const JsonMember member : jo.get_object( "terrain" ) ) {
4355  keys_with_terrain.insert( map_key( member ) );
4356  }
4357  }
4358 
4359  std::string c = "palette " + new_pal.id.str();
4360  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_terrain>( jo, "terrain", format_placings, c );
4361  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_furniture>( jo, "furniture", format_placings, c );
4362  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_field>( jo, "fields", format_placings, c );
4363  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_npc>( jo, "npcs", format_placings, c );
4364  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_sign>( jo, "signs", format_placings, c );
4365  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_vending_machine>( jo, "vendingmachines", format_placings, c );
4366  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_toilet>( jo, "toilets", format_placings, c );
4367  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_gaspump>( jo, "gaspumps", format_placings, c );
4368  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_item_group>( jo, "items", format_placings, c );
4369  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_monster_group>( jo, "monsters", format_placings, c );
4370  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_vehicle>( jo, "vehicles", format_placings, c );
4371  // json member name is not optimal, it should be plural like all the others above, but that conflicts
4372  // with the items entry which refers to item groups.
4373  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_spawn_item>( jo, "item", format_placings, c );
4374  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_remove_vehicles>( jo, "remove_vehicles", format_placings, c );
4375  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_remove_all>( jo, "remove_all", format_placings, c );
4376  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_trap>( jo, "traps", format_placings, c );
4377  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_monster>( jo, "monster", format_placings, c );
4378  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_make_rubble>( jo, "rubble", format_placings, c );
4379  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_computer>( jo, "computers", format_placings, c );
4380  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_sealed_item>( jo, "sealed_item", format_placings, c );
4381  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_nested>( jo, "nested", format_placings, c );
4382  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_liquid_item>( jo, "liquids", format_placings, c );
4383  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_corpse>( jo, "corpses", format_placings, c );
4384  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_graffiti>( jo, "graffiti", format_placings, c );
4385  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_zone>( jo, "zones", format_placings, c );
4386  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_ter_furn_transform>( jo, "ter_furn_transforms",
4387  format_placings, c );
4388  new_pal.load_place_mapings<jmapgen_faction>( jo, "faction_owner_character", format_placings, c );
4389 
4390  for( mapgen_palette::placing_map::value_type &p : format_placings ) {
4391  p.second.erase(
4392  std::remove_if(
4393  p.second.begin(), p.second.end(),
4394  []( const shared_ptr_fast<const jmapgen_piece> &placing ) {
4395  return placing->is_nop();
4396  } ), p.second.end() );
4397  }
4398  return new_pal;
4399 }

4401 mapgen_palette::add_palette_context::add_palette_context(
4402  const std::string &ctx, mapgen_parameters *params )
4403  : context( ctx )
4404  , top_level_parameters( params )
4405  , current_parameters( params )

4407 
4408 bool mapgen_function_json::setup_internal( const JsonObject &jo )
4409 {
4410  // Just to make sure no one does anything stupid
4411  if( jo.has_member( "mapgensize" ) ) {
4412  jo.throw_error( "\"mapgensize\" only allowed for nested mapgen" );
4413  }
4414 
4415  // something akin to mapgen fill_background.
4416  if( jo.has_string( "fill_ter" ) ) {
4417  fill_ter = ter_str_id( jo.get_string( "fill_ter" ) ).id();
4418  }
4419 
4420  if( jo.has_member( "rotation" ) ) {
4421  rotation = jmapgen_int( jo, "rotation" );
4422  }
4423 
4424  if( jo.has_member( "predecessor_mapgen" ) ) {
4425  predecessor_mapgen = oter_str_id( jo.get_string( "predecessor_mapgen" ) ).id();
4426  } else {
4427  predecessor_mapgen = oter_str_id::NULL_ID();
4428  }
4429 
4430  jo.read( "fallback_predecessor_mapgen", fallback_predecessor_mapgen_ );
4431 
4432  return fill_ter != t_null || predecessor_mapgen != oter_str_id::NULL_ID() ||
4433  fallback_predecessor_mapgen_ != oter_str_id::NULL_ID();
4434 }
4435 
4436 bool mapgen_function_json_nested::setup_internal( const JsonObject &jo )
4437 {
4438  // Mandatory - nested mapgen must be explicitly sized
4439  if( jo.has_array( "mapgensize" ) ) {
4440  JsonArray jarr = jo.get_array( "mapgensize" );
4441  mapgensize = point( jarr.get_int( 0 ), jarr.get_int( 1 ) );
4442  if( mapgensize.x == 0 || mapgensize.x != mapgensize.y ) {
4443  // Non-square sizes not implemented yet
4444  jo.throw_error( "\"mapgensize\" must be an array of two identical, positive numbers" );
4445  }
4446  total_size = mapgensize;
4447  } else {
4448  jo.throw_error( "Nested mapgen must have \"mapgensize\" set" );
4449  }
4450 
4451  if( jo.has_member( "rotation" ) ) {
4452  rotation = jmapgen_int( jo, "rotation" );
4453  }
4454 
4455  // Nested mapgen is always halal because it can assume underlying map is.
4456  return true;
4457 }

4489 struct phase_comparator {
4490  mapgen_phase get_phase( mapgen_phase p ) const {
4491  return p;
4492  }
4493 
4494  mapgen_phase get_phase( const jmapgen_setmap &s ) const {
4495  return s.phase();
4496  }
4497 
4498  template<typename PiecePtr>
4499  mapgen_phase get_phase( const std::pair<jmapgen_place, PiecePtr> &p ) const {
4500  return p.second->phase();
4501  }
4502 
4503  template<typename T, typename U>
4504  bool operator()( const T &l, const U &r ) const {
4505  return get_phase( l ) < get_phase( r );
4506  }
4507 };
4508 
4509 static const phase_comparator compare_phases{};
4510 
4511 /*
4512  * Parse json, pre-calculating values for stuff, then cheerfully throw json away. Faster than regular mapf, in theory
4513  */
4514 void mapgen_function_json_base::setup_common()
4515 {
4516  if( is_ready ) {
4517  return;
4518  }
4519  JsonObject jo = jsobj;
4520  mapgen_defer::defer = false;
4521  if( !setup_common( jo ) ) {
4522  jo.throw_error( "format: no terrain map" );
4523  }
4524  if( mapgen_defer::defer ) {
4525  mapgen_defer::jsi.throw_error_at( mapgen_defer::member, mapgen_defer::message );
4526  } else {
4527  mapgen_defer::jsi = JsonObject();
4528  }
4529 }
4530 
4531 bool mapgen_function_json_base::setup_common( const JsonObject &jo )
4532 {
4533  bool fallback_terrain_exists = setup_internal( jo );
4534  JsonArray parray;
4535  JsonArray sparray;
4536  JsonObject pjo;
4537 
4538  jo.read( "flags", flags_ );
4539 
4540  // mandatory: mapgensize rows of mapgensize character lines, each of which must have a
4541  // matching key in "terrain", unless fill_ter is set
4542  // "rows:" [ "aaaajustlikeinmapgen.cpp", "this.must!be!exactly.24!", "and_must_match_terrain_", .... ]
4543  point expected_dim = mapgensize + m_offset.xy().raw();
4544  cata_assert( expected_dim.x >= 0 );
4545  cata_assert( expected_dim.y >= 0 );
4546  const std::string default_row( expected_dim.x, ' ' );
4547  const bool default_rows = !jo.has_array( "rows" );
4548  if( !default_rows ) {
4549  parray = jo.get_array( "rows" );
4550  if( static_cast<int>( parray.size() ) < expected_dim.y ) {
4551  parray.throw_error( string_format( "format: rows: must have at least %d rows, not %d",
4552  expected_dim.y, parray.size() ) );
4553  }
4554  if( static_cast<int>( parray.size() ) != total_size.y ) {
4555  parray.throw_error(
4556  string_format( "format: rows: must have %d rows, not %d; check mapgensize if applicable",
4557  total_size.y, parray.size() ) );
4558  }
4559  }
4560 
4561  // just like mapf::basic_bind("stuff",blargle("foo", etc) ), only json input and faster when applying
4562  mapgen_palette palette = mapgen_palette::load_temp( jo, "dda", context_ );
4563  auto &keys_with_terrain = palette.keys_with_terrain;
4564  mapgen_palette::placing_map &format_placings = palette.format_placings;
4565 
4566  if( palette.keys_with_terrain.empty() && !fallback_terrain_exists ) {
4567  return false;
4568  }
4569 
4570  parameters = palette.get_parameters();
4571 
4572  for( int c = m_offset.y(); c < expected_dim.y; c++ ) {
4573  const std::string row = default_rows ? default_row : parray.get_string( c );
4574  static std::vector<std::string_view> row_keys;
4575  row_keys.clear();
4576  row_keys.reserve( total_size.x );
4577  utf8_display_split_into( row, row_keys );
4578  if( row_keys.size() < static_cast<size_t>( expected_dim.x ) ) {
4579  cata_assert( !default_rows );
4580  parray.throw_error(
4581  string_format( "format: row %d must have at least %d columns, not %d",
4582  c + 1, expected_dim.x, row_keys.size() ) );
4583  }
4584  if( row_keys.size() != static_cast<size_t>( total_size.x ) ) {
4585  cata_assert( !default_rows );
4586  parray.throw_error(
4587  string_format( "format: row %d must have %d columns, not %d; check mapgensize if applicable",
4588  c + 1, total_size.x, row_keys.size() ) );
4589  }
4590  for( int i = m_offset.x(); i < expected_dim.x; i++ ) {
4591  const tripoint_rel_ms p = tripoint_rel_ms( i, c, 0 ) - m_offset;
4592  const map_key key{ std::string( row_keys[i] ) };
4593  const auto iter_ter = keys_with_terrain.find( key );
4594  const auto fpi = format_placings.find( key );
4595 
4596  const bool has_terrain = iter_ter != keys_with_terrain.end();
4597  const bool has_placing = fpi != format_placings.end();
4598 
4599  if( !has_terrain && !fallback_terrain_exists ) {
4600  cata_assert( !default_rows );
4601  parray.string_error( c, i + 1,
4602  string_format( "format: rows: row %d column %d: '%s' is not in 'terrain',"
4603  "and no 'fill_ter', 'predecessor_mapgen' or 'fallback_predecessor_mapgen' is set!",
4604  c + 1, i + 1, key.str ) );
4605  }
4606  if( !has_terrain && !has_placing && key.str != " " && key.str != "." ) {
4607  try {
4608  cata_assert( !default_rows );
4609  parray.string_error( c, i + 1,
4610  string_format( "format: rows: row %d column %d: '%s' has no terrain, furniture, or other definition",
4611  c + 1, i + 1, key.str ) );
4612  } catch( const JsonError &e ) {
4613  debugmsg( "(json-error)\n%s", e.what() );
4614  }
4615  }
4616  if( has_placing ) {
4617  jmapgen_place where( p );
4618  for( auto &what : fpi->second ) {
4619  objects.add( where, what );
4620  }
4621  }
4622  }
4623  }
4624  fallback_terrain_exists = true;
4625 
4626  // No fill_ter? No format? GTFO.
4627  if( !fallback_terrain_exists ) {
4628  jo.throw_error(
4629  "Need one of 'fill_terrain', 'predecessor_mapgen', 'fallback_predecessor_mapgen', 'terrain' or a palette providing 'terrain'." );
4630  // TODO: write TFM.
4631  }
4632 
4633  if( jo.has_array( "set" ) ) {
4634  setup_setmap( jo.get_array( "set" ) );
4635  }
4636 
4637  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_remove_all>( jo, "place_remove_all", context_ );
4638  // "add" is deprecated in favor of "place_item", but kept to support mods
4639  // which are not under our control.
4640  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_spawn_item>( jo, "add", context_ );
4641  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_spawn_item>( jo, "place_item", context_ );
4642  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_field>( jo, "place_fields", context_ );
4643  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_npc>( jo, "place_npcs", context_ );
4644  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_sign>( jo, "place_signs", context_ );
4645  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_vending_machine>( jo, "place_vendingmachines", context_ );
4646  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_toilet>( jo, "place_toilets", context_ );
4647  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_liquid_item>( jo, "place_liquids", context_ );
4648  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_corpse>( jo, "place_corpses", context_ );
4649  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_gaspump>( jo, "place_gaspumps", context_ );
4650  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_item_group>( jo, "place_items", context_ );
4651  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_loot>( jo, "place_loot", context_ );
4652  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_monster_group>( jo, "place_monsters", context_ );
4653  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_vehicle>( jo, "place_vehicles", context_ );
4654  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_remove_vehicles>( jo, "remove_vehicles", context_ );
4655  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_remove_npcs>( jo, "remove_npcs", context_ );
4656  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_trap>( jo, "place_traps", context_ );
4657  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_furniture>( jo, "place_furniture", context_ );
4658  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_terrain>( jo, "place_terrain", context_ );
4659  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_monster>( jo, "place_monster", context_ );
4660  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_make_rubble>( jo, "place_rubble", context_ );
4661  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_computer>( jo, "place_computers", context_ );
4662  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_nested>( jo, "place_nested", context_ );
4663  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_graffiti>( jo, "place_graffiti", context_ );
4664  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_zone>( jo, "place_zones", context_ );
4665  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_ter_furn_transform>( jo, "place_ter_furn_transforms", context_ );
4666  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_variable>( jo, "place_variables", context_ );
4667  // Needs to be last as it affects other placed items
4668  objects.load_objects<jmapgen_faction>( jo, "faction_owner", context_ );
4669 
4670  objects.finalize();
4671 
4672  std::stable_sort( setmap_points.begin(), setmap_points.end(), compare_phases );
4673 
4674  if( !mapgen_defer::defer ) {
4675  is_ready = true; // skip setup attempts from any additional pointers
4676  }
4677  return true;
4678 }

4682  check_common();
4683 
4684  if( predecessor_mapgen != oter_str_id::NULL_ID() && expects_predecessor() ) {
4685  debugmsg( "%s uses both predecessor_mapgen and expects_predecessor; these features are "
4686  "incompatible", context_ );
4687  }
4688 }

4690 void mapgen_function_json::check_consistent_with( const oter_t &ter ) const

4693  if( expects_predecessor() && !requires_predecessor ) {
4694  debugmsg( "mapgen for oter_t %s expects a predecessor terrain but oter_type_t %s lacks the "
4695  "REQUIRES_PREDECESSOR flag", ter.id.str(), ter.get_type_id().str() );
4696  }

4704 static bool check_furn( const furn_id &id, const std::string &context )
4705 {
4706  const furn_t &furn = id.obj();
4707  if( furn.has_flag( ter_furn_flag::TFLAG_PLANT ) ) {
4708  debugmsg( "json mapgen for %s specifies furniture %s, which has flag "
4709  "PLANT. Such furniture must be specified in a \"sealed_item\" special.",
4710  context, furn.id.str() );
4711  // Only report once per mapgen object, otherwise the reports are
4712  // very repetitive
4713  return true;
4714  }
4715  return false;
4716 }
4717 
4718 void mapgen_function_json_base::check_common() const
4719 {
4720  if( static_cast <int>( flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_other_data ) ) +
4721  flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::dismantle_all_before_placing_terrain ) +
4722  flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::erase_all_before_placing_terrain ) > 1 ) {
4723  debugmsg( "In %s, the mutually exclusive flags ERASE_ALL_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN, "
4724  "DISMANTLE_ALL_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN and ALLOW_TERRAIN_UNDER_OTHER_DATA "
4725  "cannot be used together", context_ );
4726  }
4727  if( static_cast <int>( flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_furniture ) ) +
4728  flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::dismantle_furniture_before_placing_terrain ) +
4729  flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::erase_furniture_before_placing_terrain ) > 1 ) {
4730  debugmsg( "In %s, the mutually exclusive flags ALLOW_TERRAIN_UNDER_FURNITURE, "
4731  "DISMANTLE_FURNITURE_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN and ERASE_FURNITURE_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN "
4732  "cannot be used together", context_ );
4733  }
4734  if( static_cast <int>( flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_trap ) ) +
4735  flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::dismantle_trap_before_placing_terrain ) +
4736  flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::erase_trap_before_placing_terrain ) > 1 ) {
4737  debugmsg( "In %s, the mutually exclusive flags ALLOW_TERRAIN_UNDER_TRAP, "
4738  "DISMANTLE_TRAP_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN and ERASE_TRAP_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN "
4739  "cannot be used together", context_ );
4740  }
4741  if( static_cast <int>( flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::allow_terrain_under_items ) ) +
4742  flags_.test( jmapgen_flags::erase_items_before_placing_terrain ) > 1 ) {
4743  debugmsg( "In %s, the mutually exclusive flags "
4744  "ALLOW_TERRAIN_UNDER_ITEMS and ERASE_ITEMS_BEFORE_PLACING_TERRAIN "
4745  "cannot be used together", context_ );
4746  }
4747  for( const jmapgen_setmap &setmap : setmap_points ) {
4748  if( setmap.op != JMAPGEN_SETMAP_FURN &&
4749  setmap.op != JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_FURN &&
4750  setmap.op != JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_FURN ) {
4751  continue;
4752  }
4753  furn_id id( setmap.val.get() );
4754  if( check_furn( id, context_ ) ) {
4755  return;
4756  }
4757  }
4758 
4759  objects.check( context_, parameters );
4760 }
4761 
4762 void mapgen_function_json_base::add_placement_coords_to( std::unordered_set<point> &result ) const
4763 {
4764  objects.add_placement_coords_to( result );
4765 }

4779  objects.shrink_to_fit();
4780 }

4799 void jmapgen_objects::add_placement_coords_to( std::unordered_set<point> &result ) const
4800 {
4801  for( const jmapgen_obj &obj : objects ) {
4802  const jmapgen_place &where = obj.first;
4803  for( int x = where.x.val; x <= where.x.valmax; ++x ) {
4804  for( int y = where.y.val; y <= where.y.valmax; ++y ) {
4805  result.emplace( x, y );
4806  }
4807  }
4808  }
4809 }
