4811 /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4812 ///// 3 - mapgen (gameplay)
4813 ///// stuff below is the actual in-game map generation (ill)logic
4814 
4815 mapgen_phase jmapgen_setmap::phase() const
4816 {
4817  switch( op ) {
4818  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TER:
4819  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_TER:
4820  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_TER:
4821  return mapgen_phase::terrain;
4822  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_FURN:
4823  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_FURN:
4824  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_FURN:
4825  return mapgen_phase::furniture;
4826  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TRAP:
4827  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TRAP_REMOVE:
4828  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_CREATURE_REMOVE:
4829  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_ITEM_REMOVE:
4830  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_FIELD_REMOVE:
4831  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_TRAP:
4832  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_TRAP_REMOVE:
4833  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_CREATURE_REMOVE:
4834  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_ITEM_REMOVE:
4835  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_FIELD_REMOVE:
4836  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_TRAP:
4837  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_TRAP_REMOVE:
4838  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_CREATURE_REMOVE:
4839  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_ITEM_REMOVE:
4840  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_FIELD_REMOVE:
4841  return mapgen_phase::default_;
4842  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_RADIATION:
4843  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_BASH:
4844  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_VARIABLE:
4845  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_RADIATION:
4846  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_RADIATION:
4847  return mapgen_phase::transform;
4848  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_OPTYPE_POINT:
4849  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_OPTYPE_LINE:
4850  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_OPTYPE_SQUARE:
4851  break;
4852  }
4853  debugmsg( "Invalid jmapgen_setmap::op %d", static_cast<int>( op ) );
4854  return mapgen_phase::default_;
4855 }
4856 
4857 /*
4858  * (set|line|square)_(ter|furn|trap|radiation); simple (x, y, int) or (x1,y1,x2,y2, int) functions
4859  * TODO: optimize, though gcc -O2 optimizes enough that splitting the switch has no effect
4860  */
4861 bool jmapgen_setmap::apply( const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &offset ) const
4862 {
4863  if( chance != 1 && !one_in( chance ) ) {
4864  return true;
4865  }
4866 
4867  static const auto get = []( const jmapgen_int & v, int offset ) {
4868  return v.get() + offset;
4869  };
4870  const auto x_get = [this, &offset]() {
4871  return get( x, offset.x() );
4872  };
4873  const auto y_get = [this, &offset]() {
4874  return get( y, offset.y() );
4875  };
4876  const auto z_get = [this, &offset]() {
4877  return get( z, offset.z() );
4878  };
4879  const auto x2_get = [this, &offset]() {
4880  return get( x2, offset.x() );
4881  };
4882  const auto y2_get = [this, &offset]() {
4883  return get( y2, offset.y() );
4884  };
4885 
4886  map &m = dat.m;
4887  const int trepeat = repeat.get();
4888  const tripoint_bub_ms target_pos( x_get(), y_get(), dat.zlevel() + z_get() );
4889  const int z_level = dat.zlevel() + z_get();
4890 
4891  for( int i = 0; i < trepeat; i++ ) {
4892  switch( op ) {
4893  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TER: {
4894  // TODO: the ter_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
4895  m.ter_set( target_pos, ter_id( val.get() ),
4896  dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::avoid_creatures ) );
4897  }
4898  break;
4899  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_FURN: {
4900  // TODO: the furn_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
4901  m.furn_set( target_pos, furn_id( val.get() ),
4902  dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::avoid_creatures ) );
4903  }
4904  break;
4905  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TRAP: {
4906  // TODO: the trap_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
4907  mtrap_set( &m, target_pos, trap_id( val.get() ),
4908  dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::avoid_creatures ) );
4909  }
4910  break;
4911  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_RADIATION: {
4912  m.set_radiation( target_pos.raw(), val.get() );
4913  }
4914  break;
4915  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TRAP_REMOVE: {
4916  mremove_trap( &m, target_pos, trap_id( val.get() ).id() );
4917  }
4918  break;
4919  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_CREATURE_REMOVE: {
4920  Creature *tmp_critter = get_creature_tracker().creature_at( tripoint_abs_ms( m.getabs(
4921  target_pos ) ), true );
4922  if( tmp_critter && !tmp_critter->is_avatar() ) {
4923  tmp_critter->die( nullptr );
4924  }
4925  }
4926  break;
4927  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_ITEM_REMOVE: {
4928  m.i_clear( target_pos );
4929  }
4930  break;
4931  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_FIELD_REMOVE: {
4932  mremove_fields( &m, target_pos );
4933  }
4934  break;
4935  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_BASH: {
4936  m.bash( target_pos.raw(), 9999 );
4937  }
4938  break;
4939  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_VARIABLE: {
4940  queued_points[string_val] = m.getglobal( target_pos );
4941  }
4942  break;
4943  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_TER: {
4944  // TODO: the ter_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
4945  m.draw_line_ter( ter_id( val.get() ), point( x_get(), y_get() ), point( x2_get(), y2_get() ),
4946  z_level,
4947  dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::avoid_creatures ) );
4948  }
4949  break;
4950  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_FURN: {
4951  // TODO: the furn_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
4952  m.draw_line_furn( furn_id( val.get() ), point( x_get(), y_get() ), point( x2_get(), y2_get() ),
4953  z_level,
4954  dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::avoid_creatures ) );
4955  }
4956  break;
4957  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_TRAP: {
4958  const std::vector<point> line = line_to( point( x_get(), y_get() ), point( x2_get(), y2_get() ),
4959  0 );
4960  for( const point &i : line ) {
4961  // TODO: the trap_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
4962  mtrap_set( &m, tripoint_bub_ms( i.x, i.y, z_level ), trap_id( val.get() ),
4963  dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::avoid_creatures ) );
4964  }
4965  }
4966  break;
4967  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_TRAP_REMOVE: {
4968  const std::vector<point> line = line_to( point( x_get(), y_get() ), point( x2_get(), y2_get() ),
4969  0 );
4970  for( const point &i : line ) {
4971  // TODO: the trap_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
4972  mremove_trap( &m, tripoint_bub_ms( i.x, i.y, z_level ), trap_id( val.get() ).id() );
4973  }
4974  }
4975  break;
4976  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_CREATURE_REMOVE: {
4977  const std::vector<point> line = line_to( point( x_get(), y_get() ), point( x2_get(), y2_get() ),
4978  0 );
4979  for( const point &i : line ) {
4980  Creature *tmp_critter = get_creature_tracker().creature_at( tripoint_abs_ms( m.getabs( tripoint( i,
4981  z_level ) ) ), true );
4982  if( tmp_critter && !tmp_critter->is_avatar() ) {
4983  tmp_critter->die( nullptr );
4984  }
4985  }
4986  }
4987  break;
4988  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_ITEM_REMOVE: {
4989  const std::vector<point> line = line_to( point( x_get(), y_get() ), point( x2_get(), y2_get() ),
4990  0 );
4991  for( const point &i : line ) {
4992  m.i_clear( tripoint_bub_ms( i.x, i.y, z_level ) );
4993  }
4994  }
4995  break;
4996  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_FIELD_REMOVE: {
4997  const std::vector<point> line = line_to( point( x_get(), y_get() ), point( x2_get(), y2_get() ),
4998  0 );
4999  for( const point &i : line ) {
5000  mremove_fields( &m, tripoint_bub_ms( i.x, i.y, z_level ) );
5001  }
5002  }
5003  break;
5004  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_RADIATION: {
5005  const std::vector<point> line = line_to( point( x_get(), y_get() ), point( x2_get(), y2_get() ),
5006  0 );
5007  for( const point &i : line ) {
5008  m.set_radiation( tripoint( i, z_level ), static_cast<int>( val.get() ) );
5009  }
5010  }
5011  break;
5012  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_TER: {
5013  // TODO: the ter_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
5014  m.draw_square_ter( ter_id( val.get() ), point( x_get(), y_get() ), point( x2_get(), y2_get() ),
5015  z_level,
5016  dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::avoid_creatures ) );
5017  }
5018  break;
5019  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_FURN: {
5020  // TODO: the furn_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
5021  m.draw_square_furn( furn_id( val.get() ), point( x_get(), y_get() ), point( x2_get(), y2_get() ),
5022  z_level,
5023  dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::avoid_creatures ) );
5024  }
5025  break;
5026  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_TRAP: {
5027  const point c( x_get(), y_get() );
5028  const int cx2 = x2_get();
5029  const int cy2 = y2_get();
5030  for( int tx = c.x; tx <= cx2; tx++ ) {
5031  for( int ty = c.y; ty <= cy2; ty++ ) {
5032  // TODO: the trap_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
5033  mtrap_set( &m, tripoint_bub_ms( tx, ty, z_level ), trap_id( val.get() ),
5034  dat.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::avoid_creatures ) );
5035  }
5036  }
5037  }
5038  break;
5039  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_TRAP_REMOVE: {
5040  const point c( x_get(), y_get() );
5041  const int cx2 = x2_get();
5042  const int cy2 = y2_get();
5043  for( int tx = c.x; tx <= cx2; tx++ ) {
5044  for( int ty = c.y; ty <= cy2; ty++ ) {
5045  // TODO: the trap_id should be stored separately and not be wrapped in an jmapgen_int
5046  mremove_trap( &m, tripoint_bub_ms( tx, ty, z_level ), trap_id( val.get() ).id() );
5047  }
5048  }
5049  }
5050  break;
5051  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_CREATURE_REMOVE: {
5052  const point c( x_get(), y_get() );
5053  const int cx2 = x2_get();
5054  const int cy2 = y2_get();
5055  for( int tx = c.x; tx <= cx2; tx++ ) {
5056  for( int ty = c.y; ty <= cy2; ty++ ) {
5057  Creature *tmp_critter = get_creature_tracker().creature_at( tripoint_abs_ms( m.getabs( tripoint( tx,
5058  ty, z_level ) ) ), true );
5059  if( tmp_critter && !tmp_critter->is_avatar() ) {
5060  tmp_critter->die( nullptr );
5061  }
5062  }
5063  }
5064  }
5065  break;
5066  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_ITEM_REMOVE: {
5067  const point c( x_get(), y_get() );
5068  const int cx2 = x2_get();
5069  const int cy2 = y2_get();
5070  for( int tx = c.x; tx <= cx2; tx++ ) {
5071  for( int ty = c.y; ty <= cy2; ty++ ) {
5072  m.i_clear( tripoint_bub_ms( tx, ty, z_level ) );
5073  }
5074  }
5075  }
5076  break;
5077  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_FIELD_REMOVE: {
5078  const point c( x_get(), y_get() );
5079  const int cx2 = x2_get();
5080  const int cy2 = y2_get();
5081  for( int tx = c.x; tx <= cx2; tx++ ) {
5082  for( int ty = c.y; ty <= cy2; ty++ ) {
5083  mremove_fields( &m, tripoint_bub_ms( tx, ty, z_level ) );
5084  }
5085  }
5086  }
5087  break;
5088  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_RADIATION: {
5089  const point c2( x_get(), y_get() );
5090  const int cx2 = x2_get();
5091  const int cy2 = y2_get();
5092  for( int tx = c2.x; tx <= cx2; tx++ ) {
5093  for( int ty = c2.y; ty <= cy2; ty++ ) {
5094  m.set_radiation( tripoint( tx, ty, z_level ), static_cast<int>( val.get() ) );
5095  }
5096  }
5097  }
5098  break;
5099 
5100  default:
5101  //Suppress warnings
5102  break;
5103  }
5104  }
5105  return true;
5106 }
5107 
5108 bool jmapgen_setmap::has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat,
5109  const tripoint_rel_ms &offset ) const
5110 {
5111  static const auto get = []( const jmapgen_int & v, int v_offset ) {
5112  return v.get() + v_offset;
5113  };
5114  const auto x_get = [this, &offset]() {
5115  return get( x, offset.x() );
5116  };
5117  const auto y_get = [this, &offset]() {
5118  return get( y, offset.y() );
5119  };
5120  const auto z_get = [this, &offset]() {
5121  return get( z, offset.z() );
5122  };
5123  const auto x2_get = [this, &offset]() {
5124  return get( x2, offset.x() );
5125  };
5126  const auto y2_get = [this, &offset]() {
5127  return get( y2, offset.y() );
5128  };
5129  const tripoint_rel_ms start = tripoint_rel_ms( x_get(), y_get(), dat.zlevel() + z_get() );
5130  tripoint_rel_ms end = start;
5131  switch( op ) {
5132  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TER:
5133  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_FURN:
5134  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_TRAP:
5135  break;
5136  /* lines and squares are the same thing for this purpose */
5137  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_TER:
5138  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_FURN:
5139  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_TRAP:
5140  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_TRAP_REMOVE:
5141  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_LINE_ITEM_REMOVE:
5142  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_TER:
5143  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_FURN:
5144  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_TRAP:
5145  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_TRAP_REMOVE:
5146  case JMAPGEN_SETMAP_SQUARE_ITEM_REMOVE:
5147  end.x() = x2_get();
5148  end.y() = y2_get();
5149  break;
5150  /* if it's not a terrain, furniture, or trap, it can't collide */
5151  default:
5152  return false;
5153  }
5154  for( const tripoint &p : dat.m.points_in_rectangle( start.raw(), end.raw() ) ) {
5155  if( dat.m.veh_at( p ) ) {
5156  return true;
5157  }
5158  }
5159  return false;
5160 }
5161 
5162 bool mapgen_function_json_base::has_vehicle_collision(
5163  const mapgendata &dat, const tripoint_rel_ms &offset ) const
5164 {
5165  for( const jmapgen_setmap &elem : setmap_points ) {
5166  if( elem.has_vehicle_collision( dat, offset ) ) {
5167  return true;
5168  }
5169  }
5170 
5171  return objects.has_vehicle_collision( dat, offset );
5172 }
5173 
5174 static bool apply_mapgen_in_phases(
5175  const mapgendata &md, const std::vector<jmapgen_setmap> &setmap_points,
5176  const jmapgen_objects &objects, const tripoint_rel_ms &offset, const std::string &context,
5177  bool verify = false )
5178 {
5179  if( verify && objects.has_vehicle_collision( md, offset ) ) {
5180  return false;
5181  }
5182 
5183  // We must apply all the mapgen in phases, but the mapgen is split between
5184  // setmap_points and objects. So we have to make an outer loop over
5185  // phases, and apply each type restricted to each phase.
5186  auto setmap_point = setmap_points.begin();
5187  for( mapgen_phase phase : all_enum_values<mapgen_phase>() ) {
5188  if( std::find( md.skip.begin(), md.skip.end(), phase ) != md.skip.end() ) {
5189  continue;
5190  }
5191  for( ; setmap_point != setmap_points.end(); ++setmap_point ) {
5192  const jmapgen_setmap &elem = *setmap_point;
5193  if( elem.phase() != phase ) {
5194  break;
5195  }
5196  if( verify && elem.has_vehicle_collision( md, offset ) ) {
5197  return false;
5198  }
5199  elem.apply( md, offset );
5200  }
5201 
5202  objects.apply( md, phase, offset, context );
5203  }
5204  cata_assert( setmap_point == setmap_points.end() );
5205 
5206  resolve_regional_terrain_and_furniture( md );
5207 
5208  return true;
5209 }
5210 
5211 /*
5212  * Apply mapgen as per a derived-from-json recipe; in theory fast, but not very versatile
5213  */
5214 void mapgen_function_json::generate( mapgendata &md )
5215 {
5216  map *const m = &md.m;
5217  if( fill_ter != t_null ) {
5218  m->draw_fill_background( fill_ter );
5219  }
5220  const oter_t &ter = *md.terrain_type();
5221 
5222  auto do_predecessor_mapgen = [&]( mapgendata & predecessor_md ) {
5223  const std::string function_key = predecessor_md.terrain_type()->get_mapgen_id();
5224  bool success = run_mapgen_func( function_key, predecessor_md );
5225 
5226  if( !success ) {
5227  debugmsg( "predecessor mapgen with key %s failed", function_key );
5228  }
5229 
5230  // Now we have to do some rotation shenanigans. We need to ensure that
5231  // our predecessor is not rotated out of alignment as part of rotating this location,
5232  // and there are actually two sources of rotation--the mapgen can rotate explicitly, and
5233  // the entire overmap terrain may be rotatable. To ensure we end up in the right rotation,
5234  // we basically have to initially reverse the rotation that we WILL do in the future so that
5235  // when we apply that rotation, our predecessor is back in its original state while this
5236  // location is rotated as desired.
5237 
5238  m->rotate( ( -rotation.get() + 4 ) % 4 );
5239 
5240  if( ter.is_rotatable() || ter.is_linear() ) {
5241  m->rotate( ( -ter.get_rotation() + 4 ) % 4 );
5242  }
5243  };
5244 
5245  if( predecessor_mapgen != oter_str_id::NULL_ID() ) {
5246  mapgendata predecessor_md( md, predecessor_mapgen );
5247  do_predecessor_mapgen( predecessor_md );
5248  } else if( expects_predecessor() ) {
5249  if( md.has_predecessor() ) {
5250  mapgendata predecessor_md( md, md.last_predecessor() );
5251  predecessor_md.pop_last_predecessor();
5252  do_predecessor_mapgen( predecessor_md );
5253  } else {
5254  mapgendata predecessor_md( md, fallback_predecessor_mapgen_ );
5255  do_predecessor_mapgen( predecessor_md );
5256  }
5257  }
5258 
5259  mapgendata md_with_params( md, get_args( md, mapgen_parameter_scope::omt ), flags_ );
5260 
5261  apply_mapgen_in_phases( md_with_params, setmap_points, objects, tripoint_rel_ms( tripoint_zero ),
5262  context_ );
5263 
5264  m->rotate( rotation.get() );
5265 
5266  if( ter.is_rotatable() || ter.is_linear() ) {
5267  m->rotate( ter.get_rotation() );
5268  }
5269  set_queued_points();
5270 }
5271 
5272 bool mapgen_function_json::expects_predecessor() const
5273 {
5274  return fallback_predecessor_mapgen_ != oter_str_id::NULL_ID();
5275 }
5276 
5277 mapgen_parameters mapgen_function_json::get_mapgen_params( mapgen_parameter_scope scope ) const
5278 {
5279  return parameters.params_for_scope( scope );
5280 }
5281 
5282 void mapgen_function_json_nested::nest( const mapgendata &md, const tripoint_rel_ms &offset,
5283  const std::string &outer_context ) const
5284 {
5285  // TODO: Make rotation work for submaps, then pass this value into elem & objects apply.
5286  //int chosen_rotation = rotation.get() % 4;
5287 
5288  mapgendata md_with_params( md, get_args( md, mapgen_parameter_scope::nest ), flags_ );
5289 
5290  std::string context = context_;
5291  context += " in ";
5292  context += outer_context;
5293  apply_mapgen_in_phases( md_with_params, setmap_points, objects, offset, context );
5294 }
5295 
5296 /*
5297  * Apply mapgen as per a derived-from-json recipe; in theory fast, but not very versatile
5298  */
5299 void jmapgen_objects::apply( const mapgendata &dat, mapgen_phase phase,
5300  const std::string &context ) const
5301 {
5302  apply( dat, phase, tripoint_rel_ms( tripoint_zero ), context );
5303 }
5304 
5305 void jmapgen_objects::apply( const mapgendata &dat, mapgen_phase phase,
5306  const tripoint_rel_ms &offset,
5307  const std::string &context ) const
5308 {
5309  bool terrain_resolved = false;
5310 
5311  auto range_at_phase = std::equal_range( objects.begin(), objects.end(), phase, compare_phases );
5312 
5313  for( auto it = range_at_phase.first; it != range_at_phase.second; ++it ) {
5314  const jmapgen_obj &obj = *it;
5315  jmapgen_place where = obj.first;
5316  where.offset( tripoint_rel_ms( -offset.raw() ) );
5317  const jmapgen_piece &what = *obj.second;
5318 
5319  cata_assert( what.phase() == phase );
5320 
5321  if( !terrain_resolved && typeid( what ) == typeid( jmapgen_vehicle ) ) {
5322  // In order to determine collisions between vehicles and local "terrain" the terrain has to be resolved
5323  // This code is based on two assumptions:
5324  // 1. The terrain part of a definition is always placed first.
5325  // 2. Only vehicles require the terrain to be resolved. The general solution is to use a virtual function.
5326  resolve_regional_terrain_and_furniture( dat );
5327  terrain_resolved = true;
5328  }
5329 
5330  // The user will only specify repeat once in JSON, but it may get loaded both
5331  // into the what and where in some cases--we just need the greater value of the two.
5332  const int repeat = std::max( where.repeat.get(), what.repeat.get() );
5333  for( int i = 0; i < repeat; i++ ) {
5334  what.apply( dat, where.x, where.y, where.z, context );
5335  }
5336  }
5337 }
5338 
5339 bool jmapgen_objects::has_vehicle_collision( const mapgendata &dat,
5340  const tripoint_rel_ms &offset ) const
5341 {
5342  for( const jmapgen_obj &obj : objects ) {
5343  jmapgen_place where = obj.first;
5344  where.offset( tripoint_rel_ms( - offset.raw() ) );
5345  const auto &what = *obj.second;
5346  if( what.has_vehicle_collision( dat, tripoint_rel_ms( where.x.get(), where.y.get(),
5347  where.z.get() ) ) ) {
5348  return true;
5349  }
5350  }
5351  return false;
5352 }
5353 
5354 /////////////
5355 void map::draw_map( mapgendata &dat )
5356 {
5357  const oter_id &terrain_type = dat.terrain_type();
5358  const std::string function_key = terrain_type->get_mapgen_id();
5359  bool found = true;
5360 
5361  const bool generated = run_mapgen_func( function_key, dat );
5362 
5363  if( !generated ) {
5364  if( is_ot_match( "slimepit", terrain_type, ot_match_type::prefix ) ||
5365  is_ot_match( "slime_pit", terrain_type, ot_match_type::prefix ) ) {
5366  draw_slimepit( dat );
5367  } else if( is_ot_match( "lab", terrain_type, ot_match_type::contains ) ) {
5368  draw_lab( dat );
5369  } else {
5370  found = false;
5371  }
5372  }
5373 
5374  if( !found ) {
5375  // not one of the hardcoded ones!
5376  // load from JSON???
5377  debugmsg( "Error: tried to generate map for omtype %s, \"%s\" (id_mapgen %s)",
5378  terrain_type.id().c_str(), terrain_type->get_name(), function_key.c_str() );
5379  fill_background( this, ter_t_floor );
5380  }
5381 
5382  resolve_regional_terrain_and_furniture( dat );
5383 }
5384 
5385 static const int SOUTH_EDGE = 2 * SEEY - 1;
5386 static const int EAST_EDGE = 2 * SEEX - 1;
5387 
5388 // NOLINTNEXTLINE(readability-function-size)
5389 void map::draw_lab( mapgendata &dat )
5390 {
5391  const oter_id &terrain_type = dat.terrain_type();
5392  // To distinguish between types of labs
5393  bool ice_lab = true;
5394  bool central_lab = false;
5395  bool tower_lab = false;
5396 
5397  point p2;
5398 
5399  int lw = 0;
5400  int rw = 0;
5401  int tw = 0;
5402  int bw = 0;
5403 
5404  if( terrain_type == oter_lab || terrain_type == oter_lab_stairs
5405  || terrain_type == oter_lab_core || terrain_type == oter_ants_lab
5406  || terrain_type == oter_ants_lab_stairs || terrain_type == oter_ice_lab
5407  || terrain_type == oter_ice_lab_stairs || terrain_type == oter_ice_lab_core
5408  || terrain_type == oter_central_lab || terrain_type == oter_central_lab_stairs
5409  || terrain_type == oter_central_lab_core || terrain_type == oter_tower_lab
5410  || terrain_type == oter_tower_lab_stairs ) {
5411 
5412  ice_lab = is_ot_match( "ice_lab", terrain_type, ot_match_type::prefix );
5413  central_lab = is_ot_match( "central_lab", terrain_type, ot_match_type::prefix );
5414  tower_lab = is_ot_match( "tower_lab", terrain_type, ot_match_type::prefix );
5415 
5416  if( ice_lab ) {
5417  units::temperature_delta temperature = units::from_fahrenheit_delta( -20 + 30 * dat.zlevel() );
5418  set_temperature_mod( p2, temperature );
5419  set_temperature_mod( p2 + point( SEEX, 0 ), temperature );
5420  set_temperature_mod( p2 + point( 0, SEEY ), temperature );
5421  set_temperature_mod( p2 + point( SEEX, SEEY ), temperature );
5422  }
5423 
5424  // Check for adjacent sewers; used below
5425  tw = 0;
5426  rw = 0;
5427  bw = 0;
5428  lw = 0;
5429  if( ( dat.north()->get_type_id() == oter_type_sewer ) &&
5430  connects_to( dat.north(), 2 ) ) {
5431  tw = SOUTH_EDGE + 1;
5432  }
5433  if( ( dat.east()->get_type_id() == oter_type_sewer ) &&
5434  connects_to( dat.east(), 3 ) ) {
5435  rw = EAST_EDGE + 1;
5436  }
5437  if( ( dat.south()->get_type_id() == oter_type_sewer ) &&
5438  connects_to( dat.south(), 0 ) ) {
5439  bw = SOUTH_EDGE + 1;
5440  }
5441  if( ( dat.west()->get_type_id() == oter_type_sewer ) &&
5442  connects_to( dat.west(), 1 ) ) {
5443  lw = EAST_EDGE + 1;
5444  }
5445  if( dat.zlevel() == 0 ) { // We're on ground level
5446  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX * 2; i++ ) {
5447  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY * 2; j++ ) {
5448  if( i <= 1 || i >= SEEX * 2 - 2 ||
5449  j <= 1 || j >= SEEY * 2 - 2 ||
5450  i == SEEX - 2 || i == SEEX + 1 ) {
5451  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_concrete_wall );
5452  } else {
5453  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_floor );
5454  }
5455  }
5456  }
5457  ter_set( point( SEEX - 1, 0 ), ter_t_door_metal_locked );
5458  ter_set( point( SEEX - 1, 1 ), ter_t_floor );
5459  ter_set( point( SEEX, 0 ), ter_t_door_metal_locked );
5460  ter_set( point( SEEX, 1 ), ter_t_floor );
5461  ter_set( point( SEEX - 2 + rng( 0, 1 ) * 3, 0 ), ter_t_card_science );
5462  ter_set( point( SEEX - 2, SEEY ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5463  ter_set( point( SEEX + 1, SEEY ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5464  ter_set( point( SEEX - 2, SEEY - 1 ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5465  ter_set( point( SEEX + 1, SEEY - 1 ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5466  ter_set( point( SEEX - 1, SEEY * 2 - 3 ), ter_t_stairs_down );
5467  ter_set( point( SEEX, SEEY * 2 - 3 ), ter_t_stairs_down );
5468  science_room( this, point( 2, 2 ), point( SEEX - 3, SEEY * 2 - 3 ), dat.zlevel(), 1 );
5469  science_room( this, point( SEEX + 2, 2 ), point( SEEX * 2 - 3, SEEY * 2 - 3 ), dat.zlevel(), 3 );
5470 
5471  place_spawns( GROUP_TURRET, 1, point_bub_ms( SEEX, 5 ), point_bub_ms( SEEX, 5 ), dat.zlevel(), 1,
5472  true );
5473 
5474  if( dat.east()->get_type_id() == oter_type_road ) {
5475  rotate( 1 );
5476  } else if( dat.south()->get_type_id() == oter_type_road ) {
5477  rotate( 2 );
5478  } else if( dat.west()->get_type_id() == oter_type_road ) {
5479  rotate( 3 );
5480  }
5481  } else if( tw != 0 || rw != 0 || lw != 0 || bw != 0 ) { // Sewers!
5482  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX * 2; i++ ) {
5483  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY * 2; j++ ) {
5484  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_thconc_floor );
5485  if( ( ( i < lw || i > EAST_EDGE - rw ) && j > SEEY - 3 && j < SEEY + 2 ) ||
5486  ( ( j < tw || j > SOUTH_EDGE - bw ) && i > SEEX - 3 && i < SEEX + 2 ) ) {
5487  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_sewage );
5488  }
5489  if( ( i == 0 && is_ot_match( "lab", dat.east(), ot_match_type::contains ) ) || i == EAST_EDGE ) {
5490  if( ter( point( i, j ) ) == ter_t_sewage ) {
5491  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_bars );
5492  } else if( j == SEEY - 1 || j == SEEY ) {
5493  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5494  } else {
5495  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_concrete_wall );
5496  }
5497  } else if( ( j == 0 && is_ot_match( "lab", dat.north(), ot_match_type::contains ) ) ||
5498  j == SOUTH_EDGE ) {
5499  if( ter( point( i, j ) ) == ter_t_sewage ) {
5500  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_bars );
5501  } else if( i == SEEX - 1 || i == SEEX ) {
5502  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5503  } else {
5504  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_concrete_wall );
5505  }
5506  }
5507  }
5508  }
5509  } else { // We're below ground, and no sewers
5510  // Set up the boundaries of walls (connect to adjacent lab squares)
5511  tw = ( is_ot_match( "lab", dat.north(), ot_match_type::contains ) &&
5512  !is_ot_match( "lab_subway", dat.north(), ot_match_type::contains ) ) ? 0 : 2;
5513  rw = ( is_ot_match( "lab", dat.east(), ot_match_type::contains ) &&
5514  !is_ot_match( "lab_subway", dat.east(), ot_match_type::contains ) ) ? 1 : 2;
5515  bw = ( is_ot_match( "lab", dat.south(), ot_match_type::contains ) &&
5516  !is_ot_match( "lab_subway", dat.south(), ot_match_type::contains ) ) ? 1 : 2;
5517  lw = ( is_ot_match( "lab", dat.west(), ot_match_type::contains ) &&
5518  !is_ot_match( "lab_subway", dat.west(), ot_match_type::contains ) ) ? 0 : 2;
5519 
5520  int boarders = 0;
5521  if( tw == 0 ) {
5522  boarders++;
5523  }
5524  if( rw == 1 ) {
5525  boarders++;
5526  }
5527  if( bw == 1 ) {
5528  boarders++;
5529  }
5530  if( lw == 0 ) {
5531  boarders++;
5532  }
5533 
5534  const auto maybe_insert_stairs = [this]( const oter_id & terrain, const ter_id & t_stair_type ) {
5535  if( is_ot_match( "stairs", terrain, ot_match_type::contains ) ) {
5536  const auto predicate = [this]( const tripoint & p ) {
5537  return ter( p ) == ter_t_thconc_floor && furn( p ) == furn_str_id::NULL_ID() &&
5538  tr_at( p ).is_null();
5539  };
5540  const auto range =
5541  points_in_rectangle( { 0, 0, abs_sub.z() },
5542  { SEEX * 2 - 2, SEEY * 2 - 2, abs_sub.z() } );
5543 
5544  if( const auto p = random_point( range, predicate ) ) {
5545  ter_set( *p, t_stair_type );
5546  }
5547  }
5548  };
5549 
5550  //A lab area with only one entrance
5551  if( boarders == 1 ) {
5552  // If you remove the usage of "lab_1side" here, remove it from mapgen_factory::get_usages above as well.
5553  if( oter_mapgen.generate( dat, "lab_1side" ) ) {
5554  if( tw == 2 ) {
5555  rotate( 2 );
5556  }
5557  if( rw == 2 ) {
5558  rotate( 1 );
5559  }
5560  if( lw == 2 ) {
5561  rotate( 3 );
5562  }
5563  } else {
5564  debugmsg( "Error: Tried to generate 1-sided lab but no lab_1side json exists." );
5565  }
5566  maybe_insert_stairs( dat.above(), ter_t_stairs_up );
5567  maybe_insert_stairs( terrain_type, ter_t_stairs_down );
5568  } else {
5569  const int hardcoded_4side_map_weight = 1500; // weight of all hardcoded maps.
5570  // If you remove the usage of "lab_4side" here, remove it from mapgen_factory::get_usages above as well.
5571  if( oter_mapgen.generate( dat, "lab_4side", hardcoded_4side_map_weight ) ) {
5572  // If the map template hasn't handled borders, handle them in code.
5573  // Rotated maps cannot handle borders and have to be caught in code.
5574  // We determine if a border isn't handled by checking the east-facing
5575  // border space where the door normally is -- it should be a wall or door.
5576  tripoint east_border( 23, 11, abs_sub.z() );
5577  if( !has_flag_ter( ter_furn_flag::TFLAG_WALL, east_border ) &&
5578  !has_flag_ter( ter_furn_flag::TFLAG_DOOR, east_border ) ) {
5579  // TODO: create a ter_reset function that does ter_set,
5580  // furn_set, and i_clear?
5581  ter_str_id lw_type = tower_lab ? ter_t_reinforced_glass : ter_t_concrete_wall;
5582  ter_str_id tw_type = tower_lab ? ter_t_reinforced_glass : ter_t_concrete_wall;
5583  ter_str_id rw_type = tower_lab && rw == 2 ? ter_t_reinforced_glass :
5584  ter_t_concrete_wall;
5585  ter_str_id bw_type = tower_lab && bw == 2 ? ter_t_reinforced_glass :
5586  ter_t_concrete_wall;
5587  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX * 2; i++ ) {
5588  ter_set( point( 23, i ), rw_type );
5589  furn_set( point( 23, i ), furn_str_id::NULL_ID() );
5590  i_clear( tripoint( 23, i, dat.zlevel() ) );
5591 
5592  ter_set( point( i, 23 ), bw_type );
5593  furn_set( point( i, 23 ), furn_str_id::NULL_ID() );
5594  i_clear( tripoint( i, 23, dat.zlevel() ) );
5595 
5596  if( lw == 2 ) {
5597  ter_set( point( 0, i ), lw_type );
5598  furn_set( point( 0, i ), furn_str_id::NULL_ID() );
5599  i_clear( tripoint( 0, i, dat.zlevel() ) );
5600  }
5601  if( tw == 2 ) {
5602  ter_set( point( i, 0 ), tw_type );
5603  furn_set( point( i, 0 ), furn_str_id::NULL_ID() );
5604  i_clear( tripoint( i, 0, dat.zlevel() ) );
5605  }
5606  }
5607  if( rw != 2 ) {
5608  ter_set( point( 23, 11 ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5609  ter_set( point( 23, 12 ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5610  }
5611  if( bw != 2 ) {
5612  ter_set( point( 11, 23 ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5613  ter_set( point( 12, 23 ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5614  }
5615  }
5616 
5617  maybe_insert_stairs( dat.above(), ter_t_stairs_up );
5618  maybe_insert_stairs( terrain_type, ter_t_stairs_down );
5619  } else { // then no json maps for lab_4side were found
5620  switch( rng( 1, 3 ) ) {
5621  case 1:
5622  // Cross shaped
5623  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX * 2; i++ ) {
5624  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY * 2; j++ ) {
5625  if( ( i < lw || i > EAST_EDGE - rw ) ||
5626  ( ( j < SEEY - 1 || j > SEEY ) &&
5627  ( i == SEEX - 2 || i == SEEX + 1 ) ) ||
5628  ( j < tw || j > SOUTH_EDGE - bw ) ||
5629  ( ( i < SEEX - 1 || i > SEEX ) &&
5630  ( j == SEEY - 2 || j == SEEY + 1 ) ) ) {
5631  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_concrete_wall );
5632  } else {
5633  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_thconc_floor );
5634  }
5635  }
5636  }
5637  if( is_ot_match( "stairs", dat.above(), ot_match_type::contains ) ) {
5638  ter_set( point( rng( SEEX - 1, SEEX ), rng( SEEY - 1, SEEY ) ),
5639  ter_t_stairs_up );
5640  }
5641  // Top left
5642  if( one_in( 2 ) ) {
5643  ter_set( point( SEEX - 2, static_cast<int>( SEEY / 2 ) ), ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
5644  science_room( this, point( lw, tw ), point( SEEX - 3, SEEY - 3 ), dat.zlevel(), 1 );
5645  } else {
5646  ter_set( point( SEEX / 2, SEEY - 2 ), ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
5647  science_room( this, point( lw, tw ), point( SEEX - 3, SEEY - 3 ), dat.zlevel(), 2 );
5648  }
5649  // Top right
5650  if( one_in( 2 ) ) {
5651  ter_set( point( SEEX + 1, static_cast<int>( SEEY / 2 ) ), ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
5652  science_room( this, point( SEEX + 2, tw ), point( EAST_EDGE - rw, SEEY - 3 ),
5653  dat.zlevel(), 3 );
5654  } else {
5655  ter_set( point( SEEX + static_cast<int>( SEEX / 2 ), SEEY - 2 ), ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
5656  science_room( this, point( SEEX + 2, tw ), point( EAST_EDGE - rw, SEEY - 3 ),
5657  dat.zlevel(), 2 );
5658  }
5659  // Bottom left
5660  if( one_in( 2 ) ) {
5661  ter_set( point( SEEX / 2, SEEY + 1 ), ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
5662  science_room( this, point( lw, SEEY + 2 ), point( SEEX - 3, SOUTH_EDGE - bw ),
5663  dat.zlevel(), 0 );
5664  } else {
5665  ter_set( point( SEEX - 2, SEEY + static_cast<int>( SEEY / 2 ) ), ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
5666  science_room( this, point( lw, SEEY + 2 ), point( SEEX - 3, SOUTH_EDGE - bw ),
5667  dat.zlevel(), 1 );
5668  }
5669  // Bottom right
5670  if( one_in( 2 ) ) {
5671  ter_set( point( SEEX + static_cast<int>( SEEX / 2 ), SEEY + 1 ), ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
5672  science_room( this, point( SEEX + 2, SEEY + 2 ), point( EAST_EDGE - rw, SOUTH_EDGE - bw ),
5673  dat.zlevel(), 0 );
5674  } else {
5675  ter_set( point( SEEX + 1, SEEY + static_cast<int>( SEEY / 2 ) ), ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
5676  science_room( this, point( SEEX + 2, SEEY + 2 ), point( EAST_EDGE - rw, SOUTH_EDGE - bw ),
5677  dat.zlevel(), 3 );
5678  }
5679  if( rw == 1 ) {
5680  ter_set( point( EAST_EDGE, SEEY - 1 ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5681  ter_set( point( EAST_EDGE, SEEY ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5682  }
5683  if( bw == 1 ) {
5684  ter_set( point( SEEX - 1, SOUTH_EDGE ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5685  ter_set( point( SEEX, SOUTH_EDGE ), ter_t_door_metal_c );
5686  }
5687  if( is_ot_match( "stairs", terrain_type, ot_match_type::contains ) ) { // Stairs going down
5688  std::vector<point> stair_points;
5689  if( tw != 0 ) {
5690  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX - 1, 2 );
5691  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX - 1, 2 );
5692  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX, 2 );
5693  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX, 2 );
5694  }
5695  if( rw != 1 ) {
5696  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX * 2 - 3, SEEY - 1 );
5697  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX * 2 - 3, SEEY - 1 );
5698  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX * 2 - 3, SEEY );
5699  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX * 2 - 3, SEEY );
5700  }
5701  if( bw != 1 ) {
5702  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX - 1, SEEY * 2 - 3 );
5703  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX - 1, SEEY * 2 - 3 );
5704  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX, SEEY * 2 - 3 );
5705  stair_points.emplace_back( SEEX, SEEY * 2 - 3 );
5706  }
5707  if( lw != 0 ) {
5708  stair_points.emplace_back( 2, SEEY - 1 );
5709  stair_points.emplace_back( 2, SEEY - 1 );
5710  stair_points.emplace_back( 2, SEEY );
5711  stair_points.emplace_back( 2, SEEY );
5712  }
5713  stair_points.emplace_back( static_cast<int>( SEEX / 2 ), SEEY );

6341  // Handle stairs in the unlikely case they are needed.
6342 
6343  const auto maybe_insert_stairs = [this]( const oter_id & terrain,
6344  const ter_str_id & t_stair_type ) {
6345  if( is_ot_match( "stairs", terrain, ot_match_type::contains ) ) {
6346  const auto predicate = [this]( const tripoint & p ) {
6347  return ter( p ) == ter_t_thconc_floor && furn( p ) == furn_str_id::NULL_ID() &&
6348  tr_at( p ).is_null();
6349  };
6350  const auto range = points_in_rectangle( { 0, 0, abs_sub.z() },
6351  { SEEX * 2 - 2, SEEY * 2 - 2, abs_sub.z() } );
6352  if( const auto p = random_point( range, predicate ) ) {
6353  ter_set( *p, t_stair_type );
6354  }
6355  }
6356  };
6357  maybe_insert_stairs( dat.above(), ter_t_stairs_up );
6358  maybe_insert_stairs( terrain_type, ter_t_stairs_down );
6359 
6360  int light_odds = 0;
6361  // central labs are always fully lit, other labs have half chance of some lights.
6362  if( central_lab ) {
6363  light_odds = 1;
6364  } else if( one_in( 2 ) ) {
6365  light_odds = std::pow( rng( 1, 12 ), 1.6 );
6366  }
6367  if( light_odds > 0 ) {
6368  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX * 2; i++ ) {
6369  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY * 2; j++ ) {
6370  if( !( ( i * j ) % 2 || ( i + j ) % 4 ) && one_in( light_odds ) ) {
6371  const ter_id &nearby_ter = ter( point( i, j ) );
6372  if( nearby_ter == ter_t_thconc_floor || nearby_ter == ter_t_strconc_floor ) {
6373  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_thconc_floor_olight );
6374  }
6375  }
6376  }
6377  }
6378  }
6379  }
6380 }

6382 void map::draw_slimepit( const mapgendata &dat )
6383 {
6384  const oter_id &terrain_type = dat.terrain_type();
6385  if( is_ot_match( "slimepit", terrain_type, ot_match_type::prefix ) ) {
6386  for( int i = 0; i < SEEX * 2; i++ ) {
6387  for( int j = 0; j < SEEY * 2; j++ ) {
6388  if( !one_in( 10 ) && ( j < dat.n_fac * SEEX ||
6389  i < dat.w_fac * SEEX ||
6390  j > SEEY * 2 - dat.s_fac * SEEY ||
6391  i > SEEX * 2 - dat.e_fac * SEEX ) ) {
6392  ter_set( point( i, j ), ( !one_in( 10 ) ? ter_t_slime : ter_t_rock_floor ) );
6393  } else if( rng( 0, SEEX ) > std::abs( i - SEEX ) && rng( 0, SEEY ) > std::abs( j - SEEY ) ) {
6394  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_slime );
6395  } else if( dat.zlevel() == 0 ) {
6396  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_dirt );
6397  } else {
6398  ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_rock_floor );
6399  }
6400  }
6401  }
6402  if( terrain_type == oter_slimepit_down ) {
6403  ter_set( point( rng( 3, SEEX * 2 - 4 ), rng( 3, SEEY * 2 - 4 ) ), ter_t_slope_down );
6404  }
6405  if( dat.above() == oter_slimepit_down ) {
6406  switch( rng( 1, 4 ) ) {
6407  case 1:
6408  ter_set( point( rng( 0, 2 ), rng( 0, 2 ) ), ter_t_slope_up );
6409  break;
6410  case 2:
6411  ter_set( point( rng( 0, 2 ), SEEY * 2 - rng( 1, 3 ) ), ter_t_slope_up );
6412  break;
6413  case 3:
6414  ter_set( point( SEEX * 2 - rng( 1, 3 ), rng( 0, 2 ) ), ter_t_slope_up );
6415  break;
6416  case 4:
6417  ter_set( point( SEEX * 2 - rng( 1, 3 ), SEEY * 2 - rng( 1, 3 ) ), ter_t_slope_up );
6418  }
6419  } else if( dat.above() == oter_slimepit_bottom ) {
6420  // Align the stairs
6421  ter_set( point( 7, 9 ), ter_t_slope_up );
6422  }
6423  place_spawns( GROUP_SLIME, 1, point_bub_ms( SEEX, SEEY ), point_bub_ms( SEEX, SEEY ), dat.zlevel(),
6424  0.15 );
6425  place_items( Item_spawn_data_sewer, 40, tripoint_zero, tripoint( EAST_EDGE, SOUTH_EDGE,
6426  dat.zlevel() ), true,
6427  calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
6428  }
6429 }
6430 
6431 void map::place_spawns( const mongroup_id &group, const int chance,
6432  const point_bub_ms &p1, const point_bub_ms &p2, const int z_level, const float density,
6433  const bool individual, const bool friendly, const std::optional<std::string> &name,
6434  const int mission_id )
6435 {
6436  if( !group.is_valid() ) {
6437  tripoint_abs_omt omt = project_to<coords::omt>( get_abs_sub() );
6438  omt.z() = z_level;
6439  const oter_id &oid = overmap_buffer.ter( omt );
6440  debugmsg( "place_spawns: invalid mongroup '%s', om_terrain = '%s' (%s)", group.c_str(),
6441  oid.id().c_str(), oid->get_mapgen_id().c_str() );
6442  return;
6443  }
6444 
6445  // Set chance to be 1 or less to guarantee spawn, else set higher than 1
6446  if( !one_in( chance ) ) {
6447  return;
6448  }
6449 
6450  float spawn_density = 1.0f;
6451  if( MonsterGroupManager::is_animal( group ) ) {
6452  spawn_density = get_option< float >( "SPAWN_ANIMAL_DENSITY" );
6453  } else {
6454  spawn_density = get_option< float >( "SPAWN_DENSITY" );
6455  }
6456 
6457  float multiplier = density * spawn_density;
6458  // Only spawn 1 creature if individual flag set, else scale by density
6459  float thenum = individual ? 1 : ( multiplier * rng_float( 10.0f, 50.0f ) );
6460  int num = roll_remainder( thenum );
6461 
6462  // GetResultFromGroup decrements num
6463  while( num > 0 ) {
6464  int tries = 10;
6465  point_bub_ms p;
6466 
6467  // Pick a spot for the spawn
6468  do {
6469  p = { rng( p1.x(), p2.x() ), rng( p1.y(), p2.y() ) };
6470  tries--;
6471  } while( impassable( p ) && tries > 0 );
6472 
6473  // Pick a monster type
6474  std::vector<MonsterGroupResult> spawn_details =
6475  MonsterGroupManager::GetResultFromGroup( group, &num );
6476  for( const MonsterGroupResult &mgr : spawn_details ) {
6477  add_spawn( mgr.name, mgr.pack_size, { p, abs_sub.z() },
6478  friendly, -1, mission_id, name, mgr.data );
6479  }
6480  }
6481 }

6504 void map::place_vending( const tripoint_bub_ms &p, const item_group_id &type, bool reinforced,
6505  bool lootable )
6506 {
6507  if( reinforced ) {
6508  furn_set( p, furn_f_vending_reinforced );
6509  place_items( type, 100, p, p, false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
6510  } else {
6511  // The chance to find a non-ransacked vending machine reduces greatly with every day after the Cataclysm,
6512  // unless it's hidden somewhere far away from everyone's eyes (e.g. deep in the lab)
6513  if( lootable &&
6514  !one_in( std::max( to_days<int>( calendar::turn - calendar::start_of_cataclysm ), 0 ) + 4 ) ) {
6515  furn_set( p, furn_f_vending_o );
6516  for( const tripoint &loc : points_in_radius( p.raw(), 1 ) ) {
6517  if( one_in( 4 ) ) {
6518  spawn_item( loc, "glass_shard", rng( 1, 25 ) );
6519  }
6520  }
6521  } else {
6522  furn_set( p, furn_f_vending_c );
6523  place_items( type, 100, p, p, false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
6524  }
6525  }
6526 }

6539 void map::apply_faction_ownership( const point &p1, const point &p2, const faction_id &id )
6540 {
6541  for( const tripoint &p : points_in_rectangle( tripoint( p1, abs_sub.z() ), tripoint( p2,
6542  abs_sub.z() ) ) ) {
6543  map_stack items = i_at( p.xy() );
6544  for( item &elem : items ) {
6545  elem.set_owner( id );
6546  }
6547  vehicle *source_veh = veh_pointer_or_null( veh_at( p ) );
6548  if( source_veh ) {
6549  if( !source_veh->has_owner() ) {
6550  source_veh->set_owner( id );
6551  }
6552  }
6553  }
6554 }
6555 
6556 // A chance of 100 indicates that items should always spawn,
6557 // the item group should be responsible for determining the amount of items.
6558 std::vector<item *> map::place_items(
6559  const item_group_id &group_id, const int chance, const tripoint &p1, const tripoint &p2,
6560  const bool ongrass, const time_point &turn, const int magazine, const int ammo,
6561  const std::string &faction )
6562 {
6563  std::vector<item *> res;
6564 
6565  if( chance > 100 || chance <= 0 ) {
6566  debugmsg( "map::place_items() called with an invalid chance (%d)", chance );
6567  return res;
6568  }
6569  if( !item_group::group_is_defined( group_id ) ) {
6570  const tripoint_abs_omt omt = project_to<coords::omt>( get_abs_sub() );
6571  const oter_id &oid = overmap_buffer.ter( omt );
6572  debugmsg( "place_items: invalid item group '%s', om_terrain = '%s' (%s)",
6573  group_id.c_str(), oid.id().c_str(), oid->get_mapgen_id().c_str() );
6574  return res;
6575  }
6576 
6577  // spawn rates < 1 are handled in item_group
6578  const float spawn_rate = std::max( get_option<float>( "ITEM_SPAWNRATE" ), 1.0f ) ;
6579  const int spawn_count = roll_remainder( chance * spawn_rate / 100.0f );
6580  for( int i = 0; i < spawn_count; i++ ) {
6581  // Might contain one item or several that belong together like guns & their ammo
6582  int tries = 0;
6583  auto is_valid_terrain = [this, ongrass]( const tripoint & p ) {
6584  const ter_t &terrain = ter( p ).obj();
6585  return terrain.movecost == 0 &&
6586  !terrain.has_flag( ter_furn_flag::TFLAG_PLACE_ITEM ) &&
6587  !ongrass &&
6588  !terrain.has_flag( ter_furn_flag::TFLAG_FLAT );
6589  };
6590 
6591  tripoint p;
6592  do {
6593  p.x = rng( p1.x, p2.x );
6594  p.y = rng( p1.y, p2.y );
6595  p.z = rng( p1.z, p2.z );
6596  tries++;
6597  } while( is_valid_terrain( p ) && tries < 20 );
6598  if( tries < 20 ) {
6599  auto add_res_itm = [this, &p, &res]( const item & itm ) {
6600  item &it = add_item_or_charges( p, itm );
6601  if( !it.is_null() ) {
6602  res.push_back( &it );
6603  }
6604  };
6605 
6606  for( const item &itm : item_group::items_from( group_id, turn, spawn_flags::use_spawn_rate ) ) {
6607  const float item_cat_spawn_rate = std::max( 0.0f, item_category_spawn_rate( itm ) );
6608  if( item_cat_spawn_rate == 0.0f ) {
6609  continue;
6610  } else if( item_cat_spawn_rate < 1.0f ) {
6611  // for items with category spawn rate less than 1, roll a dice to see if they should spawn
6612  if( rng_float( 0.0f, 1.0f ) <= item_cat_spawn_rate ) {
6613  add_res_itm( itm );
6614  }
6615  } else {
6616  // for items with category spawn rate more or equal to 1, spawn item at least one time...
6617  add_res_itm( itm );
6618 
6619  if( item_cat_spawn_rate > 1.0f ) {
6620  // ...then create a list with items from the same item group and remove all items with differing category from that list
6621  // so if the original item was e.g. from 'guns' category, the list will contain only items from the 'guns' category...
6622  Item_list extra_spawn = item_group::items_from( group_id, turn, spawn_flags::use_spawn_rate );
6623  extra_spawn.erase( std::remove_if( extra_spawn.begin(), extra_spawn.end(), [&itm]( item & it ) {
6624  return it.get_category_of_contents() != itm.get_category_of_contents();
6625  } ), extra_spawn.end() );
6626 
6627  // ...then add a chance to spawn additional items from the list, amount is based on the item category spawn rate
6628  for( int i = 0; i < item_cat_spawn_rate; i++ ) {
6629  for( const item &it : extra_spawn ) {
6630  if( rng( 1, 100 ) <= chance ) {
6631  add_res_itm( it );
6632  }
6633  }
6634  }
6635  }
6636  }
6637  }
6638  }
6639  }
6640  for( item *e : res ) {
6641  if( e->is_tool() || e->is_gun() || e->is_magazine() ) {
6642  if( rng( 0, 99 ) < magazine && e->magazine_default() && !e->magazine_integral() &&
6643  !e->magazine_current() ) {
6644  e->put_in( item( e->magazine_default(), e->birthday() ), pocket_type::MAGAZINE_WELL );
6645  }
6646  if( rng( 0, 99 ) < ammo && e->ammo_default() && e->ammo_remaining() == 0 ) {
6647  e->ammo_set( e->ammo_default() );
6648  }
6649  }
6650 
6651  e->randomize_rot();
6652  e->set_owner( faction_id( faction ) );
6653  }
6654  return res;
6655 }

6659  const tripoint_bub_ms &p2, const bool ongrass, const time_point &turn, const int magazine,
6660  const int ammo, const std::string &faction )

6686 void map::add_spawn(
6687  const mtype_id &type, int count, const tripoint_bub_ms &p, bool friendly, int faction_id,
6688  int mission_id, const std::optional<std::string> &name, const spawn_data &data )
6689 {
6690  if( p.x() < 0 || p.x() >= SEEX * my_MAPSIZE || p.y() < 0 || p.y() >= SEEY * my_MAPSIZE ) {
6691  debugmsg( "Out of bounds add_spawn(%s, %d, %d, %d)", type.c_str(), count, p.x(), p.y() );
6692  return;
6693  }
6694  point offset;
6695  submap *place_on_submap = get_submap_at( p.raw(), offset );
6696  if( place_on_submap == nullptr ) {
6697  debugmsg( "Tried to add spawn at (%d,%d) but the submap is not loaded", offset.x, offset.y );
6698  return;
6699  }
6700 
6701  if( !place_on_submap ) {
6702  debugmsg( "centadodecamonant doesn't exist in grid; within add_spawn(%s, %d, %d, %d, %d)",
6703  type.c_str(), count, p.x(), p.y(), p.z() );
6704  return;
6705  }
6706  if( MonsterGroupManager::monster_is_blacklisted( type ) ) {
6707  return;
6708  }
6709  place_on_submap->spawns.emplace_back( type, count, offset, faction_id, mission_id, friendly, name,
6710  data );
6711 }

6713 vehicle *map::add_vehicle( const vproto_id &type, const tripoint &p, const units::angle &dir,
6714  const int veh_fuel, const int veh_status, const bool merge_wrecks )
6715 {
6716  if( !type.is_valid() ) {
6717  debugmsg( "Nonexistent vehicle type: \"%s\"", type.c_str() );
6718  return nullptr;
6719  }
6720  if( !inbounds( p ) ) {
6721  dbg( D_WARNING ) << string_format( "Out of bounds add_vehicle t=%s d=%d p=%d,%d,%d",
6722  type.str(), to_degrees( dir ), p.x, p.y, p.z );
6723  return nullptr;
6724  }
6725 
6726  std::unique_ptr<vehicle> veh = std::make_unique<vehicle>( type );
6727  tripoint p_ms = p;
6728  veh->sm_pos = ms_to_sm_remain( p_ms );
6729  veh->pos = p_ms.xy();
6730  veh->init_state( *this, veh_fuel, veh_status );
6731  veh->place_spawn_items();
6732  veh->face.init( dir );
6733  veh->turn_dir = dir;
6734  // for backwards compatibility, we always spawn with a pivot point of (0,0) so
6735  // that the mount at (0,0) is located at the spawn position.
6736  veh->precalc_mounts( 0, dir, point() );
6737 
6738  std::unique_ptr<vehicle> placed_vehicle_up =
6739  add_vehicle_to_map( std::move( veh ), merge_wrecks );
6740  vehicle *placed_vehicle = placed_vehicle_up.get();
6741 
6742  if( placed_vehicle != nullptr ) {
6743  submap *place_on_submap = get_submap_at_grid( placed_vehicle->sm_pos );
6744  if( place_on_submap == nullptr ) {
6745  debugmsg( "Tried to add vehicle at (%d,%d,%d) but the submap is not loaded",
6746  placed_vehicle->sm_pos.x, placed_vehicle->sm_pos.y, placed_vehicle->sm_pos.z );
6747  return placed_vehicle;
6748  }
6749  place_on_submap->ensure_nonuniform();
6750  place_on_submap->vehicles.push_back( std::move( placed_vehicle_up ) );
6751  invalidate_max_populated_zlev( p.z );
6752 
6753  level_cache &ch = get_cache( placed_vehicle->sm_pos.z );
6754  ch.vehicle_list.insert( placed_vehicle );
6755  add_vehicle_to_cache( placed_vehicle );
6756 
6757  rebuild_vehicle_level_caches();
6758  set_pathfinding_cache_dirty( p.z );
6759  placed_vehicle->place_zones( *this );
6760  }
6761  return placed_vehicle;
6762 }
6763 
6764 /**
6765  * Takes a vehicle already created with new and attempts to place it on the map,
6766  * checking for collisions. If the vehicle can't be placed, returns NULL,
6767  * otherwise returns a pointer to the placed vehicle, which may not necessarily
6768  * be the one passed in (if wreckage is created by fusing cars).
6769  * @param veh The vehicle to place on the map.
6770  * @param merge_wrecks Whether crashed vehicles intermix parts
6771  * @return The vehicle that was finally placed.
6772  */
6773 std::unique_ptr<vehicle> map::add_vehicle_to_map(
6774  std::unique_ptr<vehicle> veh_to_add, const bool merge_wrecks )
6775 {
6776  //We only want to check once per square, so loop over all structural parts
6777  std::vector<int> frame_indices = veh_to_add->all_parts_at_location( "structure" );
6778 
6779  //Check for boat type vehicles that should be placeable in deep water
6780  const bool can_float = size( veh_to_add->get_avail_parts( "FLOATS" ) ) > 2;
6781 
6782  //When hitting a wall, only smash the vehicle once (but walls many times)
6783  bool needs_smashing = false;
6784 
6785  for( std::vector<int>::const_iterator part = frame_indices.begin();
6786  part != frame_indices.end(); part++ ) {
6787  const tripoint p = veh_to_add->global_part_pos3( *part );
6788 
6789  if( veh_to_add->part( *part ).is_fake ) {
6790  continue;
6791  }
6792  //Don't spawn anything in water
6793  if( has_flag_ter( ter_furn_flag::TFLAG_DEEP_WATER, p ) && !can_float ) {
6794  return nullptr;
6795  }
6796 
6797  // Don't spawn shopping carts on top of another vehicle or other obstacle.
6798  if( veh_to_add->type == vehicle_prototype_shopping_cart ) {
6799  if( veh_at( p ) || impassable( p ) ) {
6800  return nullptr;
6801  }
6802  }
6803 
6804  //For other vehicles, simulate collisions with (non-shopping cart) stuff
6805  vehicle *const first_veh = veh_pointer_or_null( veh_at( p ) );
6806  if( first_veh != nullptr && first_veh->type != vehicle_prototype_shopping_cart ) {
6807  if( !merge_wrecks ) {
6808  return nullptr;
6809  }
6810 
6811  // Hard wreck-merging limit: 200 tiles
6812  // Merging is slow for big vehicles which lags the mapgen
6813  if( frame_indices.size() + first_veh->all_parts_at_location( "structure" ).size() > 200 ) {
6814  return nullptr;
6815  }
6816 
6817  /**
6818  * attempt to pull parts from `veh_to_add` (the prospective new vehicle)
6819  * in order to place them into `first_veh` (the vehicle that is overlapped)
6820  *
6821  * the intent here is to get something similar to the old wreckage behavior
6822  * (combining two vehicles) without completely garbling all of the vehicle parts
6823  * for tile rendering purposes.
6824  *
6825  * the overlap span is still a mess, though.
6826  */
6827  std::unique_ptr<RemovePartHandler> handler_ptr;
6828  bool did_merge = false;
6829  for( const tripoint &map_pos : first_veh->get_points( true ) ) {
6830  std::vector<vehicle_part *> parts_to_move = veh_to_add->get_parts_at( map_pos, "",
6831  part_status_flag::any );
6832  if( !parts_to_move.empty() ) {
6833  // Store target_point by value because first_veh->parts may reallocate
6834  // to a different address after install_part()
6835  std::vector<vehicle_part *> first_veh_parts = first_veh->get_parts_at( map_pos, "",
6836  part_status_flag:: any );
6837  // This happens if this location is occupied by a fake part.
6838  if( first_veh_parts.empty() || first_veh_parts.front()->is_fake ) {
6839  continue;
6840  }
6841  if( !inbounds( map_pos ) ) {
6842  debugmsg( "Existing vehicle %s (%s; origin %s; rot %g) and "
6843  "new vehicle %s (%s; origin %s; rot %g) "
6844  "out of map bounds at %s",
6845  first_veh->name, first_veh->type.str(),
6846  first_veh->global_square_location().to_string(),
6847  to_degrees( first_veh->turn_dir ),
6848  veh_to_add->name, veh_to_add->type.str(),
6849  veh_to_add->global_square_location().to_string(),
6850  to_degrees( veh_to_add->turn_dir ),
6851  map_pos.to_string() );
6852  }
6853  did_merge = true;
6854  const point target_point = first_veh_parts.front()->mount;
6855  const point source_point = parts_to_move.front()->mount;
6856  for( const vehicle_part *vp : parts_to_move ) {
6857  const vpart_info &vpi = vp->info();
6858  // TODO: change mount points to be tripoint
6859  const ret_val<void> valid_mount = first_veh->can_mount( target_point, vpi );
6860  if( valid_mount.success() ) {
6861  // make a copy so we don't interfere with veh_to_add->remove_part below
6862  first_veh->install_part( target_point, vehicle_part( *vp ) );
6863  }
6864  // ignore parts that would make invalid vehicle configuration
6865  }
6866 
6867  if( !handler_ptr ) {
6868  // This is a heuristic: we just assume the default handler is good enough when called
6869  // on the main game map. And assume that we run from some mapgen code if called on
6870  // another instance.
6871  if( !g || &get_map() != this ) {
6872  handler_ptr = std::make_unique<MapgenRemovePartHandler>( *this );
6873  }
6874  }
6875  // this could probably be done in a single loop with installing parts above
6876  std::vector<int> parts_in_square = veh_to_add->parts_at_relative( source_point, true );
6877  std::set<int> parts_to_check;
6878  for( int index = parts_in_square.size() - 1; index >= 0; index-- ) {
6879  vehicle_part &vp = veh_to_add->part( parts_in_square[index] );
6880  if( handler_ptr ) {
6881  veh_to_add->remove_part( vp, *handler_ptr );
6882  } else {
6883  veh_to_add->remove_part( vp );
6884  }
6885  parts_to_check.insert( parts_in_square[index] );
6886  }
6887  veh_to_add->find_and_split_vehicles( *this, parts_to_check );
6888  }
6889  }
6890 
6891  if( did_merge ) {
6892  // TODO: more targeted damage around the impact site
6893  first_veh->smash( *this );
6894  // TODO: entangle the old vehicle and the new vehicle somehow, perhaps with tow cables
6895  // or something like them, to make them harder to separate
6896  std::unique_ptr<vehicle> new_veh = add_vehicle_to_map( std::move( veh_to_add ), true );
6897  if( new_veh != nullptr ) {
6898  new_veh->smash( *this );
6899  return new_veh;
6900  }
6901  return nullptr;
6902  }
6903  } else if( impassable( p ) ) {
6904  if( !merge_wrecks ) {
6905  return nullptr;
6906  }
6907 
6908  // There's a wall or other obstacle here; destroy it
6909  destroy( p, true );
6910 
6911  // Some weird terrain, don't place the vehicle
6912  if( impassable( p ) ) {
6913  return nullptr;
6914  }
6915 
6916  needs_smashing = true;
6917  }
6918  }
6919 
6920  if( needs_smashing ) {
6921  veh_to_add->smash( *this );
6922  }
6923 
6924  veh_to_add->refresh();
6925  return veh_to_add;
6926 }

6928 computer *map::add_computer( const tripoint &p, const std::string &name, int security )

6936  static computer null_computer = computer( name, security, p );
6937  return &null_computer;
6938  }
6939  place_on_submap->set_computer( l, computer( name, security, p ) );
6940  return place_on_submap->get_computer( l );

6943 /**
6944  * Rotates this map, and all of its contents, by the specified multiple of 90
6945  * degrees.
6946  * @param turns How many 90-degree turns to rotate the map.
6947  */
6948 void map::rotate( int turns, const bool setpos_safe )
6949 {
6950 
6951  //Handle anything outside the 1-3 range gracefully; rotate(0) is a no-op.
6952  turns = turns % 4;
6953  if( turns == 0 ) {
6954  return;
6955  }
6956 
6957  real_coords rc;
6958  const tripoint_abs_sm &abs_sub = get_abs_sub();
6959  // TODO: fix point types
6960  rc.fromabs( project_to<coords::ms>( abs_sub.xy() ).raw() );
6961 
6962  // TODO: This radius can be smaller - how small?
6963  const int radius = HALF_MAPSIZE + 3;
6964  // uses submap coordinates
6965  const std::vector<shared_ptr_fast<npc>> npcs = overmap_buffer.get_npcs_near( abs_sub, radius );
6966  for( const shared_ptr_fast<npc> &i : npcs ) {
6967  npc &np = *i;
6968  const tripoint sq = np.get_location().raw();
6969  real_coords np_rc;
6970  np_rc.fromabs( sq.xy() );
6971  // Note: We are rotating the entire overmap square (2x2 of submaps)
6972  if( np_rc.om_pos != rc.om_pos || ( sq.z != abs_sub.z() && !zlevels ) ) {
6973  continue;
6974  }
6975 
6976  // OK, this is ugly: we remove the NPC from the whole map
6977  // Then we place it back from scratch
6978  // It could be rewritten to utilize the fact that rotation shouldn't cross overmaps
6979 
6980  point old( np_rc.sub_pos );
6981  if( np_rc.om_sub.x % 2 != 0 ) {
6982  old.x += SEEX;
6983  }
6984  if( np_rc.om_sub.y % 2 != 0 ) {
6985  old.y += SEEY;
6986  }
6987 
6988  const point new_pos = old.rotate( turns, { SEEX * 2, SEEY * 2 } );
6989  if( setpos_safe ) {
6990  const point local_sq = getlocal( sq ).xy();
6991  // setpos can't be used during mapgen, but spawn_at_precise clips position
6992  // to be between 0-11,0-11 and teleports NPCs when used inside of update_mapgen
6993  // calls
6994  const tripoint new_global_sq = sq - local_sq + new_pos;
6995  np.setpos( get_map().getlocal( new_global_sq ) );
6996  } else {
6997  // OK, this is ugly: we remove the NPC from the whole map
6998  // Then we place it back from scratch
6999  // It could be rewritten to utilize the fact that rotation shouldn't cross overmaps
7000  shared_ptr_fast<npc> npc_ptr = overmap_buffer.remove_npc( np.getID() );
7001  np.spawn_at_precise( tripoint_abs_ms( getabs( tripoint( new_pos, abs_sub.z() ) ) ) );
7002  overmap_buffer.insert_npc( npc_ptr );
7003  }
7004  }
7005 
7006  clear_vehicle_level_caches();
7007 
7008  // rotate zones
7009  zone_manager &mgr = zone_manager::get_manager();
7010  mgr.rotate_zones( *this, turns );
7011 
7012  const int bottom_level = zlevels ? -OVERMAP_DEPTH : abs_sub.z();
7013  const int top_level = zlevels ? OVERMAP_HEIGHT : abs_sub.z();
7014 
7015  for( int z_level = bottom_level; z_level <= top_level; z_level++ ) {
7016  clear_vehicle_list( z_level );
7017 
7018  submap *pz = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( point_zero, z_level ) );
7019  submap *pse = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( point_south_east, z_level ) );
7020  submap *pe = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( point_east, z_level ) );
7021  submap *ps = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( point_south, z_level ) );
7022  if( pz == nullptr || pse == nullptr || pe == nullptr || ps == nullptr ) {
7023  debugmsg( "Tried to rotate map at (%d,%d) but the submap is not loaded", point_zero.x,
7024  point_zero.y );
7025  return;
7026  }
7027 
7028  // Move the submaps around.
7029  if( turns == 2 ) {
7030  std::swap( *pz, *pse );
7031  std::swap( *pe, *ps );
7032  } else {
7033  point p;
7034  submap tmp;
7035 
7036  std::swap( *pse, tmp );
7037 
7038  for( int k = 0; k < 4; ++k ) {
7039  p = p.rotate( turns, { 2, 2 } );
7040  point tmpp = point_south_east - p;
7041  submap *psep = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( tmpp, z_level ) );
7042  if( psep == nullptr ) {
7043  debugmsg( "Tried to rotate map at (%d,%d) but the submap is not loaded", tmpp.x, tmpp.y );
7044  continue;
7045  }
7046  std::swap( *psep, tmp );
7047  }
7048  }
7049 
7050  // Then rotate them and recalculate vehicle positions.
7051  for( int j = 0; j < 2; ++j ) {
7052  for( int i = 0; i < 2; ++i ) {
7053  point p( i, j );
7054  submap *sm = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( p, z_level ) );
7055  if( sm == nullptr ) {
7056  debugmsg( "Tried to rotate map at (%d,%d) but the submap is not loaded", p.x, p.y );
7057  continue;
7058  }
7059 
7060  sm->rotate( turns );
7061 
7062  for( auto &veh : sm->vehicles ) {
7063  veh->sm_pos = tripoint( p, z_level );
7064  }
7065 
7066  update_vehicle_list( sm, z_level );
7067  }
7068  }
7069  rebuild_vehicle_level_caches();
7070 
7071  std::unordered_map<std::string, tripoint_abs_ms> temp_points = queued_points;
7072  queued_points.clear();
7073  for( std::pair<const std::string, tripoint_abs_ms> &queued_point : temp_points ) {
7074  //This is all just a copy of the section rotating NPCs above
7075  real_coords np_rc;
7076  np_rc.fromabs( queued_point.second.xy().raw() );
7077  // Note: We are rotating the entire overmap square (2x2 of submaps)
7078  if( np_rc.om_pos != rc.om_pos || ( queued_point.second.z() != abs_sub.z() && !zlevels ) ) {
7079  continue;
7080  }
7081  point old( np_rc.sub_pos );
7082  if( np_rc.om_sub.x % 2 != 0 ) {
7083  old.x += SEEX;
7084  }
7085  if( np_rc.om_sub.y % 2 != 0 ) {
7086  old.y += SEEY;
7087  }
7088  const point new_pos = old.rotate( turns, { SEEX * 2, SEEY * 2 } );
7089  queued_points[queued_point.first] = tripoint_abs_ms( getabs( tripoint( new_pos,
7090  z_level ) ) );
7091  }
7092  }
7093 }
7094 
7095 /**
7096  * Mirrors this map, and all of its contents along with all its contents in the
7097  * directions specified.
7098  */
7099 void map::mirror( bool mirror_horizontal, bool mirror_vertical )
7100 {
7101  if( !mirror_horizontal && !mirror_vertical ) {
7102  return;
7103  }
7104 
7105  real_coords rc;
7106  const tripoint_abs_sm &abs_sub = get_abs_sub();
7107  // TODO: fix point types
7108  rc.fromabs( project_to<coords::ms>( abs_sub.xy() ).raw() );
7109 
7110  for( int z_level = zlevels ? -OVERMAP_DEPTH : abs_sub.z();
7111  z_level <= ( zlevels ? OVERMAP_HEIGHT : abs_sub.z() ); z_level++ ) {
7112  submap *pz = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( point_zero, z_level ) );
7113  submap *pse = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( point_south_east, z_level ) );
7114  submap *pe = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( point_east, z_level ) );
7115  submap *ps = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( point_south, z_level ) );
7116  if( pz == nullptr || pse == nullptr || pe == nullptr || ps == nullptr ) {
7117  debugmsg( "Tried to mirror map at (%d, %d, %d) but the submap is not loaded", point_zero.x,
7118  point_zero.y, z_level );
7119  return;
7120  }
7121 
7122  // Move the submaps around. Note that the order doesn't matter as the outcome is the same.
7123  if( mirror_horizontal ) {
7124  std::swap( *pz, *pe );
7125  std::swap( *ps, *pse );
7126  }
7127  if( mirror_vertical ) {
7128  std::swap( *pz, *ps );
7129  std::swap( *pe, *pse );
7130  }
7131 
7132  // Then mirror them.
7133  for( int j = 0; j < 2; ++j ) {
7134  for( int i = 0; i < 2; ++i ) {
7135  point p( i, j );
7136  submap *sm = get_submap_at_grid( tripoint( p, z_level ) );
7137  if( sm == nullptr ) {
7138  debugmsg( "Tried to mirror map at (%d, %d, %d) but the submap is not loaded", p.x, p.y, z_level );
7139  continue;
7140  }
7141 
7142  if( mirror_horizontal ) {
7143  sm->mirror( true );
7144  }
7145  if( mirror_vertical ) {
7146  sm->mirror( false );
7147  }
7148  }
7149  }
7150  }
7151 }
7152 
7153 // Hideous function, I admit...
7154 bool connects_to( const oter_id &there, int dir )
7155 {
7156  switch( dir ) {
7157  // South
7158  case 2:
7159  if( there == oter_ants_ns || there == oter_ants_es ||
7160  there == oter_ants_sw || there == oter_ants_nes || there == oter_ants_nsw ||
7161  there == oter_ants_esw || there == oter_ants_nesw ) {
7162  return true;
7163  }
7164  return false;
7165  // West
7166  case 3:
7167  if( there == oter_ants_ew || there == oter_ants_sw ||
7168  there == oter_ants_wn || there == oter_ants_new || there == oter_ants_nsw ||
7169  there == oter_ants_esw || there == oter_ants_nesw ) {
7170  return true;
7171  }
7172  return false;
7173  // North
7174  case 0:
7175  if( there == oter_ants_ns || there == oter_ants_ne ||
7176  there == oter_ants_wn || there == oter_ants_nes || there == oter_ants_new ||
7177  there == oter_ants_nsw || there == oter_ants_nesw ) {
7178  return true;
7179  }
7180  return false;
7181  // East
7182  case 1:
7183  if( there == oter_ants_ew || there == oter_ants_ne ||
7184  there == oter_ants_es || there == oter_ants_nes || there == oter_ants_new ||
7185  there == oter_ants_esw || there == oter_ants_nesw ) {
7186  return true;
7187  }
7188  return false;
7189  default:
7190  debugmsg( "Connects_to with dir of %d", dir );
7191  return false;
7192  }
7193 }

7195 void science_room( map *m, const point &p1, const point &p2, int z, int rotate )
7196 {
7197  int height = p2.y - p1.y;
7198  int width = p2.x - p1.x;
7199  if( rotate % 2 == 1 ) { // Swap width & height if we're a lateral room
7200  int tmp = height;
7201  height = width;
7202  width = tmp;
7203  }
7204  for( int i = p1.x; i <= p2.x; i++ ) {
7205  for( int j = p1.y; j <= p2.y; j++ ) {
7206  m->ter_set( point( i, j ), ter_t_thconc_floor );
7207  }
7208  }
7209  int area = height * width;
7210  std::vector<room_type> valid_rooms;
7211  if( height < 5 && width < 5 ) {
7212  valid_rooms.push_back( room_closet );
7213  }
7214  if( height > 6 && width > 3 ) {
7215  valid_rooms.push_back( room_lobby );
7216  }
7217  if( height > 4 || width > 4 ) {
7218  valid_rooms.push_back( room_chemistry );
7219  valid_rooms.push_back( room_goo );
7220  }
7221  if( z != 0 && ( height > 7 || width > 7 ) && height > 2 && width > 2 ) {
7222  valid_rooms.push_back( room_teleport );
7223  }
7224  if( height > 7 && width > 7 ) {
7225  valid_rooms.push_back( room_bionics );
7226  valid_rooms.push_back( room_cloning );
7227  }
7228  if( area >= 9 ) {
7229  valid_rooms.push_back( room_vivisect );
7230  }
7231  if( height > 5 && width > 4 ) {
7232  valid_rooms.push_back( room_dorm );
7233  }
7234  if( width > 8 ) {
7235  for( int i = 8; i < width; i += rng( 1, 2 ) ) {
7236  valid_rooms.push_back( room_split );
7237  }
7238  }
7239 
7240  tripoint_bub_ms trap( rng( p1.x + 1, p2.x - 1 ), rng( p1.y + 1, p2.y - 1 ), z );
7241  switch( random_entry( valid_rooms ) ) {
7242  case room_closet:
7243  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_cleaning, 80, p1, p2, z, false,
7244  calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7245  break;
7246  case room_lobby:
7247  if( rotate % 2 == 0 ) { // Vertical
7248  int desk = p1.y + rng( static_cast<int>( height / 2 ) - static_cast<int>( height / 4 ),
7249  static_cast<int>( height / 2 ) + 1 );
7250  for( int x = p1.x + static_cast<int>( width / 4 ); x < p2.x - static_cast<int>( width / 4 ); x++ ) {
7251  m->furn_set( point( x, desk ), furn_f_counter );
7252  }
7253  computer *tmpcomp = m->add_computer( tripoint( p2.x - static_cast<int>( width / 4 ), desk, z ),
7254  _( "Log Console" ), 3 );
7255  tmpcomp->add_option( _( "View Research Logs" ), COMPACT_RESEARCH, 0 );
7256  tmpcomp->add_option( _( "Download Map Data" ), COMPACT_MAPS, 0 );
7257  tmpcomp->add_failure( COMPFAIL_SHUTDOWN );
7258  tmpcomp->add_failure( COMPFAIL_ALARM );
7259  tmpcomp->add_failure( COMPFAIL_DAMAGE );
7260  m->place_spawns( GROUP_LAB_SECURITY, 1,
7261  point_bub_ms( static_cast<int>( ( p1.x + p2.x ) / 2 ), desk ),
7262  point_bub_ms( static_cast<int>( ( p1.x + p2.x ) / 2 ), desk ), z, 1, true );
7263  } else {
7264  int desk = p1.x + rng( static_cast<int>( height / 2 ) - static_cast<int>( height / 4 ),
7265  static_cast<int>( height / 2 ) + 1 );
7266  for( int y = p1.y + static_cast<int>( width / 4 ); y < p2.y - static_cast<int>( width / 4 ); y++ ) {
7267  m->furn_set( point( desk, y ), furn_f_counter );
7268  }
7269  computer *tmpcomp = m->add_computer( tripoint( desk, p2.y - static_cast<int>( width / 4 ), z ),
7270  _( "Log Console" ), 3 );
7271  tmpcomp->add_option( _( "View Research Logs" ), COMPACT_RESEARCH, 0 );
7272  tmpcomp->add_option( _( "Download Map Data" ), COMPACT_MAPS, 0 );
7273  tmpcomp->add_failure( COMPFAIL_SHUTDOWN );
7274  tmpcomp->add_failure( COMPFAIL_ALARM );
7275  tmpcomp->add_failure( COMPFAIL_DAMAGE );
7276  m->place_spawns( GROUP_LAB_SECURITY, 1,
7277  point_bub_ms( desk, static_cast<int>( ( p1.y + p2.y ) / 2 ) ),
7278  point_bub_ms( desk, static_cast<int>( ( p1.y + p2.y ) / 2 ) ), z, 1, true );
7279  }
7280  break;
7281  case room_chemistry:
7282  if( rotate % 2 == 0 ) { // Vertical
7283  for( int x = p1.x; x <= p2.x; x++ ) {
7284  if( x % 3 == 0 ) {
7285  for( int y = p1.y + 1; y <= p2.y - 1; y++ ) {
7286  m->furn_set( point( x, y ), furn_f_counter );
7287  }
7288  if( one_in( 3 ) ) {

7290  point( x, p2.y - 1 ), z, false,
7291  calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7292  } else {
7293  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_chem_lab, 70, point( x, p1.y + 1 ),
7294  point( x, p2.y - 1 ), z, false,
7295  calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7296  }
7297  }
7298  }
7299  } else {
7300  for( int y = p1.y; y <= p2.y; y++ ) {
7301  if( y % 3 == 0 ) {
7302  for( int x = p1.x + 1; x <= p2.x - 1; x++ ) {
7303  m->furn_set( point( x, y ), furn_f_counter );
7304  }
7305  if( one_in( 3 ) ) {
7306  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_mut_lab, 35, point( p1.x + 1, y ),
7307  point( p2.x - 1, y ), z, false,
7308  calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7309  } else {
7310  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_chem_lab, 70, point( p1.x + 1, y ),
7311  point( p2.x - 1, y ), z, false,
7312  calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7313  }
7314  }
7315  }
7316  }
7317  break;
7318  case room_teleport:
7319  m->furn_set( point( ( p1.x + p2.x ) / 2, static_cast<int>( ( p1.y + p2.y ) / 2 ) ),
7320  furn_f_counter );

7322  static_cast<int>( ( p1.y + p2.y ) / 2 ) ),

7325  furn_f_counter );

7330  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_teleport, 70, point( ( p1.x + p2.x ) / 2,
7331  static_cast<int>( ( p1.y + p2.y ) / 2 ) ),
7332  point( static_cast<int>( ( p1.x + p2.x ) / 2 ) + 1, static_cast<int>( ( p1.y + p2.y ) / 2 ) + 1 ),
7333  z,
7334  false,

7336  break;
7337  case room_goo:
7338  do {
7339  mtrap_set( m, trap, tr_goo );
7340  trap.x() = rng( p1.x + 1, p2.x - 1 );
7341  trap.y() = rng( p1.y + 1, p2.y - 1 );

7343  if( rotate == 0 ) {

7347  false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7348  } else if( rotate == 1 ) {
7349  mremove_trap( m, tripoint_bub_ms( p1.x, p1.y, z ), tr_null );
7350  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( p1.x, p1.y, z ), furn_f_fridge );
7351  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_goo, 60, p1, p1, z, false,
7352  calendar::start_of_cataclysm );

7355  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( p2.x, p1.y, z ), furn_f_fridge );
7356  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_goo, 60, point( p2.x, p1.y ), point( p2.x, p1.y ), z,

7417  "-=-\n",
7418  mapf::ter_bind( "- | =", ter_t_concrete_wall, ter_t_concrete_wall, ter_t_reinforced_glass ),
