7461 
7462  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( biox + 2, bioy, z ), furn_f_console );
7463  computer *tmpcomp = m->add_computer( tripoint( biox + 2, bioy, z ), _( "Bionic access" ), 2 );
7464  tmpcomp->add_option( _( "Manifest" ), COMPACT_LIST_BIONICS, 0 );
7465  tmpcomp->add_option( _( "Open Chambers" ), COMPACT_RELEASE_BIONICS, 3 );
7466  tmpcomp->add_failure( COMPFAIL_MANHACKS );
7467  tmpcomp->add_failure( COMPFAIL_SECUBOTS );
7468  tmpcomp->set_access_denied_msg(
7469  _( "ERROR! Access denied! Unauthorized access will be met with lethal force!" ) );
7470 
7471  bioy = p2.y - 2;
7472  mapf::formatted_set_simple( m, point( biox - 1, bioy - 1 ),
7473  "|-|\n"
7474  "=c|\n"
7475  "|-|\n",
7476  mapf::ter_bind( "- | =", ter_t_concrete_wall, ter_t_concrete_wall, ter_t_reinforced_glass ),
7477  mapf::furn_bind( "c", furn_f_counter ) );
7478  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_bionics_common, 70, point( biox, bioy ),
7479  point( biox, bioy ), z, false, calendar::turn_zero );
7480 
7481  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( biox - 2, bioy, z ), furn_f_console );
7482  computer *tmpcomp2 = m->add_computer( tripoint( biox - 2, bioy, z ), _( "Bionic access" ), 2 );
7483  tmpcomp2->add_option( _( "Manifest" ), COMPACT_LIST_BIONICS, 0 );
7484  tmpcomp2->add_option( _( "Open Chambers" ), COMPACT_RELEASE_BIONICS, 3 );
7485  tmpcomp2->add_failure( COMPFAIL_MANHACKS );
7486  tmpcomp2->add_failure( COMPFAIL_SECUBOTS );
7487  tmpcomp2->set_access_denied_msg(
7488  _( "ERROR! Access denied! Unauthorized access will be met with lethal force!" ) );
7489  }
7490  break;
7491  case room_dorm:
7492  if( rotate % 2 == 0 ) {
7493  for( int y = p1.y + 1; y <= p2.y - 1; y += 3 ) {
7494  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( p1.x, y, z ), furn_f_bed );
7495  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_bed, 60, point( p1.x, y ), point( p1.x, y ), z,
7496  false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7497  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( p1.x + 1, y, z ), furn_f_bed );
7498  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_bed, 60, point( p1.x + 1, y ),
7499  point( p1.x + 1, y ), z, false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7500  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( p2.x, y, z ), furn_f_bed );
7501  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_bed, 60, point( p2.x, y ), point( p2.x, y ), z,
7502  false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7503  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( p2.x - 1, y, z ), furn_f_bed );
7504  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_bed, 60, point( p2.x - 1, y ),
7505  point( p2.x - 1, y ), z, false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7506  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( p1.x, y + 1, z ), furn_f_dresser );
7507  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( p2.x, y + 1, z ), furn_f_dresser );
7508  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_dresser, 70, point( p1.x, y + 1 ),
7509  point( p1.x, y + 1 ), z, false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7510  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_dresser, 70, point( p2.x, y + 1 ),
7511  point( p2.x, y + 1 ), z, false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7512  }
7513  } else if( rotate % 2 == 1 ) {
7514  for( int x = p1.x + 1; x <= p2.x - 1; x += 3 ) {
7515  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( x, p1.y, z ), furn_f_bed );
7516  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_bed, 60, point( x, p1.y ), point( x, p1.y ), z,
7517  false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7518  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( x, p1.y + 1, z ), furn_f_bed );
7519  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_bed, 60, point( x, p1.y + 1 ),
7520  point( x, p1.y + 1 ), z, false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7521  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( x, p2.y, z ), furn_f_bed );
7522  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_bed, 60, point( x, p2.y ), point( x, p2.y ), z,
7523  false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7524  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( x, p2.y - 1, z ), furn_f_bed );
7525  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_bed, 60, point( x, p2.y - 1 ),
7526  point( x, p2.y - 1 ), z, false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7527  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( x + 1, p1.y, z ), furn_f_dresser );
7528  m->furn_set( tripoint_bub_ms( x + 1, p2.y, z ), furn_f_dresser );
7529  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_dresser, 70, point( x + 1, p1.y ),
7530  point( x + 1, p1.y ), z, false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7531  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_dresser, 70, point( x + 1, p2.y ),
7532  point( x + 1, p2.y ), z, false, calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7533  }
7534  }
7535  m->place_items( Item_spawn_data_lab_dorm, 84, p1, p2, z, false,
7536  calendar::start_of_cataclysm );
7537  break;
7538  case room_split:
7539  if( rotate % 2 == 0 ) {
7540  int w1 = static_cast<int>( ( p1.x + p2.x ) / 2 ) - 2;
7541  int w2 = static_cast<int>( ( p1.x + p2.x ) / 2 ) + 2;
7542  for( int y = p1.y; y <= p2.y; y++ ) {
7543  m->ter_set( tripoint_bub_ms( w1, y, z ), ter_t_concrete_wall );
7544  m->ter_set( tripoint_bub_ms( w2, y, z ), ter_t_concrete_wall );
7545  }
7546  m->ter_set( tripoint_bub_ms( w1, static_cast<int>( ( p1.y + p2.y ) / 2 ), z ),
7547  ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
7548  m->ter_set( tripoint_bub_ms( w2, static_cast<int>( ( p1.y + p2.y ) / 2 ), z ),
7549  ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
7550  science_room( m, p1, point( w1 - 1, p2.y ), z, 1 );
7551  science_room( m, point( w2 + 1, p1.y ), p2, z, 3 );
7552  } else {
7553  int w1 = static_cast<int>( ( p1.y + p2.y ) / 2 ) - 2;
7554  int w2 = static_cast<int>( ( p1.y + p2.y ) / 2 ) + 2;
7555  for( int x = p1.x; x <= p2.x; x++ ) {
7556  m->ter_set( tripoint_bub_ms( x, w1, z ), ter_t_concrete_wall );
7557  m->ter_set( tripoint_bub_ms( x, w2, z ), ter_t_concrete_wall );
7558  }
7559  m->ter_set( tripoint_bub_ms( ( p1.x + p2.x ) / 2, w1, z ), ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
7560  m->ter_set( tripoint_bub_ms( ( p1.x + p2.x ) / 2, w2, z ), ter_t_door_glass_frosted_c );
7561  science_room( m, p1, point( p2.x, w1 - 1 ), z, 2 );
7562  science_room( m, point( p1.x, w2 + 1 ), p2, z, 0 );
7563  }
7564  break;
7565  default:
7566  break;
7567  }
7568 }
7569 
7570 void map::create_anomaly( const tripoint &cp, artifact_natural_property prop, bool create_rubble )
7571 {
7572  // TODO: Z
7573  const int z = cp.z;
7574  point c( cp.xy() );
7575  if( create_rubble ) {
7576  rough_circle( this, ter_t_dirt, c, 11 );
7577  rough_circle_furn( this, furn_f_rubble, c, 5 );
7578  furn_set( c, furn_str_id::NULL_ID() );
7579  }
7580  switch( prop ) {
7581  case ARTPROP_WRIGGLING:
7582  case ARTPROP_MOVING:
7583  for( int i = c.x - 5; i <= c.x + 5; i++ ) {
7584  for( int j = c.y - 5; j <= c.y + 5; j++ ) {
7585  if( furn( point( i, j ) ) == furn_f_rubble ) {
7586  add_field( tripoint_bub_ms{i, j, z}, fd_push_items, 1 );
7587  if( one_in( 3 ) ) {
7588  spawn_item( point( i, j ), "rock" );
7589  }
7590  }
7591  }
7592  }
7593  break;
7594 
7595  case ARTPROP_GLOWING:
7596  case ARTPROP_GLITTERING:
7597  for( int i = c.x - 5; i <= c.x + 5; i++ ) {
7598  for( int j = c.y - 5; j <= c.y + 5; j++ ) {
7599  if( furn( point( i, j ) ) == furn_f_rubble && one_in( 2 ) ) {
7600  mtrap_set( this, tripoint_bub_ms( i, j, z ), tr_glow );
7601  }
7602  }
7603  }
7604  break;
7605 
7606  case ARTPROP_HUMMING:
7607  case ARTPROP_RATTLING:
7608  for( int i = c.x - 5; i <= c.x + 5; i++ ) {
7609  for( int j = c.y - 5; j <= c.y + 5; j++ ) {
7610  if( furn( point( i, j ) ) == furn_f_rubble && one_in( 2 ) ) {
7611  mtrap_set( this, tripoint_bub_ms( i, j, z ), tr_hum );
7612  }
7613  }
7614  }
7615  break;
7616 
7617  case ARTPROP_WHISPERING:
7618  case ARTPROP_ENGRAVED:
7619  for( int i = c.x - 5; i <= c.x + 5; i++ ) {
7620  for( int j = c.y - 5; j <= c.y + 5; j++ ) {
7621  if( furn( point( i, j ) ) == furn_f_rubble && one_in( 3 ) ) {
7622  mtrap_set( this, tripoint_bub_ms( i, j, z ), tr_shadow );
7623  }
7624  }
7625  }
7626  break;
7627 
7628  case ARTPROP_BREATHING:
7629  for( int i = c.x - 1; i <= c.x + 1; i++ ) {
7630  for( int j = c.y - 1; j <= c.y + 1; j++ ) {
7631  if( i == c.x && j == c.y ) {
7632  place_spawns( GROUP_BREATHER_HUB, 1, point_bub_ms( i, j ), point_bub_ms( i, j ), z, 1,
7633  true );
7634  } else {
7635  place_spawns( GROUP_BREATHER, 1, point_bub_ms( i, j ), point_bub_ms( i, j ), z, 1, true );
7636  }
7637  }
7638  }
7639  break;
7640 
7641  case ARTPROP_DEAD:
7642  for( int i = c.x - 5; i <= c.x + 5; i++ ) {
7643  for( int j = c.y - 5; j <= c.y + 5; j++ ) {
7644  if( furn( point( i, j ) ) == furn_f_rubble ) {
7645  mtrap_set( this, tripoint_bub_ms( i, j, z ), tr_drain );
7646  }
7647  }
7648  }
7649  break;
7650 
7651  case ARTPROP_ITCHY:
7652  for( int i = c.x - 5; i <= c.x + 5; i++ ) {
7653  for( int j = c.y - 5; j <= c.y + 5; j++ ) {
7654  if( furn( point( i, j ) ) == furn_f_rubble ) {
7655  set_radiation( point( i, j ), rng( 0, 10 ) );
7656  }
7657  }
7658  }
7659  break;
7660 
7661  case ARTPROP_ELECTRIC:
7662  case ARTPROP_CRACKLING:
7663  add_field( {c, abs_sub.z()}, fd_shock_vent, 3 );
7664  break;
7665 
7666  case ARTPROP_SLIMY:
7667  add_field( {c, abs_sub.z()}, fd_acid_vent, 3 );
7668  break;
7669 
7670  case ARTPROP_WARM:
7671  for( int i = c.x - 5; i <= c.x + 5; i++ ) {
7672  for( int j = c.y - 5; j <= c.y + 5; j++ ) {
7673  if( furn( point( i, j ) ) == furn_f_rubble ) {
7674  add_field( tripoint_bub_ms{i, j, abs_sub.z()}, fd_fire_vent,
7675  1 + ( rl_dist( c, point( i, j ) ) % 3 ) );
7676  }
7677  }
7678  }
7679  break;
7680 
7681  case ARTPROP_SCALED:
7682  for( int i = c.x - 5; i <= c.x + 5; i++ ) {
7683  for( int j = c.y - 5; j <= c.y + 5; j++ ) {
7684  if( furn( point( i, j ) ) == furn_f_rubble ) {
7685  mtrap_set( this, tripoint_bub_ms( i, j, z ), tr_snake );
7686  }
7687  }
7688  }
7689  break;
7690 
7691  case ARTPROP_FRACTAL: {
7692  // Want to choose a random anomaly type which isn't fractal
7693  // (because nested fractal anomalies lead to out of bounds
7694  // placement). To be able to easily choose a random type excluding
7695  // fractal we want ARTPROP_FRACTAL to be the last type in the enum.
7696  // Verify that here with a static_assert.
7697  static_assert( ARTPROP_FRACTAL + 1 == ARTPROP_MAX,
7698  "ARTPROP_FRACTAL should be the last type in the list before "
7699  "ARTPROP_MAX" );
7700  auto random_type = []() {
7701  return static_cast<artifact_natural_property>(
7702  rng( ARTPROP_NULL + 1, ARTPROP_FRACTAL - 1 ) );
7703  };
7704  create_anomaly( c + point( -4, -4 ), random_type() );
7705  create_anomaly( c + point( 4, -4 ), random_type() );
7706  create_anomaly( c + point( -4, 4 ), random_type() );
7707  create_anomaly( c + point( 4, 4 ), random_type() );
7708  break;
7709  }
7710  default:
7711  break;
7712  }
7713 }
7714 void map::create_anomaly( const tripoint_bub_ms &cp, artifact_natural_property prop,
7715  bool create_rubble )
7716 {
7717  create_anomaly( cp.raw(), prop, create_rubble );
7718 }

7820 
7821 bool update_mapgen_function_json::update_map(
7822  const tripoint_abs_omt &omt_pos, const mapgen_arguments &args, const tripoint_rel_ms &offset,
7823  mission *miss, bool verify, bool mirror_horizontal, bool mirror_vertical, int rotation ) const
7824 {
7825  if( omt_pos == overmap::invalid_tripoint ) {
7826  debugmsg( "Mapgen update function called with overmap::invalid_tripoint" );
7827  return false;
7828  }
7829 
7830  std::unique_ptr<smallmap> p_update_smap = std::make_unique<smallmap>();
7831  smallmap &update_smap = *p_update_smap;
7832 
7833  update_smap.load( omt_pos, true );
7834  update_smap.rotate( 4 - rotation );
7835  update_smap.mirror( mirror_horizontal, mirror_vertical );
7836 
7837  mapgendata md_base( omt_pos, *update_smap.cast_to_map(), 0.0f, calendar::start_of_cataclysm, miss );
7838  mapgendata md( md_base, args );
7839 
7840  bool const u = update_map( md, offset, verify );
7841  update_smap.mirror( mirror_horizontal, mirror_vertical );
7842  update_smap.rotate( rotation );
7843 
7844  if( get_map().inbounds( project_to<coords::ms>( omt_pos ) ) ) {
7845  // trigger main map cleanup
7846  p_update_smap.reset();
7847  // trigger new traps, etc
7848  g->place_player( get_avatar().pos(), true );
7849  }
7850 
7851  // Trigger magic to add roofs (within load) if needed.
7852  if( omt_pos.z() < OVERMAP_HEIGHT ) {
7853  std::unique_ptr<smallmap> p_roof_smap = std::make_unique<smallmap>();
7854  smallmap &roof_smap = *p_roof_smap;
7855  // The loading of the Z level above is not necessary, but looks better.
7856  const tripoint_abs_omt omt_above = { omt_pos.x(), omt_pos.y(), omt_pos.z() + 1 };
7857  roof_smap.load( omt_above, false );
7858  }
7859 
7860  return u;
7861 }
7862 
7863 class rotation_guard
7864 {
7865  public:
7866  explicit rotation_guard( const mapgendata &md )
7867  : md( md ), rotation( oter_get_rotation( md.terrain_type() ) ) {
7868  // If the existing map is rotated, we need to rotate it back to the north
7869  // orientation before applying our updates.
7870  if( rotation != 0 && !md.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::no_underlying_rotate ) ) {
7871  md.m.rotate( rotation, true );
7872  }
7873  }
7874 
7875  ~rotation_guard() {
7876  // If we rotated the map before applying updates, we now need to rotate
7877  // it back to where we found it.
7878  if( rotation != 0 && !md.has_flag( jmapgen_flags::no_underlying_rotate ) ) {
7879  md.m.rotate( 4 - rotation, true );
7880  }
7881  }
7882  private:
7883  const mapgendata &md;
7884  const int rotation;
7885 };
7886 
7887 bool update_mapgen_function_json::update_map( const mapgendata &md, const tripoint_rel_ms &offset,
7888  const bool verify ) const
7889 {
7890  mapgendata md_with_params( md, get_args( md, mapgen_parameter_scope::omt ), flags_ );
7891 
7892  rotation_guard rot( md_with_params );
7893 
7894  return apply_mapgen_in_phases( md_with_params, setmap_points, objects, offset, context_,
7895  verify );
7896 }
7897 
7898 mapgen_update_func add_mapgen_update_func( const JsonObject &jo, bool &defer )
7899 {
7900  if( jo.has_string( "mapgen_update_id" ) ) {
7901  const update_mapgen_id mapgen_update_id{ jo.get_string( "mapgen_update_id" ) };
7902  const auto update_function = [mapgen_update_id]( const tripoint_abs_omt & omt_pos,
7903  mission * miss ) {
7904  run_mapgen_update_func( mapgen_update_id, omt_pos, {}, miss, false );
7905  };
7906  return update_function;
7907  }
7908 
7909  update_mapgen_function_json json_data( {},
7910  "unknown object in add_mapgen_update_func" );
7911  mapgen_defer::defer = defer;
7912  if( !json_data.setup_update( jo ) ) {
7913  const auto null_function = []( const tripoint_abs_omt &, mission * ) {
7914  };
7915  return null_function;
7916  }
7917  const auto update_function = [json_data]( const tripoint_abs_omt & omt_pos, mission * miss ) {
7918  json_data.update_map( omt_pos, {}, tripoint_rel_ms( tripoint_zero ), miss );
7919  };
7920  defer = mapgen_defer::defer;
7921  mapgen_defer::jsi = JsonObject();
7922  return update_function;
7923 }
7924 
7925 bool run_mapgen_update_func(
7926  const update_mapgen_id &update_mapgen_id, const tripoint_abs_omt &omt_pos,
7927  const mapgen_arguments &args, mission *miss, bool cancel_on_collision, bool mirror_horizontal,
7928  bool mirror_vertical, int rotation )
7929 {
7930  const auto update_function = update_mapgens.find( update_mapgen_id );
7931 
7932  if( update_function == update_mapgens.end() || update_function->second.funcs().empty() ) {
7933  return false;
7934  }
7935  return update_function->second.funcs()[0]->update_map(
7936  omt_pos, args, tripoint_rel_ms( tripoint_zero ), miss, cancel_on_collision, mirror_horizontal,
7937  mirror_vertical, rotation );
7938 }

7940 bool run_mapgen_update_func( const update_mapgen_id &update_mapgen_id, mapgendata &dat,
7941  const bool cancel_on_collision )

7943  const auto update_function = update_mapgens.find( update_mapgen_id );
7944  if( update_function == update_mapgens.end() || update_function->second.funcs().empty() ) {
7945  return false;
7946  }
7947  return update_function->second.funcs()[0]->update_map( dat, tripoint_rel_ms( tripoint_zero ),
7948  cancel_on_collision );
7949 }

7951 void set_queued_points()
7952 {
7953  global_variables &globvars = get_globals();
7954  for( std::pair<const std::string, tripoint_abs_ms> &queued_point : queued_points ) {
7955  globvars.set_global_value( "npctalk_var_" + queued_point.first, queued_point.second.to_string() );
7956  }

7959 
7960 bool apply_construction_marker( const update_mapgen_id &update_mapgen_id,
7961  const tripoint_abs_omt &omt_pos,
7962  const mapgen_arguments &args, bool mirror_horizontal,
7963  bool mirror_vertical, int rotation, bool apply )
7964 {
7965 
7966  const auto update_function = update_mapgens.find( update_mapgen_id );
7967 
7968  if( update_function == update_mapgens.end() || update_function->second.funcs().empty() ) {
7969  return false;
7970  }
7971 
7972  fake_map tmp_map( ter_t_grass );
7973 
7974  mapgendata base_fake_md( *tmp_map.cast_to_map(), mapgendata::dummy_settings );
7975  mapgendata fake_md( base_fake_md, args );
7976  fake_md.skip = { mapgen_phase::zones };
7977 
7978  std::unique_ptr<tinymap> p_update_tmap = std::make_unique<tinymap>();
7979  tinymap &update_tmap = *p_update_tmap;
7980 
7981  update_tmap.load( omt_pos, true );
7982  update_tmap.rotate( 4 - rotation );
7983  update_tmap.mirror( mirror_horizontal, mirror_vertical );
7984 
7985  {
7986  // Make sure rot goes out of scope and its destructor restores the map before the
7987  // "outer scope" mirroring/rotation is undone. It's unlikely inherent map rotation will
7988  // be present at the same time as construction rotation/mirroring is, but better safe than sorry.
7989 
7990  mapgendata md_base( omt_pos, *update_tmap.cast_to_map(), 0.0f, calendar::start_of_cataclysm,
7991  nullptr );
7992  mapgendata md( md_base, args );
7993 
7994  rotation_guard rot( md );
7995 
7996  if( update_function->second.funcs()[0]->update_map( fake_md ) ) {
7997  for( const tripoint &pos : tmp_map.points_on_zlevel( fake_map::fake_map_z ) ) {
7998  const tripoint level_pos = tripoint( pos.xy(), omt_pos.z() );
7999  if( tmp_map.ter( pos ) != ter_t_grass || tmp_map.has_furn( level_pos ) ) {
8000  if( apply ) {
8001  update_tmap.add_field( level_pos, fd_construction_site, 1, time_duration::from_turns( 0 ), false );
8002  } else {
8003  update_tmap.delete_field( level_pos, fd_construction_site );
8004  }
8005  }
8006  }
8007  }
8008  }
8009 
8010  update_tmap.mirror( mirror_horizontal, mirror_vertical );
8011  update_tmap.rotate( rotation );
8012 
8013  return true;
8014 }
8015 
8016 std::pair<std::map<ter_id, int>, std::map<furn_id, int>> get_changed_ids_from_update(
8017  const update_mapgen_id &update_mapgen_id,
8018  const mapgen_arguments &mapgen_args, ter_id const &base_ter )
8019 {
8020  std::map<ter_id, int> terrains;
8021  std::map<furn_id, int> furnitures;
8022 
8023  const auto update_function = update_mapgens.find( update_mapgen_id );
8024 
8025  if( update_function == update_mapgens.end() || update_function->second.funcs().empty() ) {
8026  return std::make_pair( terrains, furnitures );
8027  }
8028 
8029  fake_map tmp_map( base_ter );
8030 
8031  mapgendata base_fake_md( *tmp_map.cast_to_map(), mapgendata::dummy_settings );
8032  mapgendata fake_md( base_fake_md, mapgen_args );
8033  fake_md.skip = { mapgen_phase::zones };
8034 
8035  if( update_function->second.funcs()[0]->update_map( fake_md ) ) {
8036  for( const tripoint &pos : tmp_map.points_on_zlevel( fake_map::fake_map_z ) ) {
8037  ter_id ter_at_pos = tmp_map.ter( pos );
8038  if( ter_at_pos != base_ter ) {
8039  terrains[ter_at_pos] += 1;
8040  }
8041  if( tmp_map.has_furn( pos ) ) {
8042  furn_id furn_at_pos = tmp_map.furn( pos );
8043  furnitures[furn_at_pos] += 1;
8044  }
8045  }
8046  }
8047  return std::make_pair( terrains, furnitures );
8048 }
